title: beef baked with yogurt
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove all fat from meat and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Heat oil in Dutch oven over medium heat.
Brown meat on all sides, about 1/4 at a time.
Remove from pan and set aside.

title: orange fluff
directions: Mix jello and water.
Add ice cubes and stir until thick. Remove any unmelted ice cubes.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Beat until smooth with hand mixer.
Fold in oranges and marshmallows.
Chill 2 hours.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt pan or cake pans.
Mix all together. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Mold in 2 small loaves and top with bread crumbs.
Bake in 325° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.
Recipe can be halved.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken and remove skin and bones.
Place chicken in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour broth over chicken; salt and pepper to taste.
Spread undiluted soup over chicken (add peas and carrots, if you like).

title: sunrise coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch (12-cup) Bundt or tube pan.

title: turkey (or chicken) and rice casserole
directions: Combine turkey or chicken, rice, celery, onion, soup and mayonnaise in casserole dish.
Top with crushed corn flakes and melted margarine.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Combine mixed vegetables, soup and ground beef.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbling.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Mix hot water, sugar, salt and oleo;
let cool.
Measure warm water in bowl and sprinkle in yeast;
let dissolve.
Add to first mixture.
Add beaten egg.
Add 1/2 of the flour, beating well. Add the rest of the flour.
Knead just enough to shape the dough. Place in greased bowl and put in refrigerator overnight.
Shape in rolls, letting them rise for 1 hour, approximately.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: cranberry ice
directions: Boil berries in water until all berries have popped.
Mash through colander, discarding pulp.
Add sugar and stir until sugar is completely dissolved.
Pour into pan and freeze, cutting through mixture 2 or 3 times as it sets up.
Serve in sherbet cups.
Great at Thanksgiving with turkey meal.

title: poor man's cookies
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, salt, vanilla and cream.
Stir in 1 cup flour at a time.
Dough should be stiff.
Chill.
Take a small amount at a time on a lightly floured surface.
Roll 1/8-inch thick.
Cut in 2 x 3-inch triangles.
Make a little slit in middle of each.
Drop in hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Turn once. Drain on paper towel and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: instant ice cream
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, cream, instant pudding mixes, white sugar, brown sugar and salt.
Pour in freezer and freeze.
For 1 gallon freezer.

title: neiman marcus brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
Grease and flour a 9 X 13 inch bake pan.
Mix cake mix, 1/2 c. margarine and 1 egg.
Press into pan.
In a separate bowl, mix cream cheese, remaining 1/2 cup margarine, remaining 2 eggs, vanilla and powdered sugar until smooth.
Pour over cake mixture.
Sprinkle top with pecans.
Bake about 55 minutes or until filling appears set when pan is gently shaken.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Cut into bars of desired size.

title: italian pot roast
directions: Have eye of round roast at room temperature.
Sprinkle with coarse black pepper or other seasoning.
Preheat oven to 500° and bake 5 minutes per pound.
Turn oven off and do not open for 2 hours.
Roast will be pink.
Great for Sunday dinner or company.

title: baked potato spears
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise into wedges.
Brush with salad dressing.
Season with onion salt and pepper.
Place on greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: quick peanut candy
directions: Grease large baking sheet. In 3-quart saucepan, mix corn syrup and sugar, stirring constantly. Bring to boil over medium heat. Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter. Add cereal and peanuts. Quickly stir until well coated. Spoon onto baking sheet. With greased hands, pat evenly to 1/2-inch thickness. Cool. Break into pieces.
Store between sheets of waxed paper in covered container.
Makes 1 1/4 pounds.

title: funny cake
directions: Mix water, 1 1/2 cups sugar and cocoa in 3-quart saucepan and cook until soupy; set aside.
Mix egg, 2 cups sugar, butter, milk, flour, baking powder and pinch of salt together.
Divide sauce into pans, then spoon filling over top (5 spoons).
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and baking soda; stir and allow to cool. Cream shortening with 1 cup sugar. Add eggs and date mixture. Sift flour and salt; mix well with other ingredients. Pour into a well-greased 8 x 12-inch pan and sprinkle the chocolate chips, nuts and 1/2 cup sugar over the top. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: spice ornaments
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll out or pat out with hands on wax paper.
Cover with cinnamon.
Cut into shapes and place on cookie sheet.
Cut hole in top of shape with drinking straw.
Bake at 200° for approximately 2 or 3 hours, until dry and hard.
May want to put ornaments on cookie rack to let bottom dry.

title: penuche frosting
directions: Mix together 1/2 cup melted butter and 1 cup brown sugar.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup evaporated milk.
Bring to a boil while stirring constantly.
Cook to lukewarm.
Add 1 3/4 cups powdered sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Great on yellow cake!

title: senate bean soup
directions: Soak beans as called for. Combine ingredients; cook for 1 1/2 hours. Remove 1 cup of beans and mash; add to pot. Cook for additional 30 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix sugar and eggs with mixer until dissolved.
Add milk and continue mixing with mix, then add cooking oil, vanilla, nutmeg and baking soda.
Add flour slowly to this mixture until dough can be rolled out.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch on floured area.
Cut with cookie cutters and bake for 10 minutes at 350° or until lightly brown.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolk.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour; add and mix well.
Bake in cookie pan (do not grease) for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
While still hot, top with 6 regular size Hershey bars.
When melted, spread to frost.
Cut into squares.

title: corn delight
directions: Grease saucepan and saute onions and bell pepper.
Add rest of ingredients.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes to corn.
Cook down, over medium-low heat at least 1/2 hour or more until thick.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Put rhubarb into pie crust.
Beat remaining ingredients and pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes.

title: scalloped hash browns
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly in a bowl and pour into a 9x13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serves 12.

title: taco meal
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add taco seasoning, tomato soup, tomato sauce and garlic salt.
Set aside.
Mix together cheese soup, grated cheese and milk.
Heat until cheese melts.
Slice tomatoes in cubes and slice lettuce.
Arrange on plate in this order:
Fritos, rice, meat sauce, tomatoes, lettuce and cheese sauce.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash in a small amount of water (slightly).
Grease a casserole dish.
Drain squash.
Add a layer of squash, onion and cheese; dot with butter.
Add salt and pepper.
Repeat another layer of same.
Add sliced eggs.
Pour mushroom soup over top and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake until bubbly and brown, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ice box fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Dip strips of eggplant in flour; then in beaten egg, then in cracker crumbs.
Saute in small amount of oil for 5 to 10 minutes or until tender and golden brown.
Or, French fry in hot oil (375°) for 2 to 4 minutes on each side.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: pudding fudge
directions: Melt margarine.
Add pudding.
Stir in milk gradually.
Boil for about a minute, stirring constantly.
Beat in powdered sugar and vanilla (nuts).
Refrigerate for about 2 hours or until cutting consistency.
Pour into a 9-inch buttered pie plate.

title: hamburger mac casserole
directions: Brown meat until crumbly and pour off excess grease.
In a large skillet, combine all ingredients except cheese.
Mix well. Sprinkle cheese over top of casserole.
Bake for 40 minutes at 400°.
Serve with green salad and Texas toast.

title: chicken in the chips
directions: Combine chicken, soup, sour cream and picante sauce, mixing well.
Spoon 1/2 mixture into lightly greased 1.5-quart casserole. Top with 1 cup cheese and 1 corn chips.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until hot.
Serve with additional picante sauce on the chips.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix ingredients together and pat into pizza pan. Bake at 350° in greased pan for 15 minutes.

title: fat-free mashed potatoes
directions: Steam potatoes until tender.
In small saucepan, combine milk and granules.
Heat until warm.
Combine in a large bowl and mash until smooth.
Add pepper and serve.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Skin and cut up potatoes.
Heat margarine and soup.
Blend sour cream into soup mixture, then add green onions and cheese. Heat and stir into the potatoes.
Place potatoes in a 2 1/2-quart dish.
Sprinkle with extra cheese and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake as directed; let cool.
Poke holes in cake with the end of a wooden spoon.
Mix Coco Lopez and Eagle Brand together; pour over cake.
Chill.
Mix frozen coconut and Cool Whip together; top the cake.

title: crock-pot cheese dip
directions: Heat Velveeta cheese in crock-pot until melted (cut cheese into chunks).
Mix other ingredients into melted cheese.
Keep pot on low.
Serve with your favorite tortilla chips and salsa.

title: mom's baked beans
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Pour into shallow pan and cover with cheese slices.
Place bacon on top.
Bake at 450° for 1/2 hour, uncovered.
Serves 4.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: In saucepan, combine mushrooms, shoots, meat, soy sauce and pepper in broth.
Bring to a boil and simmer 4 minutes.
Add tofu, vinegar and hot sauce.
Mix arrowroot and water.
Add slowly to soup.
Stir until soup thickens.
Slowly stir beaten egg into hot soup.
Garnish with scallions.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: grandma wolfe's berry pudding
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients.
Stir in berries as desired. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
"You can add 2 tablespoons of cornstarch to regular flour in place of the cake flour."

title: belgium salad
directions: Mix all vegetables.
Boil sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Cool.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.
Let set for at least 8 hours.

title: m&m party cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Mix in flour.
Stir in 1 cup M&M's (reserve remaining candies for decorating).
Drop teaspoon of dough on ungreased cookie sheet. Decorate tops with M&M's.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 6 dozen 2 1/2 inch cookies.

title: ken's pig stomach
directions: Boil cabbage until tender.
Peel potatoes; cut into bite size chunks and boil
until soft.
Brown onion and sausage; save drippings.
Pour over potatoes and cabbage.
Mix well.
Season to taste.
Stuff hog maw with mixture.
Sew opening of hog maw with trussing string.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until hog maw is crispy brown.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans, soup, bacon, and onion powder. Pour into casserole dish.
Top with cheese and dried onions.
Bake 350 degrees for about 30 minutes or until onions are brown.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Cut shortening into flour with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add milk stirring until dry ingredients are moist.
Roll dough into a 20x14 inch rectangle; spread butter on dough.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over butter.
Add raisins and pecans, if desired.
Roll up and cut into 1 inch slices.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit bavarian
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Add lemon juice and mashed fruit, mixing well.
Chill until fruit mixture begins to thicken.
Whip cream and sugar until stiff, then fold into fruit mixture.
Fold in angel food cake (cut in cubes).
Pour dessert into bowl or 8-inch square pan.
Chill. Makes 6 servings.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Place browned beef into baking dish with the whole kernel corn, creamed corn and creamed potatoes (stacked).
Add cheese to top of creamed potatoes.
Bake in oven at 350° until cheese is melted and crusty.
Serve hot.
May be used as a one dish meal.

title: polk salad
directions: Wash polk salad through several waters and bring to rapid boil.
Boil for about 10 minutes.
Drain water and cover again with water and boil rapidly for 5 more minutes.
Drain water again.
Cover the third time with water and cook until tender and drain.
Put in skillet with bacon grease and salt to taste. Cook down until almost dry.

title: easy yeast refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix in order given.
I use 1/2 cup of the warm water to dissolve yeast in.
After mixing, place in refrigerator and cover with wax paper and place on top of bowl until dough rises to double in size.
Take out of refrigerator and roll dough to desired shape, set and let rise to double in size again (away from draft).
I cut with cutter, dip in melted butter and fold over. Bake in a 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Cream in eggs and vanilla real good and add to margarine and sugar.
Slowly blend in all dry ingredients.
Chill dough at least 3 hours.
Roll out on a lightly floured board.
Cut out with a floured cookie cutter.
Bake on an ungreased pan for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook lima beans until tender. Drain. Stir in soup, margarine and onion. Put in casserole dish. Top with cheese, then crackers. Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Serve with carrot sticks.

title: potatoes o'brien
directions: Mix soup and milk; add cheese, onion, salt, pepper and potatoes.
Place in a greased casserole pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients except butter and apples, adding milk gradually until batter pulls.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Stand butter in baking pan, larger than 13 x 9-inch, and place in oven until butter melts.
Grease pan with melted butter, pouring remainder of butter into batter.
Mix well and pour batter back into baking pan.
Lay apple slices on top using as many as you can so that batter is hardly visible.
Sprinkle sugar over apples and batter and do the same with cinnamon.
Put little dabs of butter all over the top of the cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: thai turkey
directions: Coarsely shred turkey breast meat (shredded turkey should equal about 3 cups) and thinly slice green onions.
Cut red pepper into 2-inch long matchstick thin strips.
In small bowl, mix garlic, soy sauce, cilantro, honey, curry powder, sesame oil, cornstarch, crushed red pepper and 1/3 cup water until well blended.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: In a bowl, combine the flour, sugar, and cinnamon.
In a mixing bowl, beat the eggs, oil, and vanilla.
Stir in sweet potatoes.
Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool for 5 minutes before removing from pans to wire racks.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: butterballs
directions: Mix ingredients together thoroughly.
Chill and then roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients, then beat, beat and beat.
Best served at room temperature.
Serve on crackers or party sliced assorted breads.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl, except egg.
Stir in egg last.
Refrigerate.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: macaroni with ham and broccoli
directions: Prepare macaroni as package directs.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except cheese.
Pat in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake 55 minutes until bubbly.
Cover top with cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: company beans with rice
directions: Saute onion and garlic.
Add tomatoes, zucchini and oregano. Cover and let simmer until vegetables soften.
Add beans.
Simmer together until vegetables are just done.
Add salt if desired. Pour over cooked rice and cover with shredded cheese.
Serves 4.

title: gone all day stew
directions: Mix together soup, water and flour until smooth.
Combine remaining ingredients in covered roasting pan.
Bake at 275° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: amish dump cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes in a greased and floured glass baking dish.

title: nesselrode pie
directions: P.S.
Depending on size of eggs, there should be enough for two 8-inch pies.

title: flaky pastry
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Combine egg, vinegar and water and stir into dry ingredients until all is moistened. Shape into a ball.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
This makes five 9-inch crusts.
(This freezes well.)

title: salsa tomatoes
directions: Core tomatoes and chop coarsely.
Add onions, cilantro and spices.
Mix well and let stand for at least 1 hour to blend flavors.
Serve as a side dish.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: block party beans
directions: Brown beef and drain fat.
Add onion and celery and cook until tender.
Stir in tomato soup, paste and catsup; simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Spoon into large roaster and add all remaining ingredients; stir well.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour. Yield: about 25 servings.

title: turkey chili
directions: Cook turkey until no longer pink in skillet.
In slow crockery cooker combine with all ingredients.
Cover, cook on high heat for 2 to 3 hours.

title: fritter batter
directions: Use for onion rings or mushrooms or apple slices.
Coat with flour, dip in batter and allow excess to drip off.
Deep fry at 375°.

title: peach chutney
directions: In large saucepan, boil vinegar and sugar 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 20 to 30 minutes or until peaches are tender and chutney is thickened.
Spoon hot chutney into 5 or 6 clean, hot 1/2-pint jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Seal with lids. Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes.
(To peel peaches easily, dip into boiling water 1 minute, then quickly into cold water.
Slip off peel with paring knife.
Also, boiling water bath may be omitted if you spoon hot chutney into hot, sterilized jars and seal at once.)
Must be stored in refrigerator.
Will keep several weeks.

title: individual cheesecakes
directions: Cream ingredients.
Put wafers in paper-lined muffin pans. Fill 2/3 full.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Garnish with cherry pie filling.
(Three cherries and a spoonful of filling look nice on top.)

title: poor man's stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger.
Pour off grease.
Brown bacon and add to hamburger along with drippings.
Add onions and saute.
Add rest of ingredients.
Place a spoonful of mixture on half a hamburger bun until all is used.
Place on a baking sheet and broil in oven until bubbly.

title: melting moments cookies
directions: Mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Break off 36 pieces and bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cool and frost.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine chopped onion, sage, milk, egg and cornmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep, hot grease.
When done, they will float. Drain on paper towels.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Put all ingredients in a bag and shake.

title: apple strudel
directions: Melt
oleo.
Add
warm
water, egg yolk and flour.
Mix together
and chill in refrigerator for about 3 hours.
Divide into
3 portions.
Take one out to work with leaving the other two in the refrigerator.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs. Beat thoroughly. Blend in milk, pineapple, and juice.
Pour mixture over bread cubes.
Mix thoroughly. Turn into a buttered 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until delicately browned.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: chicken alexandria
directions: Cook rice as directed on packages.
Melt shortening in top of double boiler.
Blend flour.
Add broth and milk; stir until mixture thickens.
Add seasonings.
Combine rice, chicken, sauce and remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture into greased shallow pans.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or crumbs are golden brown.
Serves 50.

title: caramel pie
directions: Beat
egg
yolks;
add	1/2
cup sugar, flour, salt and milk. Cook until thickens; add vanilla.
Caramelize other 1/2 cup
sugar in
an iron skillet.
Add to preceding mixture and cook
slowly until the caramelized sugar dissolves.
Pour into baked pie shell and cover with meringue.

title: pee wees pizzas
directions: Prepare Robin Hood pizza crust per package directions. Separate and give kids individual amounts to make their own pizzas.
Cover with Prego pizza sauce, cheese and toppings of choice.
Bake on low rack at 450° for 12 to 17 minutes.

title: oatmeal treats
directions: *Note:
One cup of Grape-Nuts can be substituted for chocolate and raisins.

title: pineapple raspberry drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Puree until smooth.

title: banana split salad
directions: Peel the banana; slice it in half lengthwise, then put it on a salad plate.
Put a scoop of cottage cheese in the middle of the banana slices.
Spoon the crushed pineapple over the cottage cheese.
Top it with a cherry.
Yield:

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat skillet over medium-high heat.
Place ground beef, chopped onion and shortening in hot skillet.
Cook, stirring with a fork, until meat is broken up and has lost its red color.
Pour off excess drippings.

title: vichyssoise
directions: *Reduce 8 to 10 cups chicken stock to 6.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Melt oleo in pan; saute onion.
Add cheese and mushroom soup; mix.
Add broccoli and mix all.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: hungarian beef tips
directions: Brown meat in large frypan.
Add onions and cook until transparent.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serve over rice or buttered noodles.
(Excellent for crock-pot, low approximately 10 hours.)

title: pecan butter balls
directions: In medium bowl, stir together flour, granulated sugar and salt.
Add butter and vanilla, blending with wooden spoon until a soft, smooth dough.
Add pecans; mix well.
Shape in 1-inch balls. Bake on ungreased cookie sheets in 325° oven for 25 minutes or until firm and lightly browned on bottom.
Remove to racks and set over waxed paper.
While still warm, sift confectioners sugar over tops.
Cool completely and store airtight in cool place.

title: frozen rainbow delight
directions: Whip cream; add sugar and vanilla.
Fold macaroon crumbs and nuts into whipped cream.
Spread half of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with alternate spoonfuls of sherbet so some of each color will be in each serving.
Top with remaining cream mixture. Freeze.
Cover with plastic.
May be made several days in advance. Serves 10 to 16.

title: tangy green beans
directions: In a small skillet, cook bacon and onion until bacon is crisp and onion is tender.
Stir in vinegar, sugar, salt and celery seed.
Simmer, covered, 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook beans according to package directions; drain thoroughly.
Combine beans and bacon-vinegar mixture.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: screwy noodles
directions: Cook noodles, drain and mix other ingredients and pour over noodles.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Nice to add: chopped green peppers, chopped tomatoes and parboiled broccoli.

title: crab dip
directions: In a bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Store in refrigerator.
Serve with crackers, chips, etc.

title: george washington pie
directions: Mix flour, pecans and oleo together.
Pack into long Pyrex dish.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 400° oven.
Let cool.

title: frosted gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in soda.
Add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill until firm.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt oleo and sugar together on low heat and stir until sugar melts.
Take from heat and cool, then add eggs, nuts and dates. Cook for 6 minutes on low heat until dates melt, stirring all the while.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Stir and add Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
When cool enough to handle, roll into balls or 2-inch long logs and roll in coconut.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch greased pan, place potatoes.
Add cheese mixture.
Stir lightly.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: vegetable ball
directions: After I let pineapple drain well in a colander, I take it in my hands and squeeze it to get all the juice out that I can.
Mix all ingredients well; make into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans or chopped fresh parsley.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Allow to soften for about 15 minutes before serving.
Very good with Wheat Thins or other snack crackers.

title: chocolate croissant bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cut croissants into 1-inch cubes and place in a baking dish. In a saucepan, heat the half and half, heavy cream and salt, stirring occasionally until mixture reaches a fast simmer (do not let it boil). Remove from heat and add chocolate. Whisk until melted.

title: canadian chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix brown sugar, catsup, water and onion soup.
Spoon over chicken.
Cover lightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° until bubbly, about 45 minutes.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add blackberries and beat.
Add cinnamon, soda, allspice and nutmeg; beat again.
Add flour with sour milk.
Add eggs, beat well.
Best baked in tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: linda's banana nut bread
directions: Add soda to milk.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs. Add milk and remaining ingredients.
Bake in 2 small size loaf pans at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Mix together stuffing, butter (melted) and 1 1/4 cups broth.
In another bowl, mix together chicken, remaining 3/4 cup broth, onion, chives, celery and mayo.
Layer 1/2 stuffing in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with chicken mix then cover with remaining stuffing.
Whisk together eggs, milk and soup.
Pour evenly over all.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°; remove from oven.
Top with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes, until melted.
A great family supper.
Everyone loves it!

title: chicken suzanne
directions: Season chicken (skin removed) with salt and pepper; brown in melted margarine.
Remove to greased, shallow casserole.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Add strawberries and fold in Cool Whip.
Spread between layers and on top.
Refrigerate.

title: slaw
directions: Mix and chill.
Pour over cabbage, carrots and bell pepper.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes; drain.
Mix onion, sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Add cheese; mix half of mixture with potatoes. Spread remainder of mixture on top.
Put corn flakes or bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: ruby squares
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl. Cut in 2 tablespoons butter.
Combine eggs and milk; add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.

title: linguini salad
directions: Combine Italian dressing and Salad Supreme.
Cook linguini and drain.
Chop or slice vegetables into small pieces.
Combine with pasta and dressing.
Chill.
Best if made the day before.

title: spinach squares
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients, then mix in all the rest. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or less. Cool and cut.
Can be reheated in microwave.

title: chewy squares
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Put into greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm; don't overcook.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Bring pineapple and sugar to boil.
Add jello.
Remove from stove.
In another bowl, mix Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Add cream cheese mixture to pineapple mixture.
Chill until set. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: spinach artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop the artichoke hearts. Combine the spinach, mayonnaise, cheese and garlic in a large casserole (a 6-cup dish is about right). Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes. Yield: 8 servings.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy and 1 stick oleo; set aside.
Cream sugar and other stick of oleo.
Add eggs.
Alternate flour, buttermilk and soda. Add candy mixture and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Put in greased pan (one at a time) cherries.
Sprinkle cake mix over cherries.
Pour melted oleo over cake mix, then coconut and then nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Beat butter, sugar and egg, in a large bowl with an electric mixer at high speed, until light and fluffy.
Stir in pumpkin and potatoes.
Stir in flour mixture, a little at a time, beating well after each addition.
Fold in pecans.

title: french onion corn cakes
directions: Combine dip, water, and oil.
Mix well.
Add cornmeal and mix.
Heat a griddle or electric skillet that has been coated with cooking spray.
Drop batter from tablespoon onto hot griddle or skillet.
Cook until lightly browned on bottom and then turn over and brown other side.
Remove from pan and serve warm with butter.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Put one slice onion on each chop.
Mix rest of ingredients together and pour over chops.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: pea picking cake
directions: Mix all together at medium speed on mixer for 3 minutes.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° until done.
Cool and frost.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix together well.
Grease a 10 or 12-inch pie pan.
Pour mixture into greased pan.
Pie gets beautifully frothy while baking.
Add catsup before eating.

title: blueberry-rhubarb jam(or cherry)
directions: Cook rhubarb in water until tender.
Add sugar.
Cook a few minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Add pie filling and cook 6 to 8 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir in jello until completely dissolved.
Pour into jars and seal. Store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Mix Crisco and flour until it resembles coarse meal.
Mix egg and water together and add to flour mixture.
Mix together until dough cleans side of bowl.
Roll out between sheets of waxed paper.

title: cowboy casserole
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Brown ground beef and onion, drain. Add soups and seasonings.
Mix with cooked spaghetti.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: artelia's plain biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, then, with a butter knife, cut in shortening.
Slowly add milk until mixture is moist enough to hold together.
Turn onto a floured board.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a biscuit cutter or a drinking glass.
Bake in a preheated oven at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 12 biscuits.

title: oven french toast
directions: Set oven to 425°.
Melt butter in 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan in oven.
Make sure butter covers pan bottom when you remove from oven.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on butter.
Set aside.

title: cheese chicken
directions: Melt magarine, add garlic.
In shallow pan, mix bread crumbs, cheeses, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken, one piece at a time, first in margarine, then in crumb mixture, turning to coat.
Place in single layers in pan.
Bake at 350° until brown (about 45 minutes).

title: mexican chicken(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Take meat off bones, reserving 1 cup broth.
Cut chicken into strips or bite size pieces.
Place chicken in bottom of 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Chop onion and spread over chicken.
Spread cheese over chicken and onion; mix a little with your fingers.
Mix soups, tomatoes, all but 1 1/2 cups chips (chopped finely) and chicken broth.
Allow chips to become soggy.
Pour mixture over cheese and chicken.
Top with remaining crushed chips.
Bake until hot and bubbly, 20 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cut sirloin steak into bite-size pieces.
Brown all ingredients.
Add soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Mix flour with 1/4 cup water.
Stir into mixture.
Add tomatoes.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: lasagna
directions: Combine ground beef, garlic, basil, tomatoes sauce and tomato paste.
Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.
Cook 1/2 package lasagna noodles according to package directions.
Mix cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley and eggs together.
In 9 x 13 pan, layer noodles, 1/2 cheese mixture, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese, 1/2 meat mixture and repeat.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: fisherman's catch chowder
directions: Cut cleaned fish into 1-inch pieces.
Add all ingredients except flour, butter and cream to crock-pot and stir.
Cover and cook 7 to 8 hours on low.
One hour before serving, combine flour, butter and cream.
Stir in mixture until it is slightly thickened.

title: busy-day pork chops and potatoes
directions: Brown the pork chops in butter. Season with garlic salt and pepper. Remove pork chops from frying pan and place in a 10 x 13-inch baking dish. Add soup to pork chop drippings in frying pan and mix together. Slice the potatoes over the pork chops in the baking dish.
Pour soup over the potatoes and chops.
Bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush the cookies with a rolling pin; set aside.
Cream the cream cheese, margarine and Cool Whip together.
Set aside.
Mix milk with the pudding.
Now mix the cream cheese mixture with the pudding.

title: pia colada punch
directions: Blend 2 cups pineapple juice with cream of coconut in blender. Combine pured mixture with remaining 3 cups of pineapple juice, soda, juice of 1 lime, rum and ice. Garnish with 1 sliced lime. Makes 15 servings.

title: mayonnaise dressing
directions: Mix as you add ingredients.
Cook until thick and cool.
Add 1/2 to 3/4 pint of Miracle Whip mayonnaise.

title: best doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add shortening.
Add flour, sifted with salt, baking powder and spices, alternately with milk.
Roll on lightly floured surface to 1/2-inch thickness and cut with doughnut cutter.
Fry in hot shortening (365° to 375°) until brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in skins and then peel and mash.
Combine the next 4 ingredients.
Mix with mixer.
Spread in baking dish.

title: corn muffin topped casserole
directions: In an ovenproof skillet, brown the beef lightly; drain off excess fat.
Add onion and pepper.
Cook until tender; stir in corn, tomato sauce, chili powder and salt.
Prepare corn muffin mix as directed on package.
Spoon onto mixture and bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together and pour in baking dish; cover with thin slices bacon.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: zesty shrimp dip(makes about 2 cups)
directions: In small bowl, combine ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Serve with assorted fresh vegetables or potato chips.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in covered microwave-safe dish but do not stir.
Microwave 5 minutes on High.
Add vanilla.
Beat well with mixer until thick.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool until firm; cut into pieces.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, beat well.
Bake at 350 degrees about 45 minutes.

title: kraut casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread the sauerkraut and top with the corned beef.
Combine the biscuit mix, milk, mayonnaise and eggs. Pour over the kraut and corned beef.
Arrange the cheese slices over the batter.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: bran muffins
directions: Beat egg slightly.
Mix with cereal and milk.
Stir slightly. Add oil.
Combine the rest of the ingredients.
Do not overstir.

title: monkey bread
directions: Separate biscuits and cut into quarters.
Put into plastic bag containing 1 cup brown sugar and cinnamon.
Shake to coat well. Remove and place into greased Bundt or tube pan.
Melt 1 stick margarine in saucepan.
Add 1 cup brown sugar and heat until dissolved.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove from pan immediately.

title: cracker candy
directions: Spray your cookie sheet with Pam and line with foil.
Lay crackers on the sheet.
In a boiler, place butter and brown sugar. Stir until it comes to a boil.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Pour all over the crackers.
Bake for 5 minutes at 400°.

title: mama's roast
directions: In large pan, place roast on large piece of aluminum foil. Bend aluminum up to hold vegetables.
Add vegetables and vegetables for seasoning.
Put both soups on and around roast. Add wine.
Wrap foil tightly around the whole thing.
Roast at 350° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
With cornbread, it's a whole meal!

title: almond joy cake
directions: Bake cake, freeze.
When frozen, slice lengthwise to make 2 layers.
Mix evaporated milk, sugar, marshmallows and vanilla, bring to boil slowly, boil for 3 minutes, then add pecans and coconut.
Spread on 1 layer of cake, top with other layer of cake. Put your favorite chocolate icing on top.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Combine dry ingredients with butter, etc.
Stir in oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Drop onto cookie sheet, the size of walnuts.
Bake approximately 8 minutes at 400°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix
flour,
sugar,
soda, salt and cinnamon.
In large bowl, beat
eggs;
beat in oil.
Gradually add flour mixture. Mix
in carrots
and nuts.	Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch rectangle pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or
pour into
three
8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add syrup, eggs, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in pecan halves; turn into pie shell. Bake in preheated 350° oven until filling is firm.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Make the cake according to the directions on the box.
While warm. poke holes with a straw.
Pour three- fourths of the coconut milk on top.
When cool, top with the cool whip, the rest of the coconut milk and the pine apples.
Sprinkle the coconut on top.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook over medium heat sugar, corn starch and water stirring constantly, until thick.
remove from heat, stir jello and let cool.
Add strawberries.
Pour into cooked pie crust. refrigerate until jelled.
top with Cool whip.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water. Add pineapple and other ingredients. Place 4 hours in refrigerator.
Prepare topping.

title: miracle soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pressure cook 5 minutes or put in regular stockpot and cook.

title: dark nut date bread
directions: Add butter and salt to hot coffee and soak dates; let cool. Add sugar, eggs, flour, soda, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into two 9 x 4 1/4 x 3-inch loaf pans which have been greased and lined with wax paper.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.

title: cheesy party log
directions: Marinate cream cheese in soy sauce.
Roll in sesame seed. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: "mother's" lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar,
cornstarch
and water, cook until it's thick and clear.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased pans.
Bake at 450° until lightly browned.

title: apple salad
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Stir into cream (not whipped). Add pineapple.
Cook in double boiler or thick pot.
When thick, remove from heat.
Add butter and cool.
Peel and dice apples; add cherries and nuts, then stir in cooled dressing.

title: ham and cabbage soup
directions: In a large soup pot, cover ham bone with cold water.
Tie peppercorns, cloves, garlic and parsley in a cheesecloth bag and add to soup pot.
Simmer, covered, for 2 to 3 hours.
Discard cheesecloth bag.
Remove bone; cut meat from bone.
Cut meat into bite sizes.
Discard bone.
Return meat to soup pot; add potatoes and carrots.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Add cabbage and simmer 15 minutes.
Add salt to taste and serve.
Yields 1 1/2 quarts.

title: spiced tea
directions: Dip tea and spices into 1 gallon hot water until colored and seasoned.
Sweeten to taste while hot with honey.
When cool, add juices.
Makes about 2 gallons.

title: chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in 9-inch glass pie plate.
Pour chili over cheese and spread olives on top.
Sprinkle with cheese. Microwave for 10 minutes on High, until cheese melts.
Serve with chips.

title: easy stuffed fish
directions: Saute onion and celery in olive oil until soft.
Add bread crumbs and mix.
Lay 2 fillets in greased baking dish.
Mound stuffing over fillets.
Top with remaining fillets.
Anchor with toothpicks.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until fish flakes. Serves 4.

title: milk chocolate pie
directions: Prepare, bake and cool a 9-inch crust.
In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and dash of salt.
Stir in milk.
Cook and stir this mixture until bubbly.
Reduce heat; cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Add chocolate.
Stir 1 cup of hot mixture into yolks; return to pan.
Return to gentle boil.
Cook and stir 2 minutes. Stir in butter and vanilla.
Turn into pastry shell.
Prepare meringue for pie.
Spread on top of pie.
Seal meringue to edges. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Brown the top and cool. Chill.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients.
Remove from the heat and add the butter and vanilla.
Cool and pour into pie shell.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: watergate salad
directions: Stir well.
Chill 1 hour.
Top with cherries for color.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except coconut.
Add the coconut and mix. Fill 2 (9-inch) pie shells.
Cook for 10 minutes at 350°, then for 40 minutes at 325°.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine spinach, apples and raisins in bowl.
Measure 1/3 cup orange juice from can and mix with mayonnaise until smooth.
Pour over salad and toss.

title: cheese bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast; mix well.
Gradually add water and 2 tablespoons of margarine; mix until soft dough forms.
Combine Swiss and Parmesan cheeses; reserve 1/4 cup.
Add remaining cheese mixture, egg and 1 cup flour to dough; mix well.

title: microwave marinated chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Place in a shallow container. Combine next 6 ingredients in a jar; cover tightly and shake well.
Pour over chicken and marinate overnight.
Combine green pepper, onion and water in a large glass bowl; cover with plastic wrap and microwave 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain.
Remove chicken from marinade and add to pepper mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave 7 minutes on High; stir and microwave 7 minutes more. Serve over rice.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla. Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Chill when cooled.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
Spread out hash browns in dish. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over hash browns.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: scallop appetizers
directions: Combine melted butter, garlic salt and lemon juice.
Pour over scallops.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Drain, saving marinade.
Arrange scallops in foil lined shallow pan.
Broil 4 inches below heat until lightly browned.
Add sherry to marinade.
Spoon over scallops.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Broil 1 or 2 minutes longer. Transfer to chafing dish to keep warm.
Serve with wooden toothpicks.
Serves 8.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs in bowl. Add sugar.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt and fold in.
Fold in apples, raisins and nuts.
Add vanilla. Bake in greased and floured 8-inch square pan for 45 minutes.

title: caviar delights artichoke
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; add artichoke hearts and onion.
Spread in an 8 or 9-inch glass pie plate.
Chill.
Before serving, spread caviar on top of cream cheese mixture and place grated egg on top.
Serve with crackers.

title: potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Peel the potatoes or leave skins on (just wash them) or peel them and cut into 4 chunks.
In a large, plastic bag, place potatoes, cut in chunks, soup mix and oil. Close bag and shake until potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty potatoes into shallow baking or roasting pan.
Bake, stirring occasionally, for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: jar cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add applesauce, water and eggs; mix well.
Mix dry ingredients in another bowl and add mixture. Add nuts or raisins.
Spray wide-mouth pint canning jars with Pam and fill about half full.
Bake at 225° exactly 45 minutes. Remove jars one at a time and quickly screw lid on each jar.
Let set until ready to eat.
Makes 6 to 8 jars.
One year shelf life.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat in oil with garlic.
Stir in onion soup mix, water, tomato sauce, tomato paste, salt, oregano and sugar.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: apple squares
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Sift the dry ingredients and add to the mixture.
Mix thoroughly and then stir in apples and nuts.
Batter is quite stiff.
Spread on greased (18 x 12-inch) cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: french onion soup
directions: Over medium heat in hot butter, cook onion and sugar about 10 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Add water, wine, and broth.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover, simmer 10 minutes.
Cut four 1-inch slices of bread.
Toast in 325° oven until brown.
Pour soup in 4 bowls, place one slice of bread on top.
Put cheese on bread. Sprinkle a little Parmesan cheese on top if desired.
Place bowls on pan and bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: date bread
directions: Mix dates, shortening, soda and boiling water; cool.
Add egg, sugar, flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: cream of carrot and potato soup
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan and soften onions for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add the carrots and potatoes and cook them for about 15 minutes, stirring from time to time, but do not let them color.
Add the chicken stock, bring to a boil and simmer gently for about 30 minutes, until vegetables are tender. Puree the vegetables in a food processor or blender and stir them back into the liquid.
Season with salt and pepper.
Just before serving, stir in the cream and herbs and heat the soup without letting it boil.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Deseed all your jalapenos or leave 1 or 2 with seeds for heat. Toss all your ingredients together in a glass bowl (for freshness). Put a squeeze of lemon juice and season with salt and pepper to your desire!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli about 5 minutes; drain.
In same pan, cook 1/4 cup of chopped onions until clear and soft.
Drain.
In same pan, mix the remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted.
Place broccoli in greased 7 x 11-inch dish. Pour sauce over mix.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of crumbs on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Pour over pork chops.
Let set for 1 hour; turn chops hourly.
Marinate for several hours.
Grill chops.
Serve reserved (leftover) sauce with chops.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain and add all other ingredients. Simmer for 1 hour.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cook chicken; cut off the bones.
Make a gravy with oleo, flour and chicken broth.
Cook until thick.
Add cut up chicken. Cut onion and celery; fry in 1/4 cup oleo.
Add pepper, poultry seasoning and salt.
Stir into gravy and chicken mix.
Cube bread. Pour chicken mixture over the bread and mix lightly.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes with foil on top. Uncover and bake for another 10 minutes.
If you have a glass pan, bake at 325° instead of 350°.

title: reese's cup
directions: Melt margarine.
Crush graham crackers.
Add to margarine. Add peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Spread into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips.
Spread over top of peanut butter mixture.
Refrigerate until set.
Cut into squares.

title: strawberry short cut cake
directions: Combine berries and jello. Set aside.
Grease bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle marshmallows evenly on bottom. Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour evenly over marshmallows.
Spoon berry mixture over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in glass baking dish.
Combine melted butter, honey, mustard, salt and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and toss to coat.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake chicken for 1 hour or until well browned, basting every 15 minutes.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into wedges.
Brush potatoes with half of mixture.
Bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Mix pretzels and butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip. Spread on pretzel crust.
Top with pie filling.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter with milk slow. Use a whip, then slowly add instant pudding. Mix well and fold in Cool Whip. Pour in graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: tangy corn relish
directions: With sharp knife, cut kernels from corn cobs to make 8 cups kernels.
In 5-quart saucepan over high heat, bring corn and remaining relish ingredients to boiling.
Reduce heat to low simmer.
Cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Water bath 15 minutes, using five 1 pint canning jars.

title: carrot cutlets
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs and oil.
Roll in crumbs and shape into cakes.
Fry in hot oil.
Serve hot.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Fold in the whipped cream or Cool Whip and freeze.
If
desired, the salad may be poured into individual molds before
freezing.
Makes
about 18 servings.

title: date nut cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together, then sift over dates and nuts.
Pull dates apart to get flour on every piece.
Beat eggs in different bowl.
Add sugar, vanilla and salt.
Beat well and pour over dates and nuts.
Mix well and pack in well-greased pan (tube pan).
Bake slow in a 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Better if sets several days.

title: hamburger or sausage dip
directions: Brown the meat and melt the cheese. Add all the other ingredients and mix together.

title: baked custard
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add a little cold milk.
Add egg and beat well.
Add the vanilla.
Pour in hot milk, stirring continuously. Cook over low heat, stirring continuously, until it coats the spoon.
Pour in custard cups.
Put cups in pan with enough hot water to cover bottom.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: cinnamon toast butter
directions: Mix with mixer until smooth.
Refrigerate.
Spread on hot toast.
Will keep indefinitely refrigerated.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and marshmallow creme. Mix until well blended. One drop of red food coloring can be used. Use strawberries or any fruit to dip. To use apple chunks, dip in lemon juice before fruit dip.

title: apple walnut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease 12-cup muffin pan or line with paper liners. Mix together flour, baking soda, spices and salt. Mix separately the eggs, apple juice and buttermilk.

Stir flour mixture and oatmeal in with egg mixture. Do not overmix. Gently stir in apples and nuts. Spoon batter into prepared pan, filling 2/3 full. Bake until lightly golden and tops spring back when pressed (about 25 minutes).

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla in top of double boiler and place over boiling water.
Beat constantly at high speed. Cook for 7 minutes or until frosting will stand in peaks.
Remove from boiling water.
Add vanilla and beat at high speed until thick enough to spread.
Makes enough to ice 2 layer cake all over.

title: orange chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread chicken in a pan.
Mix together juice, soup and water.
Cover chicken with juice mixture.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours, uncovering chicken for the last 15 to 30 minutes (depending on how crispy you like it). Baste often while baking.

title: pancakes for a crowd
directions: Use a very large mixing bowl.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar and mix well.
Stir in flour and milk, using either mixer or whisk.
Beat until smooth.
Add melted oleo and stir thoroughly.
Add vanilla. Pour onto preheated griddle.
Turn pancakes when bubbles appear.

title: lemon torte
directions: First Layer:
Mix butter, flour and nuts until crumbly.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes; cool.

title: crab spread
directions: Spread cream cheese evenly on plate.
Spread cocktail sauce over cream cheese.
Sprinkle pepper and garlic powder over top evenly.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Serve cold on crackers.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in an unbaked pie shell at 325 degrees.

title: puff phyllo spinach squares
directions: Arrange 6 sheets of the phyllo dough in bottom of a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan, brushing margarine between each sheet.
(Allow edges to overlap sides of pan.)
Spread souffle evenly over dough. Sprinkle with water chestnuts.
Top with remaining 6 sheets of dough, brushing margarine between.

title: pear and sour cherry crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, 1/3 cup sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Peel and core pears and cut into chunks.
Drain cherries.
Combine pears and cherries with remaining 2/3 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Put fruit mixture in a 2-quart casserole baking dish (I first spray dish with nonstick spray).
Sprinkle crumb topping over fruit and bake until golden, about 1 hour.
This is a great Fall/Winter dessert! Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken lo mein
directions: Slice chicken breast into thin strips.
Heat oil in wok; add onion, ginger and garlic.
Saute 1 minute.
Add chicken and saute until done.
Add mushrooms and vegetables and a little water.
Put on lid to steam.
Add vermicelli, soy sauce and oyster sauce. Stir to combine; heat through.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage; add chopped onion and pepper.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll biscuits very thin to look like a pencil.
Mix other ingredients in a shallow bowl or plate.
Dip rolled out biscuits in melted oleo.
Roll in a circle and place on baking sheet. Spoon sugar mixture on top.
Drizzle with honey.
You may add pecans or raisins to these.
Bake until done in a 350° oven.

title: divinity - twice cooked
directions: Stir sugar, water and Karo together in a saucepan and bring to a rolling boil.
Pour 1/3 of the mixture over the egg whites, which have been beaten until stiff.
Beat mixture thoroughly and set aside.
Cook remaining syrup to hard ball stage or until strings fly away when the syrup is poured from a spoon held about 12 to 15 inches above the pot.
Beat the last syrup into the egg white mixture.
Beat until it holds shape or until it is not shiny.
Add vanilla and pecans and drop on wax paper.
Do not cover.
Leave open to dry out. Cooking time will vary according to the weather.
It makes best on cold, dry days.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Cut chicken, separate.
In a bowl, juice 6 lemons; scrape out lemon meat from skin.
Combine with tarragon, paprika, garlic, olive oil and white wine.
Marinate chicken overnight.
Grill the following day.
Finish in the oven.
Brush with honey lightly just before serving.
Service with lemon wedge or sprinkle with lemon juice.

title: beer cheese dip
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese in food processor.
Grate Blue cheese, butter and garlic together.
Add dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce, then add 1 can of beer while mixing.
Start out with a half can and keep adding gradually until you get the right consistency (usually takes about 3/4 can).

title: pumpkin crunch cake
directions: *A No. 2 1/2 can equal to 1 pound and 13 ounces or 29 ounce can.

title: lasagna
directions: Prepare tomato sauce. Heat 3 tablespoons olive oil in a large deep skillet or 3-quart saucepan. Add onions and garlic (crushed or minced). Cook until onion is soft, stirring occasionally. Add hamburger and bulk sausage. Separate into small pieces; cook until lightly browned. Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, water, salt, pepper and oregano. Cook, uncovered, over low heat about 1 hour, stirring occasionally. (Add mushroom pieces along with onion if you like.)

title: karo nut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix flour with sugar and add to the eggs.
Add Karo, oleo and pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake slowly until done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans or 1 tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Mix oleo with cake mix.
Add coconut.
Put in 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350°
for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Place fruit on cake.

title: rice and broccoli
directions: Cook, season and drain broccoli.
Saute onion in oleo.
Mix together the prepared ingredients with the soup in casserole dish. Top with grated cheese.
Cook in 350° oven until the mixture bubbles and is slightly brown (about 1 hour).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until meat can be removed from the bones.
In a greased casserole dish, place in layers: thinly sliced potatoes, peas, chicken and part of the soup.
Repeat layers and add the remaining soup.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: butter pecan fluff
directions: Mix together pudding and milk.
Add ice cream; mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Smooth Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle crackers on top.
Freeze.

title: zucchini pizza casserole
directions: Place zucchini in a strainer; sprinkle with salt.
Let drain 10 minutes.
Squeeze out moisture.
Combine zucchini with eggs, Parmesan cheese and 1/2 of the Cheddar and Mozzarella cheeses. Press into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: dijon dressing for chicken
directions: Mix all together and rub on chicken before baking.

title: ham dip or spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing, mixing well until blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
Place a drinking glass in center of serving platter.
Drop rounded tablespoons of mixture to form a ring around glass, just touching the outer edge of the glass.
Smooth with a spatula.
Remove glass.
Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Cover with Saran Wrap.

title: cranberry meatballs
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on a rack in a baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine cranberry sauce and tomato soup. Heat through.
Add meatballs and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.
May also be used as an appetizer.

title: spinach pizza
directions: Cut up any assortment of vegetables into large chunks.
Mix all ingredients together thoroughly. Cover tightly and never stir while baking for 1 1/2 hours at 350° or 4 hours at 250°.

title: spicy chicken and peppers
directions: Stir together barbecue sauce, lime juice, Worcestershire sauce and chili powder.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Drain, reserving marinade.
Place chicken and peppers on greased grill over low coals (coals will be ash gray) and grill 10 minutes on each side or until tender, brushing frequently with reserved marinade.

title: shortcut-style lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef slowly and spoon off fat.
Add spaghetti sauce and cook for 5 minutes.
Place 1/3 noodles in 11x7x11-inch baking dish; cover with 1/3 sauce.
Add half the Mozzarella cheese and half the cottage cheese.
Repeat layer: noodles, sauce, cheeses.
Add another layer of noodles and top with sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes; cut into squares.
Serves 12.

title: deviled ham roll-ups
directions: Combine ham and onion.
Separate rolls into triangles.
Spread ham mixture over each section.
Split each in half lengthwise. Roll into crescent shape, beginning at wide end.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix well.
Store in a tight container.
Place 2 teaspoons dry mixture in cup and add 1 cup boiling water.

title: milk custard
directions: Mix flour with water and stir until smooth.
Set aside. Mix milk, eggs and sugar.
Cook until it comes to a good boil. Remove from heat.	Add flour and water mixture, stir constantly until smooth.
Add vanilla.

title: easy banana-cheese dessert
directions: Stir the cream cheese and gradually beat in the milk and cream until smooth.
Stir in the bananas, lemon juice, sugar and instant pudding.
Spoon into dessert dishes and chill.
Makes 6-8 servings.

title: crustless coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in pie plate.
This pie does not have to have a pie shell.
It makes its own oven crust. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn pie
directions: Combine diced potatoes, corn and eggs.
Add chicken and mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add milk to cover ingredients. Add butter, salt and pepper.
Top with pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: gumbo
directions: Heat oil in a large, heavy pot.
Add flour to oil and make a dark roux.
Add celery and onions.
Saute and add water.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
While this is cooking, heat butter in a small skillet.
Add tomato paste and cook over low heat, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes to this, then add to other mixture. Cook for about 1 hour over medium heat.
Add other ingredients and cook another 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned lentil soup
directions: In soup kettle, bring water to a boil.
Add garlic, onion, carrots, celery, lentils and bouillon or miso.
Return to boil. Add seasonings.
Mix well.
Simmer, covered, over low heat for 60 minutes.
If you want a creamier consistency, you can puree 1/2 the soup in blender or food processor.
Return to heat and add corn, if desired.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in parsley.
Serves 3 as a main course.

title: pumpkin cake roll(makes 10 servings)
directions: Grease and lightly flour a 15 x 10 x1-inch jelly roll pan. Stir together flour, cinnamon, baking powder, ginger, salt and nutmeg.
In a small mixer bowl beat whole eggs at high speed, 5 minutes until thick and lemon color.
Gradually add sugar, beat until sugar dissolves.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice, fold in dry ingredients into pumpkin mixture.
Spread on pan evenly and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes until done.
Immediately loosen edges of cake and turn out onto a towel sprinkled with powdered sugar, roll cake into roll starting at narrow edge.
Cool on wire rack.

title: tangy barbecue sauce
directions: Blend together mustard and molasses in a saucepan.
Stir in soy sauce, vinegar, pineapple and ginger.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil. Pour into desired jar. Cover tightly.
Makes 2 3/4 cups sauce.

title: tasty chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done, about 45 minutes or less.
Let cool.
In meantime chop celery and onion.
When chicken is cool, chop into small squares.
Mix all ingredients; add extra seasoning for personal taste if needed.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Add bananas and nuts alternately with flour, soda, milk and flavoring, mixing well with each addition. Bake in 9 x 9 pan or 2 small loaf pans until done in center.

title: peach crunch
directions: Rub 1/2 stick margarine generously over sides and bottom of a 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Pour in pie filling.
Pour cake mix over pie filling and don't worry if it is a little lumpy.
Cut stick of margarine over the top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until desired brownness.
You can double the recipe and use a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: my mother's goulash casserole
directions: Crumble ground beef into a large skillet and cook until almost done, then add onion.
Continue sauteing until the onion is transparent and the beef is well browned.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Combine all ingredients except cheese. Put into 15 x 11 x 3-inch pan.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.
Layer double slices of cheese on the top, covering completely.
Bake, uncovered, until cheese is melted, about 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and let set 10 minutes.
Add sugar and butter; stir until melted.
Add eggs and dry ingredients and mix well.
Add 1/2 nuts and 1/2 chocolate chips.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: real italian gravy (pasta sauce)
directions: Saute chopped onion, pepper, garlic and mushrooms in oil in large saucepan until onions are clear. Remove from heat.
Add crushed tomatoes, puree and paste. Place on medium heat and stir well. Add water to desired thickness. Bring to simmer. Season with rest of ingredients. Cover and "percolate" slowly for 2 hours.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar; add flour, nuts and vanilla. Shape into balls and bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until light brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Make rice according to directions on package.
Mix all together along with mushrooms and soups.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
The last 15 minutes, sprinkle on cashews or almonds.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Put coconut and pecans in bottom of floured pan.
Mix cake mix by directions. Pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Cream together and pour on top of cake. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: muffins
directions: Cream together egg, Crisco and sugar.
Add flour, baking powder and milk.
Spoon into cupcake pan (makes 1 dozen).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: whole wheat soft pretzels
directions: Mix together white flour, wheat flour, salt and yeast.
Mix hot water, cooking oil and honey.
Add 2 cups of flour mixture to water mixture, stirring to make soft dough.
Add remaining flour gradually.
Knead 3 to 5 minutes until elastic.
Make 16 balls (golf-ball size).
Roll each 18-inches long.
Shape into pretzel. Brush with water.
Sprinkle with coarse salt. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: shrimp de jean
directions: Saute celery, pepper and onion in butter until golden. Add raw shrimp. Stir until shrimp are pink. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer several minutes. Thicken with flour.
This may be served in patty shells or over toast points.
Serves 4.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Add other ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.

title: rich chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add beaten eggs. Stir in melted and cooled oleo and vanilla.
Fold in chopped walnuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Test pie with a knife or toothpick.
Pie should not be loose or runny, but chewy and on the thick side.
Cut pie slices rather small as this is a rich pie.
Serve while warm or it can be reheated.
Add a scoop of ice cream to the top for a few extra calories!

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Butter cookie sheet.
Microwave sugar and corn syrup on High for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts and stir until coated.
Microwave 3 to 5 minutes on High until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla. Stir.
Microwave 2 more minutes.
Add baking soda.
Mix and quickly and carefully spread on buttered cookie sheet.

title: banana cream supreme
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar.
Pat into your spring-form pan.

title: hawaiian candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes and set aside to cool. Mix cornstarch, sugar, salt and water and bring to a boil. Boil for 10 minutes. Add butter and pineapple to syrup mixture and pour over cooked sweet potatoes. Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mint frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in the order listed in a small mixing bowl.
Beat until spreading consistency.
Additional sugar may be needed if frosting is too thin.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water.
Add pineapple and cranberry sauce. Pour 1/2 of Jell-O mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan.
When Jell-O is set, cover with 1 cup sour cream.
Now add rest of Jell-O mixture which should be partially set and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Brown beef, add onion, salt and pepper.
Alternate layers of meat, cheese and chilies in 9 x 12 pan.
Mix flour and salt, gradually add egg mixture, beating till smooth, pour over meat, cheese & chili in pan.
Bake 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: super chocolate cake
directions: Bake the cake mix and, while hot, add Eagle Brand milk and ice cream topping.
When cool, add Cool Whip.
Crunch the Heath candy bars.
Sprinkle on top.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Put 1 cup of rice in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Add 1 cup of boiling water and seasonings to taste.
Lay cut up chicken over rice.
Cover with soups.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 250° and continue baking for 2 1/2 hours.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla in top of double boiler.
Cook over boiling water, beating constantly with electric mixer, about 7 minutes or until soft peaks form.
Stir in vanilla. Remove from heat; beat 1 minute more.
Use for icing Lane Cake.

title: sleazy corn puddin'
directions: Combine corn, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add eggs and mix.
Add butter to milk; heat until butter is melted.
Blend the milk with the corn and egg.
Put into baking dish; bake at 325° for 1 hour or until a knife comes out clean.

title: baked peaches
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut peaches in half from stem to root end.
Give a little twist to free one side from pit.
Gently twist pit from peach half (discard).
Place peach halves, cut side up, in 10-inch baking dish greased with butter.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Combine baking chocolate, butter or margarine and boiling water in a small bowl; stir until chocolate and butter or margarine are melted.
Combine brown sugar, flour, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Gradually add chocolate mixture; blend well.
Add eggs, sour cream and vanilla; beat one minute at medium speed.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes or until cake tester inserted comes out clean.
Top with your favorite frosting.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat in a large container, 1 large can of Carnation milk, chilled and whipped.

title: velveeta salsa dip
directions: Microwave Velveeta and picante sauce in 1 1/2-quart microwave bowl on High 5 minutes or until Velveeta is melted, stirring after 3 minutes.
Stir in cilantro.
Serve hot with tortilla chips or vegetable dippers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: pecan goodies
directions: Work together with hands.
Make mealy, then chill for a while. Pinch off marble size and place in each section of mini-muffin tin.
Press down in middle with thumb.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together well. Fold in Cool Whip. Break angel food cake into pieces and add to mixture. Top with strawberries mixed with strawberry glaze. Serve in large clear bowl or trifle dish.

title: barbecued corn
directions: Wrap corn in foil with 1 tablespoon butter, salt and paprika to taste.
Place on hot barbecue for 10 minutes, rotating frequently.
Best when burnt a little.

title: rigatoni with spinach and beans
directions: Cook pasta.
Heat olive oil in medium size skillet over low heat.
Add garlic and saute until golden (2 to 3 minutes).
Add the spinach, then saute, stirring frequently for about 4 minutes or until the spinach is wilted.

Add cannellini beans, grated Parmesan cheese, salt and red pepper flakes and cook for another 5 minutes. Toss bean mixture with hot cooked pasta in large serving bowl. Pass extra grated Parmesan cheese if you wish.

title: cheddar-apple-nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk and margarine; mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into well-greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes or until wooden toothpick comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes. Remove from pan.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add hot water and rest of ingredients in order given.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter rice krispies treats
directions: Microwave crunchy peanut butter and butterscotch morsels until melted (approx 1 min).
Watch closely so it doesn't burn. Mixture will be lumpy because of the peanuts in the peanut butter. Pour over Rice Krispies in a large bowl.
Mix and toss until cereal is coated. Pour into 9x13 pan lightly greased.
Cut when cooled.

title: lamb shanks or turkey
directions: Note: This can be a great meal for 2 adults or 2 adults and 2 kids.
The	lamb shanks were the original, but I find it easy to adapt
to
drumsticks
as
a most economical Big meal. The only real difference
is that with the lamb shanks, I like to cook the potatoes
separate	and have mashed potatoes with the lamb.
For turkey, cook them all together.

title: piquant sauce
directions: Use on top of meat loaf.

title: janet's chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken and Veg-all; put in 9 x 13 baking dish. Mix broth and soup and pour oven chicken. Melt butter. Mix flour and
milk with melted butter. Pour over chicken mixture.

title: scotch squares
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add brown sugar over low heat until blended.
Cool slightly.
Add egg, beat well.
Add mixed dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 8-inch square greased, wax paper-lined pan.
Grease top of wax paper also.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then cut.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: the easter egg
directions: Break eggs in a large bowl; break the yolks.
Warm milk, do not scorch.
Mix slowly with eggs until it looks like cottage cheese. Wrap in cheesecloth and hang.
Do not wrap too tight; will spoil.
Refrigerate.

title: dutch oven bread
directions: Combine
water,
butter,
sugar
and
salt;
heat until butter melts.
Cool until lukewarm.
Add yeast.
Stir in flour until fairly stiff; knead for 8 to 10 minutes.
Grease a 12 or 14-inch Dutch
oven
and lid.
Form dough into a smooth ball; put
in
the Dutch oven and let rise in a warm place.
Put the warmed
lid
on; set
Dutch oven on the coals.
Top with more coals;
bake	for about 45 minutes to 1 hour, until done.
Add additional coals gradually to avoid burning bread.

title: caramel chocolate brownies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and pat half of the mixture into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in square serving dish. Add pineapple, celery and carrots. Top with sliced olives. Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into servings. Serve on shredded lettuce.

title: chocolate bonbons
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients and chill.
Roll into balls.
Re-chill.
Dip into chocolate mixture with toothpick.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter together and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Add flour, lemon extract and Seven-Up and beat well.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured, jumbo, fluted mold.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: fried chicken casserole
directions: In skillet fry chicken in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Stir in can of cream of chicken soup.
Cover and cook over low heat for a few minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: alan's pizza dough
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well in a large glass bowl.
Dissolve the 1 package yeast in 1 1/4 cups warm water.
Add olive oil to this mixture.
Make well in the center of flour mix and pour liquid in.
Stir until you have a dough mixture and then knead well.
Let rise for approximately 1 hour or until the dough has doubled.
Make into two round balls, let set for 10 minutes, then press onto pizza pans.
They are now ready for your favorite toppings.

title: spaghetti with shrimp sauce
directions: Cook onion, garlic and parsley lightly in oil. Stir in tomato sauce, water and seasonings. Simmer 30 minutes. Add shrimp. Taste and add a little salt if needed. Simmer gently 10 minutes longer. Serve over hot spaghetti with parmesan cheese.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips in medium saucepan over medium heat.
When melted, add peanuts and spoon out by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool and enjoy.

title: meat ball soup
directions: Make meat balls by mixing hamburger, salt, pepper, egg, cheese, oregano and onion.
Saute in oil.
Put in a large pan; add soup mix and about 5 cups water.
Add vegetables and rice.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: layered banana pineapple dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press firmly onto bottom of pan.
Arrange banana slices on crust.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook, then drain broccoli cuts; set aside.
Brown onion in butter until tender.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Cook until cubes dissolve.
Add garlic, salt and pepper, milk and Velveeta cubes.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Add broccoli and simmer.
To thicken, mix 1/2 cup milk with 5 tablespoons flour and add to soup.

title: chocolate monkey
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender; process until smooth.
Yields 4 1/4 cups.

title: spicy apple crunch cake
directions: Combine 1 cup firmly packed brown sugar and 1/2 cup oil.
Beat well.
Blend in 2 eggs and 1 cup sweetened applesauce.
Mix well. Add the flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, salt and cloves, alternately with 1/4 cup milk.
Stir in 1 cup chopped walnuts. Turn into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, greased and floured on the bottom.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Dice fruits; chop pecans.
