Coat with flour and set aside. Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg; set aside.
Measure milk and orange juice; set aside.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, then lemon extract.
Blend well after each.
Add flour and milk/orange juice mixtures alternately.
(More or less flour may be used to have cookie batter the desired consistency.)
Add fruit and drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
If batter is thick you may need to flatten the top of each cookie; the fruit tends not to move when heated.
Bake at 250° for about 10 to 12 minutes, but watch closely.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Mix well and press into 36 tiny muffin or tassie cups

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes, or until cake springs back at touch.

title: pork steak and rice
directions: Brown pork pieces and oil in a skillet.
Drain on a paper towel.
Put pork and remaining ingredients in crock-pot and cover. Cook over low heat for 6 to 8 hours or on high for 4 hours. Serves 2 to 3 people.

title: shrimp with lobster sauce
directions: Heat oil in saucepan.
Saute diced onion until soft, but not brown.
Add shrimp and garlic and saute until pink (2 to 3 minutes).
Remove shrimp with slotted spoon.

title: basic barbecue sauce
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Over medium heat, heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Use to baste poultry, ribs or sausages during last 15 minutes of barbecuing or broiling.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruits and retain juices in a bowl. Mix pudding with fruit juices. Add fruit. Mix and serve.

title: apfel strudel
directions: Use any standard recipe for puff pastry.
To save time, use prepared puff pastry which can be purchased in sheets in the grocery store.
Roll out puff pastry to a very thin layer.
Use a pastry cloth which has been floured thoroughly.
The dough should be about 18 inches long and 6 to 7 inches wide.
Mix apples, raisins, almonds, sugar and cinnamon in a bowl.
Spread this mixture on the dough, leaving a 1-inch border on all sides.
At the end of the dough farthest away from you, fold over the 1 inch of dough onto the apples.
Then fold over the inch on each side. Grasp the pastry cloth on the far side and pull carefully up and towards yourself, making the dough form a roll.
Using a pastry cloth to drop the roll, place it on a greased sheet pan, seam down. Beat the egg and brush about 1/2 of it onto the strudel top to form a glaze.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Serve a la mode or with whipped cream.

title: artichoke dip
directions: In a medium bowl combine all ingredients and blend well. Spread in a 9 inch pie plate and bake 20 minutes at 355°F.

title: darling stew
directions: In large pot, brown ground beef and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours until done.
Serve with corn bread.

title: baked cabbage with rice
directions: Spread 1/2 cabbage in greased casserole dish.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add rice and brown.
Pour over cabbage.
Brown hamburg and sprinkle over rice.
Add salt and pepper.
Top with rest of cabbage and then pour combined boiling water and tomato sauce on top.
Sprinkle with vinegar.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours in covered casserole dish.

title: curry sauce
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a heavy pan; add chopped onion and saute until limp. Stir in garlic and curry powder, cook about 1 minute more. Add flour, cornstarch, sugar, salt and cayenne; stir over low heat until blended and bubbly. Gradually stir in chicken broth and whipping cream; cook over low heat, stirring until thickened. Makes 3 cups of sauce.

title: egg salad sandwich
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Makes 2 cups filling (enough for 6 sandwiches).

title: fried bananas
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cook in deep oil at medium heat (350°) until golden brown.
Drain and roll in white sugar.
Enjoy.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pour in well-greased square cake pan.
Mix second 3 ingredients and pour over first 3 ingredients. Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oreo cookie freeze
directions: Mix cookie crumbs with melted margarine; spoon into a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Spread ice cream on crumbs and re-freeze. Bring to a boil the sugar, milk, vanilla, semi-sweet chocolate and margarine.
Boil for 1 minute (stirring constantly).
Cool. Set aside 1/4 cup of chocolate sauce.
Spread remainder of sauce over the ice cream layer and re-freeze.
Spread Cool Whip over chocolate layer.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Dribble the 1/4 cup chocolate sauce (which was set aside) over top.
Re-freeze.
May need to slightly thaw before cutting to serve.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place yeast in warm water. Cream margarine and sugar in large bowl. Add egg. Add dissolved yeast, then flour. Mix well. Place in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: macaroni and tomatoes
directions: Heat oil in skillet. Add onion, bell pepper and celery. Fry until tender. Add tomatoes and cook for 5 minutes more. Add cooked macaroni and mix well. Cook slowly for 10 minutes. Stir often. Makes 6 generous servings.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Saute seasonings; add pork sausage and cook until seasonings are tender and pork is cooked.
Add chicken and cook about 10 minutes more.
Crumble cornbread in a large bowl and mix with bread.
Add chicken mixture and mix well.
Add enough chicken broth to make mixture very moist.
It will dry out during baking. Put in a baking dish and bake at 325 degrees for about 1 hour.

title: all-american meat loaf
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Place on a lightly greased rack of a broiler pan and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Combine last 4 ingredients and spoon over meat loaf and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder.
Cream the butter, adding sugar gradually. Add egg and lemon rind. Combine ingredients.
Mixture will be very stiff.
Place into buttered 8-inch square pans.
Butter hands to spread mixture into corners. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: cupid's cookie hearts(heritage recipe)
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine flour, spices and baking soda. In large mixing bowl beat butter or margarine on medium speed 30 seconds.
Add brown sugar, beat till fluffy.
Add eggs, beat well. Add flour mixture, beat well.
Apply seal, chill about 2 hours.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spray or grease muffin tins.
Spoon batter into tins, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 18 minutes, until done.

title: larkin's chili
directions: Brown sausage in oil.
Remove and save.
Add onions and garlic.
Saute until tender.
Return sausage to the pot and add tomatoes, paste, puree, celery and spices.
Mix.
Add beer and cook over low heat for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with red kidney beans.

title: salad dressing
directions: Blend in blender to mix.

title: sally's company cole slaw
directions: Pour over slaw.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Wash, rinse and drain wild rice.
Saute mushrooms, celery and onion in butter.
When golden, remove from heat and stir in soup, water, pimentos and soy sauce.
Mix with rice.
Pour into buttered 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until hot and bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Serve with chips.

title: creme punch
directions: Let sherbet, ice cream and fruit punch melt for 2 to 3 hours before making punch.
Put all the ingredients in punch bowl and mix well.
Makes 20 to 30 cups.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter or oleo and add saltines.
Press into a 9-inch pie plate.
Melt 1/4 stick butter in skillet.
Add onions. Cook over medium heat until tender, about 15 minutes.
Do not brown.
Put into pie crust.
Heat milk in skillet.
Beat eggs and add to milk with salt, pepper and a hint of nutmeg.
Heat until hot; do not boil.
Pour over onions.
Add cheese to top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken; pour over chicken. Cover; bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: black bean and rice tostada
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package. Add beans, corn, and taco seasoning; mix well. Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Top 10 crisped tortillas with rice mixture, lettuce, taco sauce, and cheese.
tags: taco bell home originals soft taco

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Saute beef and onion together in skillet.
In a large saucepan, stir together the next 4 ingredients.
Heat on medium to medium- high, or until cheese is melted.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer tortillas, ground beef and sauce.
Repeat layers twice.
Cover and heat in oven at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Remove cover; heat for 10 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: carrot cake icing
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients well and spread on tops only of cooled cake.
Sprinkle tops of layers with chopped nuts.
Icing will fall over tops of each layer and give a pretty effect or you can ice entire cake.

title: chicken delight
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat to boiling point.
Place chicken pieces in baking dish and pour sauce over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, turning chicken once.
There will be sauce to eat with rice.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Blend mayonnaise, salt, pepper, celery seed and mustard.
Add; toss lightly.
Chill. Serves 6.

title: mom's crusty cherry pudding
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add brown sugar and oatmeal.
Cut in oleo until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press half of the mixture into bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Spread with cherry mixture.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and Crisco.
Add flour with soda, eggs and sour cream (alternately), beginning and ending with flour. Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: dorothy's oatmeal cookies
directions: Pour oleo in a bowl; stir in sugar.
Blend oatmeal, flour, salt and mix into oleo and sugar.
Stir in boiling water and nuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place a layer of potatoes in the bottom of the baking dish and top with onions.
Place a layer of the drained green beans over potatoes topped with onions.
Alternate layers with potatoes, onions and green beans until used.
Pour soup over all; top with grated cheese.
Cook at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes until done.

title: sweet bread rolls
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 1/2 cups of flour and the yeast.
In a saucepan heat together milk, sugar, shortening and salt just until warm, stirring constantly until shortening almost melts. Add the lukewarm liquid to the dry mixture in the mixer bowl.
Add the eggs.
Beat with mixer.
By hand, stir in most of the flour. Knead in remaining flour.
Place in a lightly greased bowl.
Turn once to grease the surface.
Cover bowl with damp cloth.
Let rise until double.
When dough has doubled in size, about 1 1/4 hours, punch down, divide the dough and shape into cloverleaf balls. Place in greased muffin tins.
Cover and let rise another 60 minutes, or until doubled in size.
Bake at 375°
for 35 to 40 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.

title: ryan's ultimate hot taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese onto bottom of a glass pie plate.
Spread chili over cream cheese.
Top with cheese, olives and onions. Microwave or broil for about 1 or 2 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: amish cookies
directions: Cream together the oil, sugar and eggs.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Drop by 1/4 cup scoop (4 cookies to each cookie sheet).
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar before baking.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Watch carefully so that they won't brown too much and stay soft.
(Cookies may also be made smaller, using a tablespoon for each cookie and 8 to a cookie sheet.)

title: larry's real italian spaghetti sauce
directions: In large skillet, brown meat along with minced garlic.
Season meat with onion salt and garlic powder.
Drain and set aside. Using large pan or pot, combine sauces.
Add sugar and mushrooms. Add dry spaghetti sauce; add oregano and Italian seasoning.
Add drained meat with sauce; heat and stir occasionally until desired consistency.

title: cheese and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Stir in flour and water; cook over heat until thickened.
Blend in cheese with sauce and broccoli, then add eggs, mixing gently.
Place in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Cover with crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake in 325° oven for 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Combine egg, water and vinegar or lemon juice.
Mix the first 5 ingredients with pastry blender, then add the liquids.
Makes enough crust for 6 single or 3 double pies.
Can keep in refrigerator for 2 to 3 weeks.
Put to room temperature before using.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Thaw and drain vegetables.
Combine them with 1/2 of the cheese and other ingredients, except onions.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer. Serves 6.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix dry salad dressing mix into sour cream, stirring well. Refrigerate for at least an hour before serving.

title: oven stew
directions: Layer meat and vegetables in roaster.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and pour over meat and vegetables.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours, covered tightly.

title: peas a la yummy
directions: Saute in butter the celery, onion and pepper.
Stir together soup and milk.
Mix all together; pour into greased casserole. Cover with crushed cheese crackers (Maxine uses plain crackers). Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Pick chicken off bones and put in broth.
Add salt and pepper. When broth starts to boil, pinch off can of biscuits into broth. Turn down heat and cook until done.

title: church window cookies
directions: Stir into chocolate and margarine mixture. Spoon into rolls on wax paper. Refrigerate overnight. Slice and enjoy!

title: raw apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil until foamy; add sugar, flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and vanilla.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: praline peanut butter pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Blend filling ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes longer.
Filling should appear slightly less set in center than around edges.

title: mexitalian spaghetti
directions: Brown meat; drain off excess fat.
Add onion, pepper and garlic.
Cook 1 minute.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Serve sauce over hot spaghetti.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: old fashioned apple pie
directions: Combine the flour, baking powder and salt in the bowl of a food processor fitted with the steel blade. Pulse two or three times to mix. Add the shortening and butter. Pulse until the mixture looks like coarse cornmeal with just a few lumps the size of peas. Add the ice water gradually and process until the mixture forms a ball. Remove from the bowl and shape into two disks. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for about 30 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain very well.
Mix all ingredients and form small bite size balls.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Sift together cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add egg, milk and shortening.
Beat with beater or by hand until smooth (about 1 minute).
Bake in 8-inch square baking pan at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions and cool.
Using large punch bowl, crumble 1/2-inch layer of cooled cake in the bottom.
Mix both packages of pudding with milk.
Pour 1/2 pudding mix over cake.
Spoon 1/2 can drained pineapple over pudding.
Cover with 1 can pie filling and layer with 1/2 of the whipped topping, coconut and nuts.
Repeat layers.
Chill and refrigerate.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together with a knife and add a scant 1/4 cup ice cold water to make a dough.
Roll this dough out thin into 2 crusts.

title: candied sweet potatoes or yams
directions: Peel sweet potatoes or yams.
Split in half lengthwise.
Make syrup of water, sugar, margarine and nutmeg.
Place sweet potatoes or yams in syrup.
Lower stove to medium and cook until soft.
Can be made ahead and reheated.
Delicious with ham.
Recipe can be doubled or halved.

title: raspberry swirl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray a 10-inch round fluted tart pan with removable bottom with nonstick cooking spray.
Prepare brownie mix according to package directions for cakelike brownies.
In a small bowl, stir cream cheese and 1/3 cup preserves to mix well; swirl into batter.
Fold in 1/2 pint of fresh raspberries.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt. In large mixing bowl, cream sugar, butter and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Gradually beat in dry ingredients, alternating with milk.
Stir in mini morsels.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Mix sugar, butter and egg.
Stir in milk.
Sift dry ingredients and add to batter, stirring well.
Sprinkle blueberries with a little flour and fold into batter.
Use greased and floured 9-inch square pan.

title: diet tomato soup
directions: Boil each separately, then add a dash of baking soda.
Pour milk into tomato juice.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Chill well.
Just before serving, pour juice mixture over ice.
Add ginger ale.
Add orange slices.
Yield: 2 1/2 quarts.

title: cranberry pecan bars
directions: In medium bowl, combine the 1 cup flour and 2 tablespoons sugar. Cut in margarine until mixture looks like coarse crumbs. Stir in 1/2 cup of the pecans.
Press flour mixture in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: raspberry party punch
directions: Mash berries; add sugar, juice and undiluted lemonade.
Pour over ice cubes.
Add ginger ale or Sprite just before serving.

title: mom's chocolate pie
directions: Cook over low heat, stirring continuously, until very thick. Remove from heat and add 1 tablespoon of margarine and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Pour into browned deep dish pie shell and top with meringue.
Bake in 400° oven until meringue browns.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 4 minutes, then drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with crushed saltine crackers and bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spaghetti chicken
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove from broth and debone.
Cook onion, bell pepper and spaghetti in broth.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Mix well and pour into large Pyrex dish.
Place cheese on top.
Cover and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix in order given.
Makes 12 good size muffins.
Bake at 350° for 17 to 20 minutes.

title: lebanese slaw
directions: Combine all but cabbage and pour over chopped cabbage and mix. Leave out of refrigerator for a day.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Place pineapple rings in bottom of rectangle cake pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and dot each ring with butter.
Using the drained pineapple juice as part of the liquid, prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour over pineapple rings.
Bake as directed on box.
Cool.
Turn right side up on large platter.
Top with whipped topping before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place crumbled bread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Fry and drain sausage.
Spread over bread. Blend together eggs, soup and milk.
Pour over bread and sausage.
Cover with foil and put in refrigerator overnight.
Place in oven and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and add cheese.
Cook again until done, about 30 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix peanut butter, eggs and sugar together.
Roll dough into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes until brown and slightly cracked on top.
Immediately press a chocolate Kiss in the middle of each cookie.
Let cool - Kisses will need to harden before storing.

title: beth's chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken (chopped) with sour cream, soup and lemon juice in baking dish. Melt margarine and mix with crumbs. Add poppy seed or almonds on top of chicken mixture; then top with cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Melt butter in an 8 x 12-inch pan in oven; let cool slightly. Mix together flour, sugar, cinnamon and milk.
Pour over butter; don't stir.
Mix lemon juice and berries.
Sprinkle over batter mixture.
Don't stir.
Bake!

title: biscuit bites
directions: Cut each biscuit into thirds. Place on a greased baking sheet. Combine Parmesan cheese and onion powder. Sprinkle over biscuits and bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes or until brown. Serves 5.

title: chuck wagon stew (venison)
directions: Mix the flour, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Toss the meat in the mixture to coat and reserve any remaining flour.
Brown the meat in a large Dutch oven.
(Add a little cooking oil or liquid if using venison).
When brown stir in the onion, garlic, and the remaining flour.
Add all remaining ingredients except the potatoes and frozen vegetable. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer covered for 1 hour stirring occasionally.
Stir in potatoes and the frozen vegetable (removed from the pouch)
Simmer covered for 1 hour longer or until the meat is tender, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Bake in greased loaf pan in moderate oven for 45 minutes.

title: peach 'n spice bread
directions: Mash peaches; add sugar.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Add shortening, eggs, soda (dissolved in 1 tablespoon of water).
Add flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Stir until mixed.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast with water then add cottage cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients except flour.
Add to yeast mixture then add flour.
Make a stiff dough.
Beat well - do not use electric mixer.
Let rise 50 - 60 minutes in warm place until dough is light and doubled in size; stir down.
Turn into well-greased bread pan.
Let rise 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 to 50 minutes.
Brush with soft butter and sprinkle with salt.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given and pour into greased 12 3/4 x 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 1 hour.
Allow cake to remain in tube pan for 1 hour.
Cover warm cake with following glaze.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Blend together (like pie dough) butter, sugar, flour and cinnamon; work until crumbly, then pack close over apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt bars and marshmallows in milk.
Cool thoroughly.
Whip milk and fold into the chocolate mixture.
Pour into a graham cracker crust.

title: pimiento cream cheese spread
directions: Drain pimiento, reserving liquid.
Combine cream cheese with pimiento.
(I prefer to use a table fork for this.) Add drops of pimiento liquid as needed to bring cheese to spreading consistency.
Add Tabasco and salt, blending thoroughly.

title: pumpkin upside-down pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cake mix, then chopped pecans, then pour oleo over the top. Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until knife comes out clean. May be served topped with Cool Whip.

title: spanish coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, sugars, cinnamon, salt and oil.
Remove 1 cup of mixture and set aside for topping.
In remaining mixture, add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pan. Spread topping to cover top.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Cream the cheese and margarine until smooth.
Add flour.
Mix in Rice Krispies with hands. Roll dough in small balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Press each cookie with fork to flatten. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes. Watch closely, they burn easily.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese and milk together until smooth. Then add lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in pie crust.
Top with blueberries and chill.

title: shrimp fondue
directions: Gradually stir cold water into egg yolks and beat with a whisk.
Slowly beat in flour.
Beat egg whites and fold in at last minute.
Heat oil in a fondue pot.
Dip shrimp into batter and cook until puffed.

title: sherry cake
directions: Pour ingredients into a mixing bowl and add 1 egg at a time, beating slightly after each addition.
Beat at high speed for 10 minutes.
Pour into greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry or raspberry salad
directions: Add boiling water to Jell-O; stir in frozen berries.
Add pineapple (don't drain) and bananas and mix.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in flat dish; chill 1/2 hour.
Spread sour cream on top, then add rest.
Chill.

title: "oatmeal cake"
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal; let stand while you put together.
Mix sugars and oil well.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add oatmeal mixture and stir well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a 13 x 9 pan.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Drain liquid from salmon into measuring cup.
Add milk to make 3/4 cup.
Flake salmon to remove bones and skin.
Blend in egg; stir in remainder of ingredients.
Spoon lightly into greased loaf pan or dish.
Bake 45 minutes.
Serve with lemon wedges.
Serves 4.

title: corn custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter Pyrex baking dish.
Beat eggs well; pour over corn.
Stir in rest of ingredients, mixing until well combined.
Turn mixture into prepared baking dish.
Set in larger baking pan and fill larger pan with boiling water to depth of 1-inch.
Bake 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cool chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Preparation time: 1/2 hour or less.

title: chicken green bean casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix well with sour cream, chicken soup and onion soup mix, mayonnaise.
Add beans and chopped chicken.
Pour in oblong baking dish (large).

title: frosty cool off
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan.
Heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil; cook for 5 minutes.
Combine sugar and water mixture to fruit juices in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Float ice ring or ice cubes in punch.
Serves 25.

title: hot chocolate
directions: In a large saucepan, stir the chocolate, sugar and water over low heat until chocolate melts. Stir in the milk; increase the heat to moderate and bring just to a simmer, stirring constantly. Do not boil. Remove from the heat; cover and let stand for 5 minutes. Pour into mugs. Garnish with optional miniature marshmallows.

title: easy goulash
directions: Brown ground beef.
Cook macaroni.
Mix macaroni and ground beef.
Add sauces and cook until heated through.

title: hawaiian short ribs
directions: Dredge short ribs in flour.
Place in preheated 350° oven. Cook until partially done, about 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven. Drain off grease.
Combine all ingredients together and spread evenly over ribs.
Cover tightly and cook for one hour or until tender.

title: oysters and wild rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Butter a 9 x 13 baking dish. Rinse rice and cook according to package directions until open and soft. Drain well. Slice butter and mix with hot rice until butter has melted. Spread rice evenly in dish. Cover with oysters and sprinkle with salt and pepper. In small saucepan, heat soup and half and half. Add onion and thyme. Pour evenly over rice. Bake 45 minutes. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: rocky road supreme
directions: Melt chocolate chips and sugar in double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Add beaten egg yolks to mixture. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into chocolate mixture. Whip the cream and fold into mixture.
Tear cake into pieces and alternately layer cake and chocolate mixture, ending with chocolate.
Chill. Serve with whipped topping sprinkled with nuts.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and over medium heat. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours or until chilled.
Roll out into round balls.
Dip into melted mix of chocolate chips and paraffin wax.
Let cool before serving.

title: "microwave" fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in large, buttered glass mixing bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave 10 minutes on Medium-high.
Stir and continue cooking on Medium-high 5 to 8 minutes or until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Fold in Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm. Yields 74 fudge squares.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Spread in a flat dish or on wax paper.
Melt margarine.
Roll biscuits into long rope.
Dip in margarine, then roll in sugar mixture.
Shake off excess.
Twist into any shape.
Make into a bun or knot, etc.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: pretzels
directions: You will also need 1 pastry brush.

title: horseradish-mustard sauce
directions: In medium bowl, mix above ingredients until blended. Refrigerate.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix all ingredients except onions until smooth.
Dip onion in batter, then fry in hot grease until brown on both sides.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour a large tube pan.
Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Beat oil, eggs and sugar until thoroughly mixed.
Gradually blend flour mixture into oil, eggs and sugar mixture.
Fold in carrots, pineapple, coconut and nuts.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into large tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: spiced cider
directions: In a large pot, add the sugar and spices to the water and bring to a boil.
Add the orange juice and cider.
Remove the pot from the heat and cover.
Let the cider sit for 5 to 10 minutes before serving warm, or let the cider cool and then refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Mix zucchini, cottage cheese, eggs, flour and oil in this order.
Heat additional oil in skillet.
Make patties about 1/2-inch thick.
Brown on both sides.
Serve plain or with applesauce, syrup or sugar.

title: cherry cream freeze salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Gently fold in whipped cream until well mixed.
Put mixture in loaf pan. Cover with aluminum foil.
Place in freezer.
Will keep frozen up to three weeks.

title: jambalaya(a fabulous one pot meal.)
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and garlic in a little oil until tender.
Add chicken stock, ham and sausage; cook for 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients, just to mix.
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole.
Cover tightly with tinfoil.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until rice is done and liquid absorbed.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, onions, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Roll this in chopped ham until it is completely covered.

title: plain pound cake
directions: Sift flour before measuring.
Add baking powder to measured flour and sift again.
Place sugar and Crisco in mixer and cream thoroughly.
Add eggs 1 at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately beginning and ending with flour.
Add flavorings and salt and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: anne's golden chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken until done with salt and pepper; let cool.
Save broth and debone chicken.
Saute peppers, onions and celery in margarine (about 45 minutes).
Do not brown.
Cook spaghetti in broth, adding water if necessary.
Do not drain.
Add sauteed vegetables and chicken; mix together.
Add tomatoes and cheese. Mix lightly until cheese melts.
Add peas, plus juice.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Best when made day ahead.
Freezes well. Serves a bunch.

title: busy-day rice ragout
directions: In large skillet, stir onion and green pepper in oil until soft.
Add meat, salt and pepper.
Stir until meat loses pink color.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well blended. Reduce heat.
Cover skillet and simmer just 15 minutes.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Combine flour, pecans, butter, and brown sugar in an 8 inch square baking pan; stir well.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally; cool.

title: chocolate icebox cake
directions: Cook pudding according to directions on box in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put a first layer of chocolate pudding, then a layer of graham crackers, then so on until pudding lasts.
Put in refrigerator to set for 2 hours.
When serving, put some Cool Whip on each serving.

title: corn moussaka
directions: Spread corn in ungreased shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole or a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking pan or dish.
In medium skillet, brown ground beef; drain off fat.
Add flour; cook and stir for 1 minute.
Stir in tomato sauce, garlic powder and cinnamon.
Pour over corn in dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown onion and ground beef in a skillet.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain any excess grease.
Add mushroom soup and diced pepper.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add the mushrooms.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Add one dollop of sour cream to each plate when served.
For a crowd, double or triple.
Simple and tasty.

title: ham and bean soup
directions: Boil ham and beans for 2 hours.
Add water as needed.
Add onion, carrots and cut up potatoes.
Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Combine on plate the flour and salt.
Roll the meat cubes in the seasoned flour mixture.
In a large Dutch oven or pot, melt the shortening and add the beef cubes.
Add the soup, water, onion and basil.
Cover and bake for about 20 minutes.
Add in the carrots, potatoes, celery and red wine.
Cook, covered, for 35 minutes.
Remove and serve hot.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Scoop out eggplant, soak pulp in salted water for 2 hours. Drain and boil in fresh water until tender. Put through ricer. Melt shortening in 1 1/2 quart saucepan. Add eggplant and onion. Cook about 5 minutes. Add tomatoes, celery, egg, salt and pepper and cracker crumbs. Cook until dry. Stuff eggplant. Cover with Holland Rush crumbs. Dot with butter and bake at 350° until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Warm soup.
Melt butter.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Cook about 1 1/2 hours at 275° or until chicken is tender.

title: buttermilk sherbet
directions: Dissolve gelatine in hot water.
Mix all ingredients together and put into electric ice cream freezer and freeze.
Hand turned freezer works just as well.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and toss while warm.

title: mid-east potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until semi-soft and set aside to cool. When almost cool, remove skins, cut into chunks and place in large bowl.
Add onion and parsley.
Mix oil and lemon juice together and add to potatoes.
Stir well to coat.
Season with salt & pepper to taste.
Refrigerate.
Best when eaten the next day.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Stir cocoa and baking soda in mixing bowl.
Blend in 1/3 cup vegetable oil.
Add boiling water and stir until mixture thickens. Stir in sugar, eggs, and remaining 1/3 cup oil.
Stir until smooth. Add flour, vanilla and salt, blending completely.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan or two 8-inch square pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, depending on pan.
Cool and frost if desired.

title: party punch
directions: Cook tea bags and lemon slices in 2 cups of water for 2 minutes.
Cool.
Remove tea bags and slices.
Add sugar and juice from lemons.
Add 4 cups water, vanilla, almond and grape juice. Add 2 bottle golden ginger ale just before serving.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Boil first the sugar, syrup and water to hard boil stage, 248° in candy thermometer.
Pour syrup gradually over stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add nuts, vanilla and salt.
Beat until it is creamy. Pour into buttered pan.
Cut when cool.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients together except crust.
Pour in pie shell.
Use deep dish pie pan.
Top with crust.
Beat one egg and brush over top crust.
Put slits in crust.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let set 15 minutes before serving.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place first shell in deep dish pie pan. Mix all remaining ingredients except pie shell.
Pour mixture into pie pan.
Place second pie shell on top and secure edges of pie shells together.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons margarine and flour; cook gently.
Remove from heat and stir in seasonings and sour cream.
Fold in green beans.
Place in shallow 2-quart pan.
Cover with cheese, then with crumbs mixed with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.

title: tea sandwiches
directions: Blend cheese and salt until soft and creamy.
Add pecans and dates.
Mix well.
Spread on bread.
Wrap in foil if you have any leftovers.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli to remove as much water as possible.
Saute onion in 4 tablespoons of butter.
Mix flour in water; stir well.
Add to onion.
When thick, add cheese.
Combine sauce with broccoli in a large bowl.
Add well beaten eggs.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with bread crumbs.
Dot with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: spice cake
directions: Cream shortening; add brown sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with sour milk, starting and ending with flour mixture.
Bake in 9-inch greased and floured square pan or Bundt pan at 350° for approximately 1 hour. When cake cools, glaze with mixture of coffee and confectioners sugar.

title: angel food mousse
directions: Cook egg yolks, sugar and milk until hot.
Soak gelatin in water.
Add to custard just enough for gelatin to melt.
Chill until it jiggles but not set.
Add pineapple, lemon juice, pecans and whipped cream.
Stiffly beat egg whites and fold into custard. Butter 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Make a layer of cake and top with layer of custard.
Repeat layers as necessary.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Garnish with maraschino cherries on top.
Can freeze if you wish.
This is a delightful dessert for Easter.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: pineapple-rice casserole
directions: Mix together while rice is "hot" and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: snow cream
directions: Stir milk, sugar and vanilla until sugar dissolves, then add snow and eat.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Trim fat from pork chops.
Roll in flour.
Season to taste. Place oil in skillet and heat until hot.
Brown chops in skillet. Butter a baking dish and line the bottom with potato slices. Place chops on potatoes, onion and pepper on each chop.
Pour mushroom soup over potatoes and chops.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes in oven preheated to 350°.

title: teriyaki roast tenderloin
directions: Combine all ingredients, except tenderloin.
Add terderloin and marinate 2 hours or more.
Bake at 425° for 45 to 50 minutes. Serves 6.

title: sugar-free baked apples
directions: Wash and core whole apples or wash, core and slice in half apples.
Fill cavities or sprinkle on halves gelatin evenly, using whole package.
Sprinkle on butter flavored granules.
Bake in microwave, covered, until done or bake in a 350° oven, covered, until done or desired crispness is reached.
Very pretty and tasty.
Great for diabetics.
(One fruit exchange.)

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix all ingredients except paraffin and chocolate chips by hand. Chill for 45 minutes. Then shape into small balls. On low heat in double boiler, melt paraffin and chocolate. Use toothpick to drop balls into chocolate mixture. Place on wax paper.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Mix together brown sugar and butter until well blended.
Add eggs and molasses, blending well.
Add the remaining ingredients. Chill for 1 hour.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350° on a greased baking sheet.
Decorate with Sugar Icing after these have cooled.
This recipe makes approximately 24 (5-inch) cookies.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Slowly add one egg at a time.
Add vanilla and baking soda.
Add salt to sift flour and sift 2 more times.
Then add slowly to flour, alternating the milk and mix.
Add nuts and banana; stir.
Pour in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more; test with toothpick if it comes out clean, it's done.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes before taking out.

title: low-fat banana bread
directions: Mix applesauce, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients. Add bananas.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain.
Combine cream and butter in saucepan. Cook over medium low heat until butter is melted.
Add to hot pasta alternately with parmesan cheese, tossing to mix well.
Serve hot.
May add sauteed scallops, shrimp, chicken or even sliced mushrooms and season with black pepper.

title: sugar pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add 2 cups half and half and a pinch of salt.
Pour into an uncooked pie shell.
Slice the butter over the top and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: seven step bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer rest of ingredients over butter in order given.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Cook pineapple, sugar and flour until thick and then cool. Mix 3 1/2 cups flour and Crisco; add 3/4 cup sugar, baking powder, 1/4 teaspoon baking soda and salt in separate bowl; set aside. Mix sour cream, egg yolks and vanilla.
Add to the dry ingredients and put into cookie sheet.
Spread filling mixture on top and garnish with 1/2 cup crushed walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: velvet sugar cookies
directions: Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla; blend well.
Measure dry ingredients together; add to the sugar mixture and mix well.
Roll dough the size of a walnut.
Dip in sugar and press down with a fork.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: pineapple cottage cheese pie
directions: Roll crackers fine; reserve 3 tablespoons of crumbs for top of pie.
Mix remainder with softened butter and sugar.
Press the mixture firmly against the bottom and sides of well buttered pie tin.

title: bacon-wrapped chicken livers
directions: In a large skillet, saute chicken livers in margarine on low heat.
Drain off margarine.
Set oven to 325°.
Wrap each chicken liver with a slice of raw bacon.
Pin, using a toothpick.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes, until bacon is crisp.
Serve on bed of lettuce with spicy brown mustard as a garnish.

title: french bean and chicken salad
directions: Mix green beans, chicken, French dressing and Tabasco together.
Place in refrigerator to chill for 1/2 hour.
Stir in shredded lettuce, olives, butter, tomatoes, onions, celery and pimento.
Toss until all is evenly mixed.
Serve at once on lettuce leaves or endive.
Serves 6.

title: salmon spread
directions: In a large bowl, blend all together.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.
Yields 2 cups of spread.

title: pat's chicken
directions: Roll chicken parts in flour.
Brown in oil or butter. Combine all other ingredients and pour over browned chicken in a pan.
Cover and simmer over med-low heat for 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: italian pie
directions: Cut up sausages, eggplant, zucchini and onion.
Add tomato sauce, cheese soup, mushrooms, salt and pepper.

title: amish potato soup
directions: Combine vegetables, water, chicken cubes, and salt in large saucepan.
Cover and cook until tender.
Add 1 cup milk, heat. Mix sour cream, flour, and chives and remaining milk in bowl. Gradually stir into soup base.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened.

title: p.b. graham snacks
directions: Combine Crisco, powdered sugar and peanut butter in a large bowl, with an electric mixer, until well blended.
Stir in one cup crumbs and chocolate chips.
Cover and refrigerate one hour.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Mix crumbs, cheese and tarragon.
Dip chops in crumb mixture. Place in 9 x 13-inch glass casserole.
Sprinkle lemon juice over. Bake covered with foil in 425° oven for 30 minutes.

title: texas chili
directions: Dice up onions and peppers.
Cook half with meat and half with sauce.
Let sauce slow cook.
When meat is cooked, mix with sauce and slow cook for 5 to 8 hours.

title: applesauce pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Pour 1/4 cup batter onto hot griddle, greased.
Cook until pancakes are dry around edges. Turn and cook other side until golden, about 12 pancakes.

title: baked stuffed trout
directions: Chop onion and celery.
Mix bread crumbs, onion, celery, eggs, butter and seasonings.
Stuff trout and sew sides together with heavy thread.
Bake in dish lined with cheesecloth.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
You can lift the fish out onto a platter by turning cheesecloth.
Garnish with lemon slices and parsley.

title: flan
directions: Melt 1/2 cup white sugar in heavy skillet.
When melted, pour into custard cups or pie pan.
Beat eggs, milk, vanilla, and 1/3 cup sugar until mixed -- about two minutes. Pour into custard cups or pie pan.
Place into larger pan of water and bake at 350° until set, or about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pie almandine
directions: Combine 1/2 cup milk and whipped topping mix in a chilled mixing bowl; beat on high speed of electric mixer for 3 minutes or until stiff peaks form.
Add pudding mix, salt, 1/2 cup milk and Amaretto.
Beat at high speed of electric mixer 2 minutes or until smooth and thickened.
Pour into pastry shell; sprinkle with almonds.
Chill 3 or 4 hours.

title: glazed baby carrots
directions: Place carrots in a saucepan with enough water to cover; bring to a boil.
Cover and cook until crisp-tender, about 10 minutes. Drain; remove and keep warm.
In the same pan, heat butter and sugar until bubbly.
Return carrots to pan.
Toss to coat; heat through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all together, except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
Serve on ice.
Serves 50.

title: ginger chicken
directions: Stir
together sherry, soy sauce, bean sauce, water and cornstarch.
Set
aside.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Cut into thin
bite-size
strips.
Preheat
a wok or large skillet over high
heat.
Add

(Add remaining oil as necessary during cooking.) Stir-fry ginger root in hot oil for

Add carrots and stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add bok choy, pea
pods and onions;
stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes, until crisp-tender.
Remove vegetables from wok or skillet.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix the first two ingredients; spread half of this in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
Set aside the other half.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain thoroughly.
Combine vegetables, meat and salad dressing in large bowl.
Toss and chill.

title: fudge bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate chips and 1/2 cup margarine in milk over low heat in heavy saucepan.
Stir in nuts and set aside.
Cream 1 cup margarine and sugars.
Mix in eggs.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Press two-thirds of mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread with chocolate mixture.
Spread remaining mixture evenly over chocolate.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown. Cool.
Cut into bars.
Makes 60 bars.

title: shredded beef barbecue
directions: Place beef in Dutch oven.
Combine all remaining ingredients and pour over beef.
Cover and bake at 325° for 5 hours, turning beef occasionally.
Take out of oven and shred beef with fork.

title: quick caramel coffee cake
directions: Melt margarine in small saucepan; use 2 tablespoons to grease a 12-inch fluted pan.
Place 2 tablespoons nuts in bottom of pan. Put the remaining nuts, brown sugar and water in the melted margarine.
Heat to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Cut the biscuits in half and roll into balls.
Put 20 rolls in pan.
Top with sauce, then repeat.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Invert onto plate to cool.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: I like to add some chopped nuts.

title: oregano cheddar bread
directions: Stir together the yeast and two cups of the flour in large mixing bowl.
Heat together the remaining ingredients (except rest of flour) until lukewarm.
Add to flour-yeast mixture.
Beat on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat at high speed for 3 minutes.
Stir in as much of the remaining flour as you can mix in with a spoon.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and margarine to make the crust. Press in to a 9 x 12 pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°, then allow crust to cool. To make filling, mix powdered sugar, milk and cream cheese in a small bowl. Mixer beat until creamy and
smooth. Spread over cool crust. Sprinkle nuts on top and refrigerate 30 minutes. Mix whipped topping and spread over nuts. Top with pie filling.

title: rice pudding
directions: Place rice in the cold water and boil until water is absorbed. Add milk and cook slowly until rice is done, stirring occasionally. Beat eggs; add in sugar, vanilla and cinnamon.
Pour into rice; let come to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Pour into casserole dish. Refrigerate when cooled.

title: lillian whitehurst pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until creamy.
Add sugar.
Beat until flacky.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each one.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and flavorings.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: lumberjack macaroni
directions: Boil macaroni until tender. Spread out on a large platter. Sprinkle macaroni with grated cheese, Worcestershire sauce, chili sauce, salt and pepper. Pour the melted butter over all. Mix with 2 forks until the sauce is creamy. Serve at once on hot plates. Makes 6 servings.

title: easy beef or pork steaks
directions: In large baking dish, mix soup and 1 can water.
Add steaks. Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Add flour-water mixture (just enough to thicken gravy).
Sprinkle Kitchen Bouquet; mix all together.
Put back in oven for 15 more minutes.
This is one of the easiest meats I've ever made.
Goes great with mashed potatoes and a vegetable!

title: mini ham puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop ham and onion.
Place on bowl.
Add cheese, egg, pepper and mustard.
Stir to combine.
Spray 2 mini muffin pans with vegetable oil spray.
Unroll crescent rolls and press dough into one large rectangle.
Cut rectangle into 24 pieces using a pizza cutter.
Place dough pieces into muffin pan cups. Form a crust with each one.
Using a spoon, place filling in cups. Bake for 15 minutes.

title: chicken-rice divan
directions: Cook broccoli and drain; arrange in bottom of baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/2 the cheese.
Top with chicken, salt and pepper. Spoon on cooked rice.
Blend soup and milk together and pour over top.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and refrigerate.
When ready to bake, put in 400° oven and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 27.
May be divided into 1/3.

title: tomato pies
directions: Bake individual pie shells; cool. Peel tomatoes and cut into chunks. Place in cooked pie shells. Top with mayonnaise, grated cheese, onion and basil. Bake at 325° to 350° until hot and bubbly, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Wash wild rice.
Place in Dutch oven with enough water to cover rice.
Place in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Drain and cool. Fry hamburger, celery and onion.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: chewy cheese squares
directions: Cream well 1 stick margarine and 1 egg.
Add cake mix and 1 cup of pecans.
Pat into a large 9 x 13-inch dish and cover with the following.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Blend together all ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Top with 1/2 cup chopped pecans and 1/2 cup Rice Krispies, browned in butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Mix butter in dry ingredients with pastry mixer until crumbly. Pat mixture into 8-inch square pan half way up sides.
Slice peaches.
Place in pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then pour slightly beaten eggs and sour cream on top.
Bake 30 minutes more.
Good hot or cold.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mince salmon with fork.
Add eggs and other ingredients.
Form into a greased loaf pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
The remaining 1/2 cup of soup may be diluted slightly with water to make a sauce.

title: mushroom and potato chowder
directions: In a large kettle, saute onion in butter until tender.
Add flour, salt and pepper; stir to make a smooth paste.
Gradually add water and milk, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 1 minute.
Add the mushrooms and potatoes.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add half and half and Parmesan cheese; heat through. Thicken with a cornstarch and water paste, if needed, to reach desired consistency.
Serve immediately.

title: biscuits
directions: With pastry cutter, cut shortening into dry ingredients. Add milk. Mix until mixture forms a ball. Turn onto a floured surface. Knead until smooth. Let stand to rise for 10 minutes. Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut biscuits. Brush tops with melted margarine and bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: sour cream chili bake
directions: Brown ground beef, drain off fat.
Stir in drained beans, enchilada sauce, tomato sauce, 1 cup cheese and onions.
Set aside 1 cup corn chips, coarsely crush remaining chips and stir into meat mixture.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 minutes.
Spoon sour cream on top, sprinkle with the 1/2 cup cheese and remaining chips around the edge.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy holiday cookies
directions: Measure flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt into flour sifter.
Cream butter and peanut butter with sugar until fluffy. Beat in egg.
Sift in flour mixture.
Add alternately with orange juice and blend well.
Chill dough until easy to handle.
Roll into 1-inch balls; flatten with a fork.
Bake in oven at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet; brush with slightly beaten egg white.
Sprinkle with coconut, red hots or colored sugar.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Heat oven
to
Place
butter
in baking dish and place in	oven.
Watch carefully while browning butter.
Drop fish in egg then in crumbs.
Coat well.
Place each fillet in butter, turning
to coat evenly.
Season to taste.	Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: binky batter for veggies
directions: Mix well; dip cut veggies or meat and fry.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine beef in 2 quarts of water, mixing beef until it comes apart.
Add celery, pepper and onion, cut up fine.
Cook together 45 minutes, covered (boiling).

Remove top and add remaining ingredients and continue cooking uncovered until thick. (This will probably take four or five hours, depending upon heat setting. Stir occasionally to keep from sticking.)
Serves 15 people.

title: squash bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Mix and add remainder of ingredients to first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 2 loaf pans or Bundt pan (greased).

title: oh, so easy date bread
directions: Pour
boiling
water
over dates; let stand until cool. Blend sugar,
egg
and oil well; add to date mixture.
Add dry ingredients,
which
have been sifted together.
Stir in nuts. Pour into
2 medium size bread pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for
hour,	or
until
it
tests
done.
Cool; wrap in aluminum foil.
Freezes well and can be made ahead.

title: taiwanese style fried rice
directions: Cook rice in 4 cups water.
Scramble eggs, milk and salt and pepper; set aside.
Chop onion, cabbage, green pepper and meat into 1/2-inch cubes or smaller.
Fry veggies in oleo for 1 minute. Add pork, stirring constantly.
Cover and cook 10 minutes or until pork is done.
If too much liquid, drain off most.
Add Accent, celery and garlic salt and soy sauce.
Add rice; cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Add eggs and cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: maple sugar pears
directions: Drain pears; reserve 1/4 cup liquid.
Combine syrup, sugar and oil in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. Stir in lemon juice, maple flavoring and cinnamon.
Arrange pear halves (cut side up) in a shallow baking dish.
Pour mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When serving, top each pear with a dollop of sour cream.

title: hot dog chili sauce
directions: Brown beef and mash.
Combine ingredients.
Cover and simmer about 35 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cook ground beef; drain.
Boil green peppers 5 minutes or until tender.
Cook rice according to directions.
Mix rice and ground beef.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini 10 minutes, drain.
Brown together the pork sausage and onion, drain.
Beat eggs and add to mixture, then add remaining ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole (or smaller if desired) and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: linda's angel dessert
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Beat egg yolks and a tablespoon of milk and add to the melted chocolate.
The mixture will become thick and very stiff.
Add nuts and let cool.
Slice and dice (or tear into pieces) the angel food cake.
Whip the cream and whip the egg whites and fold the two together.
Add the chocolate mixture to the whipped cream and egg white mixture by folding.
Mix half of the mixture with cake and pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass cake dish.
Pour remaining mixture on top. Refrigerate and serve cold or at room temperature.

title: tossed vegetable salad
directions: Combine vegetables and eggs.
Chill.
Mix oil and vinegar. Pour over chilled vegetables and eggs.
Toss lightly; serve on lettuce.

title: quick stuffed peppers
directions: Mix hash with onions and catsup.
Stuff peppers.
Pour sauce over all.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Place cheese on top and return to oven until slightly browned.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Heat the first 4 ingredients.
Brown hamburger with taco seasoning.
Mix with the refried beans and the heated mixture. Spoon 2 tablespoons or so of the mixture on a tortilla; roll up and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Fill pan with tortillas.
Pour leftover mixture over the top.
Sprinkle with the grated cheese and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream 2 tablespoons butter, cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Add 1 egg, 2 tablespoons milk and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Combine the rest of the ingredients. Spread 1/2 of batter in pan, then the cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool and frost with chocolate frosting.

title: hot taco pie
directions: In large baking dish layer in order, refried beans, browned meat, chili peppers and taco sauce and top with grated cheese. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Remove from oven and garnish with rings of black olives and tomatoes.
In the center, add sour cream and top with pimento.
Serve with nacho chips and/or dip size corn chips.

title: barbecue meatball sauce
directions: Options:
Five pound package of frozen meatballs or prepare own from scratch.

title: boiled custard
directions: Use a large pot since this boils real high.

title: cheesy green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and reserve 1/4 cup drippings. Crumble bacon and reserve 2 tablespoons of bacon.
Cook beans; drain well.
Add mushrooms and onions to reserved 1/4 cup drippings in skillet.
Cook for 10 minutes; drain.
Add bacon, hot beans and pepper; mix lightly.
Spoon into a serving dish. Microwave process cheese as directed on label.
Pour over green beans and sprinkle with reserved bacon.
Serves 10.

title: pork cantonese casserole
directions: Place pork and sliced vegetables in greased casserole.
Mix other ingredients and pour over pork and vegetables.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 400° for about 1 hour or until pork is tender.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream eggs, butter, sugar and vanilla together well.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Form into 1-inch roll.
Refrigerate 1 hour or overnight.
Slice and place on baking sheet.
Press flat with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: grandma's hamburger hot dish
directions: Fry hamburger while Juniorettes are cooking.
Mix browned meat with cooked pasta and onion.
Mix soups with water and add to meat mixture.
Season with garlic salt, if desired.
Add cheese.
Put in a 10 x 10 x 2-inch casserole and heat through in a 350° oven.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet; drain, then add spaghetti sauce and cottage cheese.
While cooking hamburger, cook noodles and drain.
Place in baking dish, starting with layer of hamburger mixture, noodle layer next and Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbling.

title: creamy mexican dip
directions: Bring all ingredients to room temperature. Combine and mix with electric mixer until smooth. Chill and serve with tortilla chips or vegetables.
tags: dry Hidden Valley salad dressing mix

title: corn-tomato casserole
directions: In buttered baking dish,
add
corn, tomatoes and green peppers; mix.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.	Cover with crumbs, then cheese and dot with
margarine.
Bake	for
30 minutes at 375°.
Serves 8.

title: blueberry muffin
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: company rice
directions: Spray a casserole dish (1 1/2-quart or 2-quart) with cooking spray.
Add all ingredients.
Stir.
Cover tightly with foil or glass lid.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry limeade
directions: In blender container, blend strawberries well.
In pitcher, combine pureed strawberries, water, lime juice and sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Serve over ice.
Garnish with whole strawberries, if desired.

title: hardtack candy
directions: Boil syrup, sugar and water to hard crack stage (300°). Remove from heat.
Add flavor of choice and food coloring.
Stir well to mix.
(Hint:
Don't use metal or plastic spoon.)
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Allow to cool.
(Mixture will set quickly.
You will need to work fast.) Crack candy to desired slice and toss with powdered sugar.

title: misty's people crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Pour water into a large bowl.
Add the chicken bouillon cubes and crush them with a fork. stir in the yeast and let stand for 5 minutes.
Add the tomato juice, 1 cup all-purpose flour and the wheat germ.
Stir to form a smooth batter.
Stir in the remaining all-purpose flour and the whole wheat flour.
Sprinkle flour on a cutting board, then take a couple of handfuls of dough out.
Work into a small ball.
With a rolling pin, flatten the balls to about 1/4-inch thick.
Use a table knife to cut out your people shapes.
Use a spatula to put your people shapes onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Let them dry in the turned-off oven for 4 hours or more.
"For dogs only."

title: peanut butter cup pie
directions: Chop peanut butter cups. Set aside. Melt kisses in microwave on High for 1 minute or just until chocolate is melted. Stir in 3 1/2 cups Cool Whip. Spread 1/2 chocolate kisses topping mix into pie crust. Sprinkle peanut butter cups over chocolate layer. Top peanut butter cups with the remaining 1/2 chocolate mixture. Refrigerate 3 hours or until set. Spread the remaining Cool Whip over pie. Garnish with chocolate kisses.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix in a bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Let rise for 2 hours before baking.
Bake at 425°.

title: ice box fruit cake
directions: In bowl, stir together the pecans, walnuts, raisins, cherries, condensed milk and vanilla wafers.
Dough will be thick, you will need to use your hands.
Form dough into a ring shape on top of a dinner plate.
Wrap in many layers of plastic.
Wrap in foil or wax paper.
Allow to age one week in the refrigerator; the flavors will blend and all of the milk will be absorbed into the cake.

title: crispix party mix
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix the butter, Worcestershire sauce and garlic together in a saucepan.
Pour over the cereal mixture.
Stir.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 225°. Stir every 15 minutes.
Bake 30 minutes uncovered.

title: no peek stew
directions: Cook turkey; remove from bones.
Set aside.
Place onions, celery, carrots and potatoes in casserole and sprinkle with thyme, salt and pepper.
Add broth and cook until vegetables are done. Add turkey and cook until blended.
Can be thickened with cornstarch and water.

title: tic tac tostadas
directions: Brown beef in skillet; add just enough spaghetti sauce to coat meat.
Spread meat mixture on taco shell.
Cut 1 slice American cheese into 6 strips.
Arrange on meat mixture to form tic-tac-toe. Cut bell pepper into small strips and use for X's on tic-tac-toe. Slice olives as to form O's.
Bake at 350° until cheese is slightly melted.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll out the size of an English walnut.
Bake at 325° until cookies start to crack open.
Very quickly put a chocolate Hershey's kiss candy down the middle. Cool and eat.

title: caramel cream whip
directions: Mix the cream cheese, Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch graham cracker base.
Spread on caramel topping. Melt margarine in skillet.
Add pecans and coconut; stir until coconut browns.
Add as topping over caramel topping.

title: super fruitcake
directions: Mix flour with fruit and nuts.
Cream butter and sugar real good.
Add eggs (one at a time) and beat well after each one.
Add fruit mixture to batter and fold all together; add flavoring. Grease a 10-inch tube pan and line with brown paper (grease paper).
Add cake batter.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 275°. Check to be sure it is done after this time.
It may need to bake a while longer.
This is a delicious cake.

title: butterscotch chiffon pie
directions: Soak gelatine in cold water 5 minutes.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually beat in brown sugar, then the milk.
Add butter and salt and cook in top of double boiler over hot, not boiling water, stirring until mixture coats the spoon. Stir in gelatine.
Cool and add vanilla.
Beat egg whites until quite stiff.
Add granulated sugar gradually while continuing to beat until stiff.
Fold into cooled custard.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: company casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Cook noodles and set aside.
Brown meat in 3 tablespoons margarine.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, onion and pepper. Spread half the noodles in a greased casserole.
Cover with cheese mixture, then remaining noodles.
Place 2 tablespoons margarine over it.
Put meat sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Can be made day before serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Put noodles to boiling.
Brown ground chuck, onion (cook out water of onion).
Add olives and mushrooms. Add spaghetti sauce and simmer on low.
After cooking sauce, add dash of spice and cottage cheese.
Simmer about 5 minutes and turn off sauce.
In large baking dish, lay out a layer of noodles. Cover noodles in sauce.
Spread out a layer of cheese.
Repeat this process until ingredients are used.
Make sure your top layer is meat sauce and sprinkle with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese. Cook 45 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Mix first three ingredients thoroughly.
Bring to a boil on medium heat, boil for 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow cream and chocolate morsels.
Mix well.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Cool and cut.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Line muffin (small) tin with foil liners.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in each liner.

title: holiday chocolate almond crisps
directions: Toast chopped almonds on baking sheet in a preheated 300° oven for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring them once or twice for even roasting.
Put raisins in a medium bowl.
Spoon rum over raisins. Cover and let stand overnight.
Line a baking sheet with foil or waxed paper.
Melt chocolate in a double boiler over low heat or in the microwave.
Cool slightly, then add to raisin and rum mixture with almonds and candied peel.
Take small amounts of mixture and with teaspoon, place in mounds on prepared baking sheet.
Let dry slightly, then refrigerate until firm.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie(county fair first prize)
directions: While preheating oven to 350°, toast 1 1/2 cups of pecans with 3 tablespoons of butter in an empty pie pan, stirring often, until golden brown.
Watch closely because they burn easily.
While pecans are browning, in an electric mixer bowl, break eggs.
Mix slowly while adding Karo, brown sugar and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Gently mix in pecans and butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until set.

title: herbed curry chicken salad
directions: In processor, whirl egg with lemon juice, Dijon mustard and salt for 5 seconds.
With blender on, slowly drizzle in olive and safflower oils.
Add vinegar, basil and mint.
Pulse on and off until herbs are chopped.
Add sour cream and curry; blend well. Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients and add the food coloring until bright yellow.
Spoon the mixture into the pie shell.
Place in the refrigerator until you are ready to serve.
You can place fresh lemon slices around the side for decoration.

title: weeping salad
directions: Layer the lettuce, cauliflower, onion, peas and water chestnuts.
Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and Parmesan cheese; spread over the top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, crumble the bacon and eggs over the top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Do not toss until ready to serve.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and 1 1/2 cups flour to mixture, then add vanilla.
Put remaining cup of flour on chopped fruit and nuts, add to rest of mixture.
Make into 4 or more rolls, chill and cut.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Can be frozen and used later.
(I always double recipe.)

title: sweet-sour spareribs
directions: Bring all ingredients for sauce to a boil in a saucepan.
Cook spareribs for 1 hour.
Pour off grease.
Pour sauce over spareribs.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour, basting frequently. Yields 6 servings.

title: biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in butter with pastry blender. Make well in center of bowl and pour in milk.
Stir until well blended and dough is slightly dry.
Place dough on board.
Dust with flour and knead lightly.
Roll out about 1/4-inch thickness. Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Add enough mayonnaise to make pliable ball.
Roll ball in chili powder or nuts.

title: rolls
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients. Add egg, melted butter and yeast.
Cover and let rise.
Make out rolls. Cover and let rise again. Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: easy homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually, beating until mixture thickens.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly. Freeze in ice cream freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: ruth's peanut brittle
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients on high until it spins a thread from spoon.
Add 1 pat of butter and peanuts.
Boil about 7 minutes until peanuts smell and liquid has become golden brown color.
Add soda and salt quickly.
Stir in pat of butter and start dipping out with metal ladle into 7 to 9-inch buttered aluminum pie pans. Shake evenly out.
(Helps if someone will shake down while the other pours out the mixture.)

title: dishpan cookies
directions: In a dishpan, mix together sugars, eggs and oil.
Add vanilla. Sift together soda, flour and salt. Add to sugar mixture. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Drop by spoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: rome chowder
directions: Brown beef and onion in oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add tomato juice, if needed, during cooking.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix pineapple and juice with flour and sugar. Cook in double boiler until thick. Stir almost constantly. Let cool. Cut bananas over the cooled pie shell. Sprinkle nuts over bananas. Spread pineapple mixture over bananas and nuts. Spread Cool Whip over top of pie and sprinkle on nuts. Chill.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls.
Press into bottom of a 12-inch pizza pan.
Seal the sides of rolls together to form the crust.
Onto the crust, layer sausage, potatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Beat the eggs into the milk and pour on top.
Add green peppers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mezetti
directions: Brown meat and add seasonings.
Cook about 10 minutes. Sprinkle raw noodles over meat.
Mix soups together and pour over noodles.
Add water.
Do not stir.
Cover and cook about 5 minutes.
Stir and continue to cook another 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle cheese over top when cooked and serve with French bread and a green salad for a tasty, quick meal. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese according to package.
Cook hamburger, onion and mushrooms.
Mix hamburger with macaroni and cheese, onion and mushrooms.
Fix in layers hamburger mixture, pizza sauce, pepperoni, Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4-quart casserole.

title: colorado con queso soup
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in milk and soups and heat through.
Place cheese cubes in bowl and pour hot soup over.

title: ma bailey's chocolate icing
directions: Cook
on low heat until sugar dissolves.
Turn heat up, when it	comes to a roaring boil, cook for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon
vanilla and nuts if desired.
Place in pan or sink of cold water.
Beat until it starts to thicken.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: In saucepan, melt peanut butter and butter.
In a large bowl, combine powdered sugar and cereal.
Pour peanut butter mixture over cereal.
Blend together with hands.
Form into small balls. Chill until firm.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place crescent rolls in jelly roll pan (10 x 15-inch).
Bake at temperature recommended on package.
Cool.
Mix next 5 ingredients and spread on baked dough.
Cut desired vegetables in small pieces.
Place on top of crust, then add grated Mozzarella and Cheddar cheeses.
Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: bonbons candy
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Roll out into balls and refrigerate (or you can top them with the nuts or cherries).
Melt together in double boiler the wax, chips and margarine.
Dip balls in chocolate and chill.

title: homemade hot rolls
directions: Combine oleo, sugar, salt and water in saucepan to melt butter. Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water. Add this to first mixture. Beat eggs. Add to mixture. Stir in unsifted flour. Cover with wax paper. Refrigerate overnight. (Don't knead. Sprinkle only with flour.)

Roll out on lightly floured board. Pinch off little balls. Roll together (fold in). Dip in melted margarine. Put 3 balls in greased muffin pan. Let rise 2 hours in warm place. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hard candy
directions: Sprinkle 18 to 24-inch strip of heavy-duty aluminum foil with powdered sugar.
Mix first 3 ingredients in large heavy saucepan. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil, without stirring, until temperature reaches 310° or until drops of syrup form hard and brittle threads in cold water.
Remove from heat. Stir in flavoring oil and coloring.
Pour onto foil.
Cool; break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: grilled chicken wings
directions: Salt wing joints sparingly with Charlie's on both sides, about 30 minutes before grilling.

title: five cup salad(no, six cups)
directions: Take all the ingredients, using 1 cup at a time, and place in large bowl.
Add sour cream last and slowly combine all ingredients together.

title: peach dessert
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Pour in peaches with juice. Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, until golden brown.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, milk and lime juice.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: chicken-rice casserole or pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Melt oleo and grease bottom and sides of a 2-quart casserole dish.
Place rice in bottom of casserole.
Heat soups and seasonings and pour over rice.
Dip chicken in remaining oleo and place on top of rice. Bake, uncovered, approximately 2 hours until done.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: texas governors mansion cowboy cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt in bowl. In an 8 qt. bowl, beat butter on medium speed until smooth and creamy, 1 minute. Gradually beat

in sugars, mixing well for 2 minutes. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in vanilla. Stir in flour mixture until just combined. Add chocolate chips, oats, coconut, and pecans.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine eggs, oil and bananas. Add to dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° in oiled loaf pan for 60 minutes or until separating from the side of the pan.
Cool before slicing.

title: delicious strawberry sunday coffeecakes(chs special foods lab coffeecake recipe; makes 3 coffeecakes)
directions: Stir together 1 1/2 cups flour and yeast.
Heat milk, water, oil, sugar and salt over low heat until very warm (120° to 130°). (Too hot will "kill" yeast.)
Add liquid ingredients to flour-yeast mixture and beat until smooth.
Add eggs and beat about 3 minutes.
Stir in more flour to make a moderately soft dough.

title: fiesta cheese dip
directions: In microwave-safe bowl, combine diced tomatoes and green chilies and cheese.
Stir.
Cover and microwave for 8 to 10 minutes on Medium until melted.
Stir twice during cooking.
Mix well.
Serve warm.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
