title: congealed chicken salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve over hot water.
Cool slightly and stir into mayonnaise.
Add all other ingredients, except cream, and mix well.
Whip the cream and fold into mixture.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Heat margarine in 13 x 9 x 2 pan.
Sprinkle evenly with brown sugar.
Spoon pineapple over brown sugar, spreading evenly. Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until cake pulls away from sides of pan. Cool for 10 minutes.
Invert on serving plate.
Cool completely.

title: charlotte's chicken marinade
directions: In a 1-cup Pyrex measuring cup add wine and soy sauce.
Fill the measuring cup to the top with cooking oil.
In a blender, blend the white wine, soy sauce and oil mixture with mustard, garlic salt and dehydrated onion flakes.
Pour over chicken and marinate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in covered pan. Grill 8 to 10 minutes on each side.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, green peppers, garlic and salt. Cover with cracked ice.
Mix well.
Let mixture stand 3 hours. Drain well. Remove garlic. Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over cucumbers and liquid into hot jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath (use half pint or pint jars) 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a large unbaked pie shell. Shake nutmeg over pie and bake in slow oven until set. When knife inserted into pie comes out clean, it is done.

title: baked sausage and dressing
directions: Combine sausage, crumbs, slightly beaten eggs, milk, onion and apple.
Press into greased baking dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Alternate layers of potatoes and onion in a buttered 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Rub chops on both sides with salt and pepper; lay them on top of potatoes and onions.
Pour soup over all.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until chops are tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind all raw vegetables.
Mix vinegar, salt and sugar and put pickling spice in a bag.
Put all ingredients in large pan to boil 1 or 1 1/2 hours.
When done, seal in jars for future use.

title: wedding bell punch
directions: Stir well.
Makes 1 3/4 quarts or you can reduce water in punch to 3 cans.
Just before serving, pour 1 bottle champagne.
Makes 2 1/4 quarts.
Enough for 18 (4 ounce) glasses.

title: quick caramel rolls
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths; roll in sugar and cinnamon (I put sugar and amount of cinnamon you like in a plastic bag and shake them in there).
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt butter, add sugar; cream together.
Add flour and eggs; beat well.
Stir in butter, milk and vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: egg plant patties(serves 4)
directions: In a covered sauce pan cook egg plant in boiling water until tender, about 5 minutes, drain and mash.
Stir in crumbs, cheese, eggs, parsley, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Shape into 8 patties, cook in hot oil 3 minutes on each side till golden brown.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix yogurt and Cool Whip; add to graham crust.
Place fruit on top.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini and tomatoes
directions: Saut onion and zucchini in olive oil over medium heat until zucchini starts to be tender. Add the tomatoes and basil. Stir and cook just a few seconds to heat the tomatoes. Cover and turn off the heat. Be careful not to overcook the zucchini.

title: irish coffee
directions: Beat whipping cream, powdered sugar and vanilla in a chilled 1 1/2-quart bowl until stiff; refrigerate.
Prepare coffee as directed.
Heat 2 mugs in boiling water; drain.
Place 2 tablespoons whiskey and 1 to 2 teaspoon of sugar in cup and stir. Pour hot coffee into each mug and top with whipped cream.
Serve immediately.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk in saucepan; bring to a rolling boil.
Continue to boil 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Fold in oats and peanuts.
Drop by scant tablespoonfuls onto wax paper or baking sheet.
Let stand until set.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix and put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in the morning at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken until it falls apart. Dice up celery and pickles. Remove chicken from bones and chop into small pieces. Combine chicken, celery and pickles together. Mix mayonnaise and vinegar together. Stir mixture into chicken until moist. Chill.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Fluff together dry ingredients with whisk. Add remaining ingredients. Cook on griddle until brown and before bubbles burst on top before turning. Turn only once. This batter is thick and they are light delicious pancakes! Add blueberries, if desired.

title: linguini with broccoli and bay scallops
directions: Cook linguini according to package directions.
Drain and toss with 1/2 stick butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Heat 1 stick butter in a large frypan.
Add garlic and broccoli.
Cook until crisp-tender.
Add scallops, pepper and salt.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Spoon over the linguini and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed camel
directions: Skin, clean and trim camel, lamb and chickens.
Cook each in water until tender.
Meanwhile, hard-cook and peel the eggs.
Cook rice until fluffy.
Fry nuts in oil until brown and mix with rice. Stuff the chickens with half the eggs and rice mixture.
Stuff the lamb with the 5 chickens and more rice mixture.
Stuff the camel with the lamb and more rice mixture.
Broil camel in large oven or near a gas flame until brown.
Spread the remaining rice on a serving tray and place camel on top.
Place chickens around camel.
Decorate with remaining eggs.
Serves 200.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and blend well.
Set aside. Sift the remaining ingredients together.
Add 1/4 cup butter with dry ingredients to a crumb consistency.
Line a 9-inch plate with pastry and put 1/2 crumb mixture over pastry.
Add molasses mixture and sprinkle remainder of crumbs on top.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 25 minutes.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add eggs, oil, 1/2 cup juice and vanilla.
Beat 10 minutes at low speed.
Grease and flour an angel food cake pan.
Pour half the batter in pan.
Lay half the apples on top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Repeat with remaining batter and apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When cool, drizzle with powdered sugar and orange juice mixture over top.

title: raw relish
directions: Chop vegetables; mix with salt.
Let stand 4 hours.
Drain out most of the juice.
Add rest of ingredients; stir well.
Let stand 1 hour.
Do not cook.
Seal in jars.
Let stand about 2 weeks before use.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together sugar and corn syrup.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts.
Stir.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes. Add butter and vanilla.
Stir.
Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add baking soda; stir gently.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Brown chicken in olive oil, garlic, salt and pepper; drain. Mix all ingredients (except stuffing and cheese) in large casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly. Layer cheese and stuffing. Dot with butter or margarine. Bake for 10 more minutes. Serve with rice.

title: extra crispy fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken and sprinkle with salt and pepper as desired. Roll in flour and gently shake off the excess.

With the faucet running very slow, hold chicken under the running water, turning it so the whole piece is wet. (Don't wash the flour off but just wet the chicken.) Now, batter the chicken again in the flour and drop into hot oil. Fry until golden brown on medium-high heat.

title: enchiladas
directions: Combine meat, onion, green chilies and 1/2 cup cheese; set aside.
Combine in saucepan, soups and enchilada sauce; heat until warm.
Dip each tortilla in sauce, one at a time.
Place in baking dish.
Fill with meat mixture; roll up.
Pour sauce over tortillas.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cool delight salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla and butter or margarine.
Beat until smooth (I use blender).
Cook in double boiler until thick.
When thick, remove from stove and add vanilla and butter or margarine.

title: pork chop skillet meal
directions: Brown chops in skillet with fat.
Salt.
Place slice of onion and slice of pepper ring on each chop.
Place one tablespoon rice in each ring.
Pour tomatoes over meat. Add celery. Place cover on skillet and when steam appears, turn to low heat for 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: First Layer:
Combine Worcestershire sauce, cream cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion and garlic powder.

title: chicken and cola
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour over chicken pieces.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Can be cooked in crock-pot overnight on low.

title: seafoam nut squares
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
In separate container, cream together shortening and sugars.
Add egg yolks and water; mix well.
Add vanilla and milk alternately with dry ingredients.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Add 1 1/2 cups packed brown sugar gradually; beat well.
Spread over dough and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: asparagus-tomato skillet
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; crumble.
Add onion to skillet and cook until tender.
Return bacon to skillet.
Add vinegar, water, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add asparagus; cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes over low heat.
Add tomatoes; cover and cook for 3 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Place all vegetables in casserole.
Spoon on soup over all. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken curry
directions: Cook onion, garlic and curry in oil in skillet.
Stir in chicken, sliced 1/4-inch wide, tomatoes and raisins.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 8 minutes.
Add potatoes, drained and cut in chunks, and drained green beans.
Cook, uncovered, 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Season with salt and pepper if desired. Serves 4.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Put the thawed hash browns in a buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle onions on top.
Mix together the margarine, soup and sour cream.
Stir in grated cheese.
Pour over potato and onion mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Line loaf pan with waxed paper.
Put fruit and nuts in bowl. Do not cut up or chop.
Mix together dry ingredients; sift over fruit and nuts.
Mix well.
Beat eggs; add vanilla.
Add to first mixture.
Stir until well coated.
Bake at 300°
for 1 1/2 hours. Cool 10 minutes.
Remove waxed paper.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Use 1/2 of each ingredient, layer in a large bowl with airtight cover.
Repeat layers.

title: mushroom cookies
directions: *Candy coating can be used quite effectively.

title: american berry no bake cheesecake(low calorie)
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Gentle stir in 3 c. cook whip and spoon into crust. Refrigerate 3 hours or until set. Spread remaining cool whip over top. Add berries on top.

title: trout in sour cream sauce
directions: Salt the trout inside and out.
Dredge in flour and fry in hot oil.
Remove the fish.
Add margarine, spices, lemon juice and water to the pan.
Cook briefly.
Add sour cream, stir and pour this sauce over the trout.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mashed bananas. Sift together flour, soda and cinnamon.
Add to cream mixture and stir until just moistened.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan.
Let cool and serve with cream cheese.

title: grandma lois' pasta salad
directions: First steam carrots, broccoli and cauliflower 3 to 4 minutes in microwave.
Then mix ingredients together.
Add salt, pepper, oregano and fresh garlic or garlic powder.
Pour Italian dressing (Wish-Bone) over ingredients and gently mix.
Adding a little Caesar can give it zip.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper in large skillet. Drain.
Add seasonings.
Simmer for 5 minutes on medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Serve with cornbread.

title: chicken bites
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees. Spray a cookie sheet. In a bowl, combine onions, flour and salt. Blend well. Set aside. Separate dough into 8 triangles. Cut each in half lengthwise to make 16 long triangles. Dip chicken pieces in egg; coat with onion mixture. Place 1 coated piece on wide end of each triangle; roll to opposite point. Place point side down on sprayed sheet. Brush tops with remaining egg; sprinkle with sesame seed or poppy seeds. Bake in pre-heated oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm or cold.

title: rice pilaff
directions: Melt oleo in heavy saucepan.
Add rice, onion and celery.
Cook until rice is golden brown (20 to 25 minutes), stirring often.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Simmer until liquid is absorbed, 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with chicken.

title: funeral pie
directions: In a saucepan, bring raisins and water to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered for 5 minutes.
Combine sugar and flour; add to raisin mixture.
Cook and stir 1 minute longer.
Remove from the heat; stir in lemon juice, nuts and lemon peel if desired. Line a 9 inch pie plate with bottom pastry, trim edges even with plate.
Add filling.
Top with a lattice crust, or cover with top pastry and cut slits in top.
Bake at 425° for 30-40 minutes or until filling is bubbly and crust is golden brown.
If necessary, cover edges with foil to prevent over browning.
Yield: 6-8 servings.

title: almond chicken stir-fry (in wok)
directions: Preheat oil in wok at 375°; add chicken & stir-fry until opaque (about 5 minutes). Add water chestnuts, almonds, soy sauce, garlic & chicken broth to wok; stir to blend--cover & cook 1 1/2 minutes. Combine cornstarch & water. Add to wok mixture & stir until thickened. Add pea pods & cook briefly; keep crunchy. Serve over cooked rice. May reduce wok mixture heat to warm until ready to serve.

title: karo nut pie
directions: Beat eggs; add flour, sugar, Karo, butter, vanilla, vinegar and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 410 degrees for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350 degrees and bake for 30-40 minutes.

title: pasta with broccoli, feta and olives
directions: Cook pasta in a pot of boiling water until tender but still firm to bite, about 8 minutes.
Add broccoli and cook until crisp-tender, about 2 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish with bread cubes.
Sprinkle sausage over bread. Sprinkle cheese on sausage.
Mix remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour mixture over sausage and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake as directed when ready to serve.
May also be frozen.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: In saucepan, combine gelatin, 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Beat yolks, lemon juice and 2/3 cup water. Stir into gelatin mixture. Stir over medium heat until it boils and gelatin melts. Chill until set.
Beat egg whites, gradually adding sugar. Fold in gelatin mix and place in pie crust. Top with Cool Whip. Chill until firm.

title: hawaiian fruit pie
directions: Combine milk and lemon juice.
Add nuts, pineapple and coconut.
Pour in graham cracker crusts.
Put Cool Whip on top. Keep in refrigerator.
Best if set overnight.
Makes 2 big pies.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator for 1 hour until Jell-O sets.

title: super nachos
directions: Cook ground chuck and onion in large skillet until brown. Drain.
Add salt and pepper. Set aside.
Spread beans in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer meat mixture, green chiles, cheese and taco sauce on top of beans.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts and mixture is thoroughly heated. Remove from oven. Sprinkle green onions and olives evenly over top.
Serve warm with tortilla chips, sour cream and guacamole on the side.

title: mac and cheese pinwheels
directions: Combine cream cheese, horseradish, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread half of cream cheese mixture on ham slices.
Top each slice with a slice of American cheese.
Spread remaining cream cheese mixture on American cheese.
Roll each slice, jellyroll style, and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: poor boy cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into 9-inch round ungreased pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: kathy's chicken dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Season to taste. Spray 9 x 13 pan with Pam. Add mixture to pan. Spray a little Pam on top. Helps it brown. Bake at 400° to 450° about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Then cover with the last 4 pieces of bread.

title: lemon cake
directions: Bake cake and prick holes in cake.
Pour jello and water mixture over cake.
Let cool and jell.
Beat vanilla pudding and milk.
Place on top of cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: potato pancakes(potato latkes are eaten during hanukkah.)
directions: Put all ingredients in blender container in order listed. Cover and run on high speed just until all potatoes go through blades, about 10 seconds.
Do not overblend or potatoes will be liquified.
Pour small amount onto a hot greased griddle or frypan. Fry until brown on both sides, turning once. Serve with applesauce and sour cream.

title: artichoke pie
directions: In a bowl mix eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Saute one small onion. Add artichokes and slightly brown.
Remove from pan with slotted spoon.
Place into raw pie shell.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Top with Mozzarella.
Cover with second pie crust.
Slit crust lightly. Bake 45 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: chicken breasts parmesan
directions: Pour dressing over chicken breasts; let marinate for at least 1 hour at room temperature, turning frequently.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Roll chicken, one piece at a time, in crumb mixture. Place in lightly oiled baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for about 1 hour, or until fully done and golden brown.

title: microwave easy baked beans
directions: Microwave bacon in casserole for 2 minutes on High.
Stir in chopped onion and cook, covered, on High 2 minutes.
Stir in other ingredients.
Cook, covered, on High for 4 minutes.
Stir and serve.

title: easy pizza
directions: Spoon a small amount of sauce on each muffin half.
Top with cheese; microwave on High for about 1 minute.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: In a large skillet heat oil; add meat, chili powder, onion and bell pepper.
Cook until meat browns and onions are transparent. Add cabbage; cook on low until cabbage wilts.
Stir occasionally; add Mexicorn, picante sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook until cabbage is tender.
Serves 12.

title: steak or chicken marinade
directions: Combine contents of Adolph's marinade with pineapple juice. Blend thoroughly. To this add remaining ingredients.

Mix thoroughly. Place steak or chicken in marinade. Pierce with fork. Marinate for 15 to 20 minutes, turning occasionally. Remove meat or chicken from marinade and broil, bake, roast or barbecue as desired. Baste meat with marinade while cooking.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar
and
egg;
beat
well.
Stir
in apples which have been
pared, cored and cut in thin slices or strips. Add nuts.
Sift
dry ingredients and blend with apple mixture. Bake in a 9 x 9-inch pan (greased) at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Cut in squares.
Serve plain or with ice cream.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onions in oleo, then add other ingredients.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
The longer, the better.

title: frogmore stew
directions: Fill large container of a propane cooker halfway with water; add crab bag.
Bring to a boil.
Add potatoes; return to boil and cook 10 minutes.
Add sausage and corn; return to boil.
Cook 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add shrimp; cook 3 to 5 minutes until shrimp turns pink.
Drain water off.
Serve.
Yield: 12 servings.
(Dutch oven can be used on high heat.)

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together with the remaining ingredients and anything else you may want to add.
Refrigerate.

title: turkey burger
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into four patties.
Grill indoors or outside on barbecue grill.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Remove 1 cup of crumbs and set aside.
Add buttermilk mixture and 1 egg.
Mix and pour into 9 x 11-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top of crumbs.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Best served warm.

title: marshmallow slices
directions: Mix marshmallows and cream.
Add a little butter (melted), then add graham crumbs.
Press together in roll.
When ready to serve, slice.
Put whipped cream on top.

title: bran muffins
directions: Beat first four ingredients together.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: muesli cookies(muffins)
directions: Melt butter; add syrup.
When cool, add eggs.
Pour this mixture into dry ingredients.
Spoon into patty pans (cupcake tins lined with papers).
Bake at 350° for approximately 12 minutes.

title: cheese crackers
directions: Cheese and margarine should be at room temperature.
Mix these together. Add pepper and flour.
Mix well. Add Rice Krispies.
Mix well, then roll into balls.
Bake at 375° on an ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pea casserole
directions: Melt oleo; add chopped onion and celery. Simmer until tender. When mixture is tender, add peas, pimento, cream of mushroom soup and water chestnuts. Mix all together and put in casserole. Top with Pepperidge Farm dressing. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil sugar and water for 3 minutes.
Let cool.
Blend bananas until fine.
Mix syrup, juices and bananas together really well. Pour into 1/2 gallon containers and freeze.
When ready to serve, thaw slightly.
Add 1 quart ginger ale for each 1/2 gallon of punch.
Serves 50.

title: five minute pie
directions: Beat cream cheese in small mixing bowl until smooth. Gradually add sweet milk and evaporated milk; beat until smooth. Add lime juice.
Blend slowly until thickened, about 1 minute. Pour into pie shell.
Chill 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until firm.
Garnish as desired.

title: oven-roasted potato wedges
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Leaving skins on, scrub potatoes and cut
lengthwise
into
1/2	inch
strips.
In
small
bowl combine oil,
salt, seasoned pepper and paprika.
Toss potato wedges in seasoned
oil.
Place potatoes on foil lined baking sheet and bake
for
about
20 minutes or until tender.
Turn potatoes once while baking.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.

title: pina colada fruit salad
directions: Combine coconut, yogurt, pineapple juice, rum extract and coconut cream in a small glass bowl.
Stir to blend.
Fold in fresh or canned fruits just before serving.
Yields about 6 servings.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain well.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Add this mixture to the broccoli and pour into casserole dish.
Cover with cheese and stuffing crumbs.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes (uncovered).

title: ann landers' meat loaf(doubled)
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Divide into two loaves in oblong foil pan.
Pour 15 ounce can tomato sauce over loaves. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cut one loaf in slices.
Freeze 2 or 4 slices wrapped in cling wrap, then foil to use later for quick meal!
I've used this recipe hundreds of times!
It's the best!

title: christmas nut thin cookie
directions: Mix sugar and butter together, mix well.
Add well beaten eggs, sift in flour and salt, add nuts and vanilla.
Mix until smooth and light.
Drop on greased baking sheet.
Space well apart.
Place half nut meat in center of each cookie.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine beef, rice, salt and pepper in a large bowl until well mixed.
Form into small balls about 1 1/2 inches in diameter. Place in a large baking dish.
Brown onion and pepper in shortening.
Add tomato juice (or sauce), nutmeg, salt and pepper to taste; pour over meat balls.
Cover dish with foil tightly and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter in saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar.
Add cereal and mix well.
Shape into small balls and place on wax paper; chill.
Melt chocolate chips on low heat and stir in oil.
Dip the top of each ball in chocolate and chill.
Makes 5 dozen balls.

title: baptist pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening, butter and sugar. Add eggs 1 at a time, mixing well after each egg is added. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Add to first mixture, alternating with milk until all is blended well. Add flavorings to mixture and blend again. Grease and flour a Bundt pan. Pour in the mixture and place in a cool oven. Turn on heat to 350° and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Let stand for 3 to 5 minutes before removing from Bundt pan.

title: nancy's jello salad(low calorie)
directions: Combine jello and water. Stir until dissolved.
Fold in strawberries, pineapple and bananas.

Pour half this mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Refrigerate. When firm, spread Cool Whip over first layer and cool until firm. Add remaining mixture on top. Chill until firm. Cover and keep refrigerated.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Rinse cranberries.
Mix fruit with water and sugar.
Put into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch buttered casserole dish.

title: basic gravy
directions: Measure fat into roasting pan.
Stir in liquid.
Cook over medium heat, stirring to loosen browned particles.
Remove from heat.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Stir into pan.
Add salt and pepper.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat. Boil 2 minutes.
Makes 2 cups.

title: welsh rabbit
directions: Mix beaten egg, flour, salt, mustard and pepper together and stir in cheese.
Let milk come to boil and stir in mixture until it cools together evenly.
Last, add butter and serve hot or on toast.

title: cherry glazed pork roast
directions: Combine first seven ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil; reduce heat and simmer two minutes.
Add slivered almonds.
Sprinkle roast with salt and pepper.
Place roast, fatty side up, on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes or until browned.
Brush with cherry mixture; turn roast and brush with cherry mixture.
Insert meat thermometer, making sure it does not touch fat.
Bake, uncovered, an additional 20 minutes or until thermometer registers 160°, basting frequently with cherry mixture.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before slicing.
Garnish, if desired.
Yields 10 servings of 3.5 ounces each.

title: peach delight
directions: Crush wafers into fine crumbs and line bottom of pan with 1/2 of them.
Cream sugar, butter and egg yolks until smooth.
Beat egg whites separately, until stiff, then add to yolk mixture, mixing until smooth.
Spread mixture over crumbs.
Spread layer of peaches over mixture.
(I slice "canned" sliced peaches in 1/2 so they are not too thick.)
Whip cream; add little sugar and vanilla and spread over peaches.
Top with remaining cookie crumbs. Refrigerate, minimum 6 hours; overnight even better.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: banana-apple pie
directions: Place sliced bananas on bottom of baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Pour applesauce over bananas and top with whipped cream.
Chill well.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: wonton soup
directions: In a large pot, bring 12 cups of water to a boil.
Add wontons.
Bring to a boil again.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Bring to a boil once more.
When wontons float to surface (almost immediately), remove to colander.
Rinse under cold water.
Drain and set aside.

title: big chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 12 x 15-inch pan.
Dump all ingredients (except water) in a large bowl and stir them a bit.
Add hot water and mix thoroughly.
Pour into pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza lover's casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion, green pepper, red pepper and garlic salt.
Cook until peppers and onions are tender.
Divide each biscuit into two or three pieces (biscuits are flaky and will pull apart).
Place biscuit slices into bottom of ungreased casserole dish.
Pour meat mixture over this.
Spread Cheddar cheese over meat mixture.
Top with Ragu Pizza Quick.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until crust is done.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken corn casserole
directions: Melt 4 1/2 tablespoons butter.
Add flour; blend well.
Stir over low heat until bubbly.
Add broth all at once and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine corn, chicken and sauce in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs, blended with 6 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until crumbs are brown and sauce is bubbly.

title: tex-mex
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
(Note: To peel avocado, slit lengthwise and pop off skim from both halves. Throw out seed, scoop out pulp and throw out rinds.)
In separate bowl, combine sour cream, mayo and taco mix.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased baking dish (10 x 6 x 2-inches) or larger than standard round pie dish.
Sprinkle with salt.
Add sugar and sprinkle with cinnamon; then mix flour, brown sugar and margarine. Crumble to oatmeal stage and sprinkle over apples. Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fish tempura
directions: Prepare marinade with shoyu, crushed garlic and ginger juice to taste.
Marinate fish in sauce overnight or longer.
Prepare batter by mixing Bisquick, flour and water to desired consistency. Coat each marinated piece of fish with flour.
Dip in batter and deep fry.

title: poor man's rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in glass baking dish.
Bake in slow oven for
hours,
stirring several times during the cooking period.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown beef, pepper and onion.
Mix with pork and beans, brown sugar, mustard, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In saucepan mix first 3 ingredients over low heat.
Gradually add boiling water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is clear and thick.

title: cream cheese mini-cakes(makes approximately 15)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the cream cheese; add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Put one vanilla wafer in each cupcake paper.
Fill each paper baking cup 3/4 full.
Bake 30 minutes (may take longer, depends on your oven).
After baking, add fruit spread or pie filling on top of each cupcake.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown beef and drain. Add onion and cook until tender. Add sauce and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with desired toppings. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Pour over Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue hamburger
directions: Put hamburger meat in skillet.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well with meat.
Simmer until well done.
Spoon on toasted buns.
Serves 6.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Mix and spread on party rye bread.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: milk chocolate and peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine peanut butter and butter; beat until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy. Blend in flour.
Stir in 1 cup morsels; spread into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 minutes or until edges begin to brown. Sprinkle with remaining morsels.
Let stand 5 minutes until soft and shiny.
Spread evenly.
Cool completely.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch bars.
Makes 48.

title: copper pennies(marinated carrots)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill in the refrigerator 12 hours before serving.
Keeps in the refrigerator several days.

title: fig cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar and beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together in a separate mixing bowl flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Add nuts.
Add dry mixture to creamed mixture a little at a time, alternating with buttermilk.
Add 1 cup of chopped fig preserves with juice.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 375° about 1 hour.
Cake is done when it springs back when touched.
Cake is better the next day.

title: zucchini munchies
directions: Brown sausage.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° or until browned.
Yield: 24 (2-inch) squares.

title: stay-crisp slaw
directions: Mix shredded cabbage,
carrots, green pepper and onion. Soften gelatine in cold
water.
Mix
sugar,
vinegar,
celery seed, salt and pepper	in
saucepan;
boil.
Stir
in softened gelatine. Cool until slightly
thickened; beat well.	Beat in the salad oil; blend
well.
Toss onto the slaw.
Refrigerate. Keeps well for about 1 week.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix oleo and sugar; cream well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, and then the buttermilk.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into 9-inch (deep dish) pie shell.
Bake at 275° to 300° for 45 minutes.
Ovens vary so use baking temperature that will cook slow.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine and shape into a ball.
Then roll into chopped pecans. Then chill in refrigerator.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Into a heavy 3-quart saucepan, turn the sugar, milk, butter, corn syrup and cocoa.
Mix and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook, without stirring, about 15 minutes at a full but low and gentle boil.
Add vanilla and cool to lukewarm (110°). Beat until fudge begins to thicken and loses its gloss. Quickly pour into a buttered 8-inch square dish.
Makes 2 pounds. Inexpensive!

title: homestyle sausage soup
directions: Cook sausage in large saucepan until lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Add onion; continue to cook 2 minutes.
Stir in water and contents of rice and seasoning packets.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 8 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop walnuts up fine and place all over on a flat plate.
Set aside.
Cut dried beef in small pieces.
Mix the cheeses and dip together in a bowl, mixing well by hand.
Add dried beef blending in well.
Form in a ball and roll in nuts covering the cheese ball completely.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: world famous potatoes
directions: Cut washed, unpeeled potatoes in 1/4-inch slices.
Melt margarine in water and add soup mix.
Layer potatoes and liquid in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, one hour at 350°.
Will hold in warm oven indefinitely.
Good the next day.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello, stir and cool slightly.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir and chill.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water until tender; drain well.
Add sugar, margarine, lemon juice and lemon peel.
Heat and stir until the margarine is melted.
Stir in parsley.
Serves 6 (1/2 cup per serving).

title: peachy peach cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter. Sprinkle mixture on bottom and sides of greased round pan.
Place peaches, cut side up over dough.
Combine sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over peaches.
Bake 15 minutes.
Mix egg yolk with milk. Pour over peaches and bake 30 minutes more.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Prepare dressing in a jar; shake before pouring over fruit. Best to add dressing shortly before serving.

title: diabetic "diet" cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with fork.
They will not rise, so can be close together.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Do not overcook.
This recipe can easily be doubled.

title: sweet oatmeal bread
directions: Place all ingredients in bread maker.
Select light crust setting; press start.
After the baking cycle ends, remove bread from pan, place on cake rack and allow to cool one hour before slicing (use electric knife for best results).

title: potato casserole with chicken
directions: Saute onion and celery until soft.
Add to milk and chicken soup.
Arrange potatoes, chicken, flour, salt and pepper in layers in casserole.
Pour soup mixture on top.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered, then remove cover and bake until crumbs are browned, about 10 minutes more.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Beat the eggs with milk and add the rest of the ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.
Set out to room temperature before baking. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set in the middle.
Cover with foil the first 45 minutes.
Serves 7 to 8.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix
ingredients
together.
Use additional milk if too thick. The
batter
needs to run through funnel easily.
When grease is hot,
plug funnel with finger and add enough batter to fill
tip. Hold
funnel
over grease and release finger so batter can flow into grease, making desired shape.	Cook until lightly
golden, turning
to
cook
other
side. Drain.
Cool slightly.

title: jodie crow's garlic bread sticks
directions: Cut hot dog buns into 3 strips.
Keep buns closed while cutting strips.
Melt margarine and dip strips of buns in margarine.
Place on cookie sheet and sprinkle with garlic salt, Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Turn oven off and let set for 2 hours.

title: fried chicken parmesan
directions: Combine 1/4 cup cheese, 1/4 cup flour and salt; coat chicken. Brown in oil on all sides.
Cover.
Cook 30 minutes over low heat or until tender.
Remove chicken.
Drain fat.
Gradually add water to 2 tablespoons flour, stirring until well blended.
Add flour mixture to pan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens.
Stir in water chestnuts, pimento and remaining cheese. Add chicken and cover.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Blend shortening with brown sugar and unbeaten egg; add rolled oats and coconut.
Mix well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla. Roll into little balls and drop on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake in 375°
oven for 12 minutes.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Mix the condensed milk with the lemonade.
Fold in the thawed whipped topping.
Put this mixture in the pie crust.
Refrigerate for at least 4 hours before you serve it.
No cooking is required to prepare this pie.
Serves 8.
(You can garnish with a lemon slice or twist.)

title: french raisin pie
directions: Beat eggs; mix well with the melted butter, vanilla, sugar and vinegar.
Bring the raisins to boil in water; drain.
Add to first mixture with the pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie
shell. Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.
Do not try to increase this recipe.
A lot like pecan pie - good!

title: salad
directions: Add gelatin to cold water.
Heat soup to boiling; remove from heat and add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add crumbled cheese and remaining ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator until set.

title: zesty sausage con-quesa
directions: Cook sausage until brown.
In a double boiler, melt cheese. Add other ingredients, including sausage.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.
(Also good served over scrambled eggs.)
A good dish for a buffet or party.

title: almond roca
directions: Mix butter and brown sugar.
Stir in skillet until crack stage (270° or 290°).
Put chopped almonds on bottom of sided cookie pan. Pour the cooked concoction on top of almonds.
Top with melted Hershey candy bars.
Sprinkle with more nuts.
Let cool.
Break apart.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Mix 3 or 4 teaspoons with 1 cup hot water for each serving.
Fill small decorated jars with coffee mix for good gifts.

title: jambalaya casserole
directions: Fry bacon, onion and green pepper together.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Add bacon mixture, rice, tomatoes, parsley, meat and salt.
Mix together well.
Turn into a buttered baking dish. Bake, uncovered, for about 45 minutes in a 375° oven.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: brown sugar puffs
directions: Beat egg white.
Add brown sugar and vanilla.
Dip nuts in mixture; put on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Cut heat off and let stay in oven for 30 minutes.

title: bread
directions: Add the first 5 ingredients; let stand 10 to 15 minutes.

title: annie's chocolate kiss peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour with baking soda and salt. Set aside.

title: red and yellow relish
directions: Cut peppers in half lengthwise, discard seeds and membranes. Place peppers, cut side down, on a baking sheet.
Flatten with palm of hand.
Broil 5 1/2-inches from heat, 15 to 20 minutes or until charred.
Place in a heavy-duty zip-top plastic bag. Seal and let stand 10 minutes.
Peel peppers, discard skins.
Chop peppers. Cook corn in oil in a skillet over medium-high heat for 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add garlic, cook 1 minute.
Reduce heat to medium, stir in peppers, tomatoes and remaining ingredients.
Remove from heat, let cool.
Store in refrigerator. Yield: 5 cups.

title: breakfast beans(why not)
directions: Rinse and pick over beans. Soak beans in water to cover for 4 hours. Drain. Add water to cover and simmer about 1 hour.

Mix beans with other ingredients in a large casserole with tight fitting cover. Add enough water to cover beans well. Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 4 to 5 hours until beans are soft and most of the liquid has been absorbed. Stir mixture every hour during cooking. Add boiling water as necessary if beans become dry.

title: triple cheese pasta casserole
directions: Cook corkscrew macaroni in lightly salted boiling water in a large pot for 7 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables; return to boiling.
Cook for 2 minutes more or till pasta is tender.
Drain well.

title: cabbage and bean soup
directions: Cook hamburger and drain.
In large pan, add puree, kidney beans, onion, cabbage and chili powder.
Mix well together. Sprinkle lightly with garlic powder.
Cook on low for 2 hours and serve.

title: tabasco la corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream peanut butter, Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla until well blended.
Add egg.
Beat until blended.
Combine other ingredients.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly with fork.
Bake for 6 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Boil sugar, salt, vinegar and oil and then cool.
Add to vegetables and toss well.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving. Will refrigerate up to two weeks.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef, onion and garlic.
Drain fat. In another large pan, mix the milk, olives, chilies, sauce and soup and bring to a boil.
Add meat and mix together.
Remove from heat.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Add milk gradually.
Add beaten egg yolks to small mixture.
Stir thoroughly and return to saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until bubbly (about 2 minutes).
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Top with meringue and brown in oven.

title: petersen family birthday cake
directions: Stir all together.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°
in a greased Bundt pan.
Cool; remove. (I always remove the cake when the pan is cool enough to pick up with my bare hands.) Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: crunchy oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Mix cereal crumbs, onion, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Dip chicken in butter, then into cereal mixture.
Place skin side up in ungreased baking pan.
Pour remaining butter over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is done.
Serves 4.

title: ga ga's rabbit stew
directions: Let rabbit stand overnight in fridge with chopped onion, 1/2 cup vinegar, salt, pepper and water.
Next day, stew rabbit 2 to 3 hours with 1 cup water, 1 tablespoon vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, bay leaf, parsley, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper. Cook in crock-pot or slow cooker.
After cooking, take rabbit out.
Debone and replace rabbit in broth.
Add another cup of water.
Add celery, potatoes, 2 onions, carrots and green pepper. Cook 2 to 3 hours or until vegetables are tender.
Serves 6.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove bone and skin.
Chop celery and walnuts.
Shred cheese.
Combine all ingredients (except bread crumbs) in mixing bowl.
Turn into sprayed casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter chocolate chip brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to recipe.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Combine cheese and butter in mixing bowl.
Mash together until well combined. Stir in flour, salt and red pepper.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well.
(Dough may be refrigerated.)
Drop by teaspoonfuls (1-inch apart) onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten slightly with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: gail's chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine broccoli and other ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Add cooked pieces of chicken breast into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: never fail icing
directions: Mix well. Boil briskly 2 minutes or until spoon coats.
Remove from heat and beat until creamy.

title: mulled cider or apple juice
directions: Bring juices to boil, then turn to simmer.
Add cheesecloth, tied with spices, and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove bag and keep warm.
Crock-pot is great to keep warm.
Makes house smell great, too.

title: crustless vegetable pie
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes.
Beat eggs, seasonings and 1/4 cup cheese.
Add vegetables.
Pour half of the mixture into greased 10-inch pie pan.
Top with 1/4 cup cheese.
Layer remaining mixture and cheese on top.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until set.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: crab cakes
directions: My daughter Mollie said, "You can't give exact quantities." But it is delicious; flaking the crabmeat, crumbling the crackers up in your fingers, adding the mayonnaise and sauteing the cakes in butter or butter-like substitute.

title: heavenly hamburger
directions: Brown meat in butter.
Add salt, sugar and garlic salt.
Mix in tomato sauce.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and onions.
Layer noodles, meat mixture and cream cheese mixture in a greased casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, cook 2 to 3 minutes, until peanut butter pulls away from side of pan. Pour into graham cracker crust and pat down. Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Add flour, salt and soda; mix well.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: In heavy-bottom pot, melt butter over medium-low heat.
Add garlic (do not brown).
Stir in whipping cream until simmering. Let sauce heat until reduced by 10 percent.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: low-fat crispy turkey bake
directions: Cook peas according to package directions, omitting salt and fat; drain.
Combine peas and next 3 ingredients in a medium bowl. Combine mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper; add to turkey mixture, stirring well.
Spoon mixture into an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray; arrange tomato slices on top.
Combine crushed cereal and margarine; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yield:
6 servings (200 calories and 13% fat per serving).

title: white chili
directions: Sort and wash beans; place in a Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans; let soak 8 hours.
Drain beans and return to Dutch oven.
Add broth, water, onion, garlic and salt.
Bring to a boil; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken, green chiles, cumin, oregano, red pepper and cloves. Cover and cook 30 minutes.
Spoon into serving bowls and top with cheese.

title: strawmallow delite salad
directions: Drain oranges, reserving 2 tablespoons liquid.
Combine oranges and liquid with remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Cover and chill up to 2 hours before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pressure canned green beans
directions: Wash, trim ends and break green beans into 1 to 2-inch pieces.
Pack beans tightly into jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace. Add 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon sugar to each quart.
Fill jar with water and leave 1/2-inch headspace.
Put jars in pressure cooker.
Add water in pot about 4 inches on jars.
Cook on 10 pounds pressure (240°) for 20 to 25 minutes.
Take off heat and let pressure out before opening.

title: scalloped corn supreme
directions: Heat corn and milk.
Gradually stir in egg.
Add next 4 ingredients and dash of pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 8-inch round baking dish.
Sprinkle butter crumbs over.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken fettuccine
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter in a large skillet; add chicken pieces and cook until browned.
Remove chicken from skillet, reserving pan drippings in skillet.
Set chicken aside.
Add mushrooms and next 5 ingredients to pan drippings in skillet and saute until vegetables are tender.
Add chicken; reduce heat and cook 15 minutes or until chicken is done and mixture is thoroughly heated. Set aside and keep warm.
Cook fettuccine.
Place fettuccine in large bowl.
Combine half and half, 1/2 cup melted butter, parsley, 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Add half and half mixture to fettuccine.
Toss gently to combine.
Add chicken mixture and Parmesan cheese to fettuccine.
Toss gently to combine.

title: orange-cranberry bread
directions: Combine sugar and water in medium sized saucepan.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until sugar dissolves.
Cook over low heat an additional 5 minutes, continuing to stir.
Remove from heat. Add butter and stir until melted.
Cool slightly.
Add orange juice and eggs.
Blend well.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, milk, butter, corn syrup and salt in heavy saucepan.
Stir over moderate heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture reaches a boil.
Boil 9 to 10 minutes (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat and allow to stand until lukewarm (about 1 hour).
Add vanilla and beat until mixture just begins to lose its gloss and holds its shape.
Requires little beating. Quickly stir in nuts and cherries and turn into oiled pan. Let stand until firm before cutting.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.
Good Christmas candy.

title: pastor's soup
directions: Open can.
Pour contents into saucepan.
Add water and stir. Heat to desired temperature and serve.
Serve with crackers, if desired.

title: mary ann's oven baked corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Pour in a greased skillet in center rack of oven at 375° until golden brown.
Mm-mm good.

title: baked red cabbage
directions: Trim cabbage stem and cut off bruised leaves.
Quarter cabbage and shred finely.
Brown meat in large saucepan; add onions and apples.
Add wine and bring to a boil.
Add cabbage, salt, pepper and sugar.
Mix, then bake at 350°, covered, until cabbage is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in vinegar.
Serves 8.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Goes great with chips or vegetables.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Saute ground beef in a large pot. Drain and rinse the beef. Wipe the pot dry and return the beef to the pot.
Chop the potatoes (preferably leaving the skin on), onion, celery, carrots and green beans.
Add to the pot along with crushed tomatoes, bouillon and water.
Simmer until carrots are tender.
Add sugar. Melt the margarine in a small bowl in the microwave.
Add flour and stir with a fork.
Add to the soup to thicken it.
Simmer for about half an hour.

title: fettuccine in garlic basil cream sauce
directions: Heat oil in a small skillet over low heat.
Add garlic; cook until golden, turning cloves over as they color (about 6 minutes). Add chopped basil and cook 10 seconds.
Transfer to food processor.
Add sour cream, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper. Whirl until creamy.
Pour into serving bowl.

title: sassy bonbons(august 1968 american girl)
directions: In a heavy aluminum saucepan, combine semisweet chocolate chips, applesauce, and almond extract.
Stir over low heat until chocolate is melted and blended with applesauce.

title: eggs
directions: Mix eggs, milk and butter.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Use 10-inch skillet or shallow 2-quart casserole.
Cover with foil, put in refrigerator and let it stay overnight.
Put in cold oven at 300° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: white icing
directions: NOTE:
2-3 Tbsp of peanut butter may be added to this recipe for flavoring.

title: chili with beans
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper over medium heat; remove grease.
Place mixture on paper towels to absorb any other grease.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix ingredients together in a buttered baking dish. Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally during first 1/2 hour. Last 1/2 hour, add raisins.

title: linnie's cucumber pickles
directions: Peel, remove seeds and cut 6 big cucumbers into small cubes. Use pickling cucumbers whole after cleaning.
Cut up the onions finely.
Put these in a non-metal container.
Make a brine with the 1/2 cup of salt with enough water to cover the cucumbers. Soak overnight in the brine.
Drain well in the morning.
Clean and chop the red pepper.
Put in a stainless steel or enamel pot. Add the pint of vinegar, sugar and cook until cukes are done.
Do not boil.
Mix in a bowl the turmeric, celery seed, flour, 1/2 cup sugar and add enough vinegar to make a paste.
Stir into vegetable mixture and cook until thickened.
If it doesn't thicken, add more sugar, flour and vinegar stirred to paste.
Seal in hot jars.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies, including filling, in food processor until mixture resembles dirt.
Set aside.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together, form into patties and brown. Add a can of tomato sauce and can of water.
Cover and cook slowly.

title: hot and crunchy salad
directions: Toss salad in large bowl.
Add Fritos, Ranch Style beans and Tabasco sauce.
Mix.
Serve immediately.

title: chocolate turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box. Pour 1/2 of the batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels, milk and butter in a saucepan.
Sprinkle 1 cup nuts on cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Pour caramel mixture over cake.
Spoon remaining cake batter into pan and top with remaining nuts.
Bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chop suey bake
directions: Brown hamburger; saute with celery and onions. Drain. Put in large baking dish and add remaining ingredients. Mix all together and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. May add chow mein noodles when you take it out of the oven.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Mix sugar, shortening and eggs together until light and fluffy.
Blend in the bananas.
Add dry ingredients and stir just until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake until firmly set when lightly touched in the middle, 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan after 10 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: graham crackers
directions: Mix as for pie crust.
Roll or pat on cookie sheet (ungreased).
Prick, cut and bake at 375° until it browns, then 325°.
This will fill 2 1/2 cookie sheets.

title: omelettes
directions: Note:
Use 2 eggs per omelet.
Cut up olives, mushrooms, onions and ham.
All of the ingredients are optional except for cheese.
You can use fat-free cheese.

Beat 2 eggs; pour in a skillet that is preheated with butter and put ingredients in the middle of eggs as in a line with the outer edge of eggs; use them as flaps and fold them one at a time to cover ingredients and whoopi you have some good stuff.
Josh loves 'em.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Put shrimp in a baking dish and pour other ingredients over the shrimp.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: golden chicken
directions: Mix soup and wine; set aside.
Flour chicken.
In heavy skillet, brown chicken in oil. Place in baking dish; pour soup/wine mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes. Makes a nice, brown gravy and goes great with rice.

title: chili cheese appetizer
directions: Put green chiles on bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Cover green chiles with cheese.
Pour beaten eggs over entire dish. Cover and let set 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour (may be too long).
Will be brown on top.
Cut into small squares to serve.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread sugar cookie dough on pizza pan and bake until done. Mix cream cheese and marshmallows together.
Spread on cooled cookie.
Top with any fruit.

title: mexican chef's salad
directions: Chop onion, tomatoes and lettuce; toss with cheese, mayonnaise and hot sauce.
Crunch tortilla chips and add to mixture; brown ground beef and add kidney beans and salt.
Simmer for 10 minutes and mix into cold salad.
Decorate with whole tortilla chips, avocado slices and tomato slices.

title: onion smothered steak
directions: Brown meat on both sides after dipping in flour.
Cut meat in small pieces, then add the rest of ingredients.
Cook 1 hour on simmer.

title: pineapple ring for punch
directions: Prepare gelatin in cold water (mix to dissolve).
Strain juice from pineapple.
Add hot water to pineapple juice in a pan and bring to a boil.
Stir in gelatin.
Add sugar and cool.
Add pineapple and fruit juices.
Pour into a wet ring mold.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix bread crumbs, salt, pepper, egg, onion and half the tomato juice.
Shape into a loaf.
Place in baking dish.
Pour remaining tomato juice over the meat.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Very good cold and slices well.

title: light biscuits
directions: Dissolve the yeast and sugar in warm water in medium bowl. Add Bisquick and milk and mix until dough forms.
On a surface dusted with baking mix, smooth into a ball and knead 10 times. Roll out to 1/2-inch thick; cut with a 2-inch cutter, dipped in baking mix.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Let rise in warm place about 30 minutes or until soft and puffed.
Bake at 425° for 6 to 8 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 9 to 11 biscuits.

title: fisherman's casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Saute onion in butter.
Add soup milk, cheeses and seasoning.
Heat, stirring often, until cheese melts.

title: silver cleaner
directions: In 2 cup measuring cup microwave water on High until boils, approximately 2 to 3 minutes.
Add salt, baking soda and foil. Dip flatware into mixture and watch tarnish disappear.
Wash flatware in soapy water, rinse and dry.
Makes 1 cup.

title: peas and carrots casserole
directions: Layer 1 can of peas and carrots, half of the ground beef, half of the onion, peppers and soup in a casserole dish.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
While hot, sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on top.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix eggs, corn, muffin mix and pimento.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Under broiler, brown chicken breasts.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; baste now and then.

title: funnel cake
directions: Mix sour cream and milk.
Stir into beaten eggs. Sift dry ingredients into eggs and milk mixture.
Drop into skillet full of hot oil (375°) about 3 tablespoons at a time from funnel.
Fry until golden brown on one side. Turn and fry on the other side for 1 or 2 minutes. Remove from oil.
Drain. Shake powdered sugar over cakes before eating.

title: chocolate chess pie 1
directions: Beat all ingredients with mixer.
Bake in unbaked pie shell for 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 300° and continue baking until set.

title: ice cream pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, salt & spices. Add ice cream & mix well. Put into crust & freeze.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter and confectioners sugar in a small bowl.
In another bowl, mix milk, vanilla pudding and Cool Whip. Add second mixture to first mixture.
Crush Oreo cookies.

title: barbecups
directions: Heat
oven
In
large
skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir
in barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar; heat until
bubbly.
Remove
from heat,	set aside.
Separate biscuits into 10, place each biscuit in ungreased muffin cups. Press
dough to cover bottom and sides of cup.
Spoon hot meat mixture into cups.
Sprinkle evenly with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: fudge cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 25 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: easy brunch
directions: Mix together eggs, milk, salt, mustard.
Fold in sausage, cheese, bread; add onion, pepper, if desired.
Pour mixture into 9x13 inch casserole.
Refrigerate over night (can freeze).	Remove from fridg or thaw 30 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: rice-meat casserole
directions: Brown and season meat and onion.
Add 1/2 cup rice, chicken rice soup and can of mushroom soup.
Mix well and put in baking dish.
Corn flakes or chips may be crumbled over top or left plain.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, almonds, onion, lemon juice and pepper.
Add mayonnaise and toss.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese and finish with potato chips.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: In large bowl, combine turkey, sausage, ground beef, salt, eggs, onion powder, chives, basil, thyme and flour.
Mix well. Roll into balls.
Deep fry or bake.
In large kettle or skillet, combine over low heat stewed tomatoes, vinegar and brown sugar. To this mixture, add meatballs.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt butter in saucepan. Add sugar, eggs, vanilla, flour mixture and nuts to melted butter. Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 20 to 30 cookies.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown meat with onion; add tomatoes and Italian sauce.
Bring to boil then simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Cook noodles, drain. Layer noodles, meat mixture, each kind of cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: sausage fondue
directions: Place bread in greased 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Brown sausage; drain and pat dry with paper towels.
Put sausage on top of cheese.
Beat eggs with 2 1/4 cups milk and dry mustard.
Pour over top of sausage.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: rice bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare Rice-A-Roni mix as package directs. Set aside.
Crumble meat in a 10-inch skillet; add onion and brown meat and onion.
Drain, reserving drippings in skillet; set aside. Add zucchini and garlic to drippings in skillet and saute over medium-high heat 1 minute.
Cover; continue cooking over low heat about 4 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Combine prepared Rice-A-Roni, meat mixture and 1 1/2 cups Prego sauce; add basil. Spread into 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Top with zucchini.
Pour 1/2 cup Prego sauce over zucchini.
Top with remaining 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: cheese balls
directions: Leave cheese out until soft.
Mix all ingredients.
Put mixture in freezer for about 30 minutes, then form into balls or logs.
Roll in finely chopped pecans.
Makes two large balls or three smaller logs.

title: french fried okra
directions: Place okra in a bowl and pour milk over it.
Cover; shake to saturate.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to prepare, drain okra in a colander.
Mix flour, corn meal, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Put okra in mixture and coat by stirring or shaking in a bowl with lid closed tight.
Heat oil in a frying pan; add okra and fry until golden brown, stirring twice.
Remove; drain.

title: lettuce soup
directions: Saut in butter the onion and garlic.
Add flour and stir in chicken broth. Add lettuce. Cover and cook (simmer) 20 minutes. Cool. Puree in blender or processor 1/4 portion at a time.
Return to pot. Add salt and white pepper. Bring to a boil and remove from heat. Stir in half and half.

title: delicious gingerbread with lemon sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix applesauce, syrup, egg whites and molasses.
Alternately add dry ingredients and milk mixed with vinegar.
Beat after each addition.
Pour into 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: deluxe cornbread
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend oil, corn and sour cream. Blend cornmeal, salt and baking powder. Blend all together. Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: all in one casserole
directions: Fry bacon crisp; remove bacon from pan.
Add onion to bacon fat; cook slowly until soft and lightly brown.
Add beef; sear thoroughly.
Combine vegetables, liquid, cooked noodles, bacon and seasoning with meat.
Stir and mix ingredients together.
Pour into 3-quart casserole (greased).
Bake at 325° for two hours, covered.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese (optional).

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil 1 minute; cool.
May add red food coloring.
Pour over whole or cut strawberries.
Makes 3 pies.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Mix green pepper with onion and butter.
Cook until soft.
Mix with other things and put in big casserole dish.
Put grated cheese on top and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 300° until it bubbles.

title: orange freeze
directions: Mix well and pour into gallon freezer.
Freeze as you would ice cream.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Mix for 1 minute. Refrigerate.
Better if made in advance of use.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 60 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: beefed-up biscuit casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and peppers.
Stir in sauce, chili powder and salt.
Simmer while preparing dough.
Separate each biscuit in halves and press 1/2 over bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine 1/2 cup cheese (reserve remaining 1 cup for top), sour cream and eggs and mix well.
Remove meat mixture from heat; stir in sour cream mixture and spoon over dough.
Arrange remaining biscuits on top.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: almond joy cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix together sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Stir in carrots, nuts and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into three 8-inch round layer cake pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake in a 300° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cocktail walnuts
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a shallow pan; stir in soy sauce; add walnut (halves) and stir until coated.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Bake at 350° for 10 or 15 minutes; stir occasionally. Watch carefully so they don't burn.

title: auntie betty's sherry trifle
directions: Place cake cubes in large glass dish.
Sprinkle sherry over cake cubes.
Combine pudding mix with milk.
Heat slowly until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour over cake cubes.
Spoon raspberry jam all over.

title: ham soup
directions: In large pot, put in ham.
Use bone if you have it.
Cut up vegetables.
Add parsley and water to cover.
Add more if needed. Cook until tender.
Add macaroni last 15 minutes.
Use any vegetables you like.

title: egg on toast
directions: Bake pound cake according to directions on box.
Cool and slice.
Place a small amount of Cool Whip on each slice of cake. Place one apricot half, round side up, in the middle of the Cool Whip dab, and there you have egg on toast.
An easy and wonderful dessert.

title: blackened pepper steak fettucini
directions: Marinate bottom round steak in Italian dressing.
In a large skillet, put the dressing and Worcestershire sauce over steak slices.
Cut steak in strips.
Add green peppers, onions, mushrooms, garlic and black pepper.

title: marinade for fajitas
directions: Combine all the
ingredients.
Stir
until
consistent. If more needed to cover fajitas, add more Coke.
Pour marinade over meat.
Place in
refrigerator
overnight
in covered container. Stir meat if possible
at least once.
Place on grill over hot fire.
Cook until done.
Slice across grain.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Saute onions and bell peppers in oil until clear.
Add tomato sauce and paste; cook on low heat for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well and bring to a boil.
Then reduce heat to simmer and cover.
Simmer 1 hour.
Do not lift lid during last hour.

title: lightened chicken tetrazzini amandine
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray pan with nonstick cooking spray. In small saucepan, melt margarine.
Add mushrooms; cook, stirring frequently, for 2 minutes.
Stir in flour; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Pour in broth and 1/2 cup water; stir until blended. Cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring, until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in milk, almonds and basil.
Place spaghetti in pan; top with chicken.
Pour mushroom sauce over chicken; sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: copper carrots
directions: Slice and cook carrots, onion and green pepper for 5 minutes after comes to boil.

title: pumpkin trifle
directions: Set aside 1/4 cup crumbs for topping.
Divide remaining crumbs into 4 portions.
Sprinkle 1 portion into the bottom of a trifle bowl or 3-quart serving bowl.
In a large mixing bowl, combine pumpkin, spices, milk and pudding mixes.
Mix until smooth.
Spoon 1/2 over the crumbs in bowl; sprinkle with second portion of crumbs.
Spread with 1/2 of whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Sprinkle the third portion of crumbs.
Top with remaining pumpkin mixture. Add last portion of crumbs and remaining whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs on top around the edge of the bowl.
Garnish with cherries.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate.
Combine eggs and sugar.
Add the chocolate mixture, the flour, salt, nuts and vanilla, mixing well.
Bake in a greased 9-inch pie pan at 350° for 30 minutes. Just before serving, top with coffee or vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.
Serves 6 to 8.
Freezes well.

title: lime pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill 3 hours.
Top with whipped cream.

title: tortilla chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, 1 cup of cheese, chilies, sandwich spread, onion and cumin; mix lightly.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and remaining cheese.
Stand chips up at edge of casserole; continue microwaving 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: country fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Dip pieces in buttermilk. Coat in seasoned flour.
Fry in electric skillet or covered iron skillet for about 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: old fashioned cornbread pones
directions: Mix all dry ingredients with the water in mixing bowl with a tablespoon.
Mixture will be slightly stiff.
Shape pones by tablespoonful and place in 2 well-greased iron skillets.
Press flat with spoon.
Put drippings of oil on top of each pone.
Place in a 450° preheated oven and bake for 45 minutes or until brown. Makes about 15 pones.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Spread dough in greased cookie pan.
Pour on sauce, then sausage, then cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Mix salmon, milk, eggs, green pepper, butter and salt together.
Mix potato chips and cracker crumbs.
In greased baking dish, alternate layer of salmon and potato chip mixtures.
Bake 30 minutes at 330°.

title: spaghetti pizza pie
directions: Toss cooked spaghetti, Parmesan cheese and egg. Place in 9 inch pie plate. Press along bottom and sides to form crust. Mix cooked meat and spaghetti sauce. Spread meat mixture over spaghetti crust. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting into wedges. Makes 8 servings. You may spoon additional heated spaghetti sauce on serving plate. Top with slice of Spaghetti Pizza Pie.

title: pork chop barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients; add 1 slice lemon and 1 medium onion, sliced.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup catsup and 2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce.
Pour sauce over 6 pork chops (also good on chicken) in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes. Turn chops or chicken during baking process.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add bell pepper, celery, onions and garlic; saute until wilted.
To this add milk and bread mixture; mix real good.
Add crabmeat, green onions and parsley. Pour in a greased pan, 13 x 9-inches.
Top with bread crumbs and butter.
Can also be baked in two small pans, one to freeze.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, water, butter and salt in saucepan and cook, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Continue cooking without stirring, until syrup forms a brittle ball in cold water or reaches 250° on a candy thermometer.
Add vanilla and stir only until mixed through the hot syrup.
Place popcorn in a large bowl. Pour the cooked syrup slowly over the popcorn and mix well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: I used the blender for grating the zucchini.

title: easy brownies
directions: Put all in a bowl and beat 2 minutes.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Watch closely.

title: furikake cereal mix
directions: Heat the butter, sugar, shoyu, Karo syrup and oil until sugar is	dissolved.
Pour
mixture
over
cereal,
then	add furikake. Bake at 250° for 1 hour; stir at 1/2 hour.	Cool on tinfoil.

title: sloppy joe tartlets
directions: Let crust pouches stand at room temperature 15 to 20 minutes. Heat oven to 450°.
Unfold each pie crust, press out lines and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon flour over each crust.
Place crusts, floured side down, on cutting board; peel off remaining plastic. Using 2 1/2-inch round cookie or biscuit cutter, cut 14 or 15 circles from each crust.
Fit circles into ungreased miniature muffin cups, pressing gently.
Prick each crust generously with fork.
Bake at 450° for 9 to 13 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from muffin cups.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; add egg and flavoring.
Mix thoroughly. Sift dry ingredients together and stir in.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Divide dough in half and roll on lightly floured pastry sheet.
Roll thin but thick enough to pick up design of cookie cutter.
Cut as many cookies from each rolling as possible.
The least amount of working with dough gives the best cookies.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes or until delicately golden.
Don't space too close on pan.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix well the peanut butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar; add the Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with chopped peanuts.
Freezes well.

title: streusel topped apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: caramel corn
directions: Spread popped corn and nuts in a large shallow pan and place in preheated 250° oven.

title: italian chicken
directions: Dice chicken and cook in skillet over medium heat. Remove chicken from skillet. Heat olive oil in skillet (remove heat). Saute onion and garlic for 5 minutes. Add tomatoes, sugar and cilantro. Simmer for 20 minutes. Add chicken back to skillet and mushrooms. Serve over pasta of your choice and add salt and pepper to taste.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Mix salt and water in crock about 1/2 full.
Put whole cucumbers in water and let set 14 days.
Remove and slice.
Let set overnight in water and alum.
Rinse and cover well with vinegar for 6 hours.
Pour off vinegar and discard.
Alternate layers of cucumbers, sugar and spice.
Tie up in clean white cloth, put in center of pickles.
Syrup will rise over pickles. Cover pickles.
They do not have to be sealed or refrigerated.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar, shortening, eggs, salt, lemon and vanilla.
Beat together in a separate bowl the sour cream, soda and 1/2 cup flour.
Add to the creamed mixture.
Add remaining 3 cups flour and baking powder.
Chill.
Roll 1/2-inch thick and cut with cookie cutter.
Put on cookie sheet and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: meat dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add mushroom soup, chilies and cheese.
Simmer until well mixed.
Add picante sauce.
If dip is too thick, add enough milk to thin.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Mix first six ingredients together and then mix in apples.

title: congealed salad with cherries
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour in mold and chill for several hours or overnight.
When ready to serve, turn out on lettuce leaves.

title: chicken divan
directions: Slightly brown chicken in the oil.
Add the broth you cooked the chicken in, broccoli, soup, carrots and celery all together. Bring to boil.
Add rice; cover.
Remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese or Cheddar.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Bring water and margarine to rolling boil.
Simmer.
Add flour with dry mustard.
Stir over low heat until mix pulls from side of pot.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in grated Cheddar cheese.

title: mexican meat cups
directions: Roll or pat each biscuit into 3 1/2 inch circles.
Fit over back of greased muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 9 minutes. Meanwhile, brown meat; drain well.
Stir in beans, sandwich sauce and water.
Heat to boiling.
Fill biscuits with meat sauce; top with cheese, lettuce and tomato.

title: chocolate marble cheesecake
directions: Melt chocolate and 1 cup sugar together; put aside until later.
Put soft cream cheese in small pieces in large bowl.
Mix until creamy.
Add 3/4 cup sugar; mix.
