Add sour cream and mix. Add one egg at a time; blend.
Then take another bowl, pour half the batter in it.
Add your chocolate to half of the batter.
Take 2 graham crusts.
Fill them halfway with the chocolate batter, then with plain batter.
Take a knife and work it thorough so it's marbled.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 50 minutes, or until you can put knife in center and it comes out clean.

title: party chickens
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with a strip of bacon.
Cover the bottom of a flat greased baking dish (about 8 x 12 x 2-inch) with chipped beef.
Arrange breasts on chipped beef.
Mix undiluted soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Cover and store in refrigerator overnight, if possible.
Bake chicken in very slow oven at 275°, uncovered, for 3 hours.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer all ingredients slowly until butter melts.
Stir frequently.
Set aside and let stand.
This amount is sufficient for 10 pounds meat.

title: award winning green chile
directions: Brown pork in olive oil in a large pot.
When pork is brown add the flour and brown it also lightly, but be careful that it doesn't burn.
Then add chicken broth, if you like a thick gravy, use less broth, and for thinner use more.
Add all the other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring often.
If you like, you can add cooked pinto beans.

title: quick cheeseburger pie
directions: Mix 1 1/3 cups flour and salt.
Cut
in
shortening
as for pie.
Sprinkle in 1 tablespoon of cold
water
at
a time, stirring with a fork each time.
Pat into
bottom and up sides of an 8 x 2-inch pan or 8 x 1
1/2-inch
round
pan.
Bake
at 425° for 15 minutes.
Brown beef and
onion.
Drain.
Stir
in garlic powder.
Sprinkle with salt and
flour.
Stir in pickle liquid, milk, pickles and 1 cup cheese.
Spoon into pan.
Bake 15 minutes; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until crust is golden, about 5 more minutes.

title: coconut pie with invisible pie crust
directions: Beat eggs well; sift sugar and flour together, combine with eggs and melted butter and other ingredients.
Pour in 9-inch pie pan and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel crackers
directions: Heat oven to 250° and combine crackers and nuts in a large greased shallow baking pan.
In saucepan bring butter, sugar and syrup to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and soda. Pour caramel mixture over crackers and nuts. Stir well.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Pour on waxed paper and let cool.
Then break apart.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind up all ingredients (first 5) with coarse blade.
Put in pillow case and cover with 1/2 cup of salt.
Let stand overnight. Pour cold water over it 3 to 4 times (up and down like washing). Get all salt out.
Squeeze all water out (last time).
Cook for 5 minutes (after boiling point).
Add peppers to syrup and cook 5 more minutes.
Then put into jars.

title: coney island sauce
directions: Brown
ground
beef.
Cook
slowly,
breaking up with a fork until very fine.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 10 minutes, thin with more water if necessary or if too thin cook a few minutes longer.
Makes sauce for 12 hot dogs.

title: champagne salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar.
Stir in strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Blend in topping and pecans.
Pour into container and freeze.
Thaw 1 hour before serving.

title: anniversary punch
directions: Mix sugar, boiling water and Jell-O together. Add remaining ingredients. Divide into 6 gallon size Ziploc bags. Freeze.

title: lemon crumb squares
directions: Blend together milk, juice and lemon rind and set aside.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening; blend sugar.

Add oatmeal and flour mixture and mix until crumbly. Spread half the mixture in an 8 x 12 x 2-inch buttered baking pan and pat down; spread condensed milk mixture over top and cover with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown around edges (about 25 minutes).
Cool in pan at room temperature for 15 minutes; cut into 1 3/4-inch squares and chill in pan until firm.

title: chef's chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bread pudding
directions: In a large bowl beat eggs.
Add milk, sugar, butter, raisins, cinnamon, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Add bread cubes.
Stir gently.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold.
Store in the refrigerator.
Yield:
12 to 16 servings.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Place carrots in boiling salted water; cover and cook for about 10 minutes until tender.
Drain and add butter and sugar. Stir around to cover carrots.

title: french quarter green beans
directions: Cook beans per directions on package or if using cans, drain well.
Melt butter in Dutch oven.
Add soup and cream cheese. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cream cheese is melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in green beans, onion flakes, water chestnuts, garlic salt, pepper and cheese.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 1 3/4-quart casserole dish.
Top with almonds.
Sprinkle on paprika.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, 45 minutes.

title: fat-free creamy honey dijon dressing
directions: Combine and whisk until smooth.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix oleo and sugar together. Add bananas; cut in thin slices. Mix until blended. Add eggs and buttermilk. Beat in flour, soda and nuts. Pour in greased bread pans. Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°. Freezes well.

title: lemon slices
directions: Mix butter, powdered sugar and 2 cups flour like pie dough. Pat into ungreased pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
While crust is baking, mix eggs (unbeaten), rind and juice, sugar and 4 tablespoons flour.
Mix well and pour into hot crust.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Remove from oven and while still hot, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
If out of lemons, 6 tablespoons lemon juice and 1/4 teaspoon salt equals whole lemon.

title: stuffed peppers for two
directions: Cut tops off peppers and discard; remove seeds. Blanch peppers in boiling water for 5 minutes. Drain in cold water. Set aside. In a bowl, combine ground beef, tomato sauce (1/4 cup), uncooked rice, 2 tablespoons cheese, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and egg. Mix well. Spoon mixture into peppers. Place peppers in an ungreased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Pour remaining tomato sauce over peppers. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese; return to oven for 5 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Crust:
Spread out crescent rolls in two pans.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: sausage and sweet potato dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Break sausage into small pieces and cook until lightly browned.
Remove sausage from pan and set aside.
Cook onion and celery in sausage.
Grease until onion is transparent.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and add to sausage.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake for one hour.
Remove cover the last 30 minutes of baking time.

title: stir-fry eggs with tomatoes(brunch treat)
directions: Beat eggs with sherry and 1/2 teaspoon salt; set aside.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in wok.
Stir-fry tomatoes with sugar and 1/2 teaspoon salt for 2 minutes.
Remove and set aside.
Reheat wok with 2 tablespoons oil.
Pour beaten eggs into wok and gently stir-fry until almost done.
Add tomatoes and green onions and stir until set.
Serve immediately.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine cocktail, pineapple and juice with pudding until thick.
Add oranges, bananas, cherries and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Beat egg in Cool Whip; add cake mix. Chill. Make balls and roll in powdered sugar. Bake at 350°.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Beat
eggs
until light and fluffy.
Add other ingredients. Pour
into	the unbaked pie shells and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: florida sunshine(fruit salad)
directions: Cook pudding until thick; stir in frozen orange juice (let cool).
Slice 4 to 6 bananas; mix with fruit.
When pudding gets cold, put on top of fruit.
Don't stir until you serve.

title: marshmallow dainty
directions: Pour 2 or 3 tablespoons of warm water over marshmallows; leave on back of stove until dissolved.
Stir in egg whites, beaten stiff; add nuts, pineapple and flavor.
Put in cool place to set.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chocolate coconut balls
directions: Melt syrup and marshmallow cream together.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Roll into balls and chill.
Dip in melted chocolate.

title: cherry bran bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and 1/2 cup sugar.
Set aside.
Combine cereal and milk.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Beat in egg and oil.
Stir in flour mixture.
Set aside 2 tablespoons chopped cherries.
Fold remaining cherries and 3/4 cup nuts in batter.
Spread in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Heat margarine in small frypan until bubbly.
Remove from heat. Stir in 1/4 cup sugar, 1/4 cup nuts and reserved cherries. Sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: date casserole cookies
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and mix well.
Add nuts, dates, coconut, vanilla and almond extract.
Mix and bake in greased casserole for 25 minutes at 350°.
Stir a few times.
Let cool and stir while cooling.
When cool enough to handle, roll into balls.
Roll in coconut; top with a cherry.

title: lobster quiche
directions: Sprinkle lobster, cheese and onion into pastry shell.
Beat eggs.
Pour cream into eggs.
Add pepper and parsley flakes. Bake 15 minutes at 425°. Reduce heat to 300°. Bake 35 to 40 minutes before serving.

title: lemon pumpkin pie
directions: Beat egg whites until they hold peaks.
Mix other ingredients together.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in prepared crust at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Simmer for at least an hour.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl mix together the oleo, sugar sweetener and egg.
Add flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and baking soda.
Mix in applesauce.
Fold in all-bran buds, raisins and nuts; mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Lightly flatten each cookie with fork dipped in milk.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Note:
Don't grease pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.

title: raisin sauce for ham
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Slowly add remaining ingredients.
Stir over low heat until thick.
Makes 2 cups.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add chopped green pepper.
Add cooked rice.
Salt to taste, bay leaf and cloves.
Add tomatoes.
Simmer 15 or 20 minutes.
Take out bay leaf and cloves.

title: spiced fruit bake
directions: Drain juice thoroughly from fruit but save 2 teaspoons pineapple juice.
Arrange pineapple, pears, peaches and apricots in 2-quart casserole; add maraschino cherries to taste.
Melt butter; add pineapple juice, ginger, brown sugar and cinnamon. Pour this mixture over fruit.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: mom's brown sugar cookies
directions: Combine ingredients and chill dough for 20 minutes. Shape into small balls. Roll into granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press flat with a bottom of glass.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix buttermilk, oil and egg. Add to sifted flour.
Mix all ingredients. Pour batter onto hot griddle.
These can be made and frozen until ready to serve.

title: cheerwine ice cream
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in ice cream freezer.
Chop jar of cherries into little bits and add to freezer.
Finish filling with whole milk.
Freeze 30 to 40 minutes until freezer stops.

title: spinach-cheese mushroom caps
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms. Set aside. Finely chop the stems. In a skillet, saute the chopped mushrooms, onion and garlic in oil until tender. In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, Feta cheese, bacon, salt and mushroom mixture. Spoon into mushroom caps. Sprinkle with the remaining Parmesan cheese. Place on a baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and jello in the hot water.
Add sugar and lemon juice; stir and chill until partially set.
Add everything else.

title: orange slice squares
directions: Gradually add sugar to beaten eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients over candy and nuts until each piece is coated. Combine mixtures; stir until well mixed.
Pour into a greased shallow pan (15 x 11 x 12-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown beef and sausage together.
Drain fat. Put in crock-pot. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and serve when warm.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
Mix sugars and cinnamon in bowl. Put in plastic bag.
Shake cut biscuits in sugar-cinnamon mixture. Place biscuits in greased Bundt pan.
Put any leftover sugar-cinnamon mixture on top.
Pour on melted butter.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: london broil marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients in a small bowl.
Pour over London Broil and marinate overnight.
You may adjust the seasonings to suit your taste.

title: cherry cheesecake muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 12 muffin cups with paper liners or grease muffin cups.
With an electric mixer, beat cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 egg until smooth.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl combine the flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add the milk, egg, and oil and stir together just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Add the cherries and stir together. Spoon the batter into muffin cups, about 1/2 full each.
Spoon a layer of the cream cheese mixture over the batter in each cup. Add spoonfuls of batter on top of the cream cheese layer until 2/3 or more full.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Remove from oven and let cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stir first 5 ingredients together.
Bake in a 9 x 13 pan at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving sprinkle chow mein noodles and reheat to brown slightly. Some people mixed the noodles in and baked and then added some on top - great both ways.

title: lamb pilaf
directions: Brown lamb and onions until very dark.
Stir constantly. Place in a casserole with the seasonings, water and rice.
Be sure to add salt for the rice.
Cover and bake in a moderate oven until rice is cooked and water is absorbed.

title: milnot cheese cake
directions: Melt oleo.
Add crumbs and spread in pie plate, 9-inch.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Cream together first 2 ingredients.
Add eggs to creamed mixture.
Alternately add flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Mix in nuts and lemon peel.
Bake in greased loaf pan for one hour at 350°.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar and lemon juice.
Pour over hot baked loaf after first poking holes in top of loaf so juice will go through evenly.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine soup, milk and pepper in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onions and sauce.
Dot top with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover.

title: green kale soup
directions: Cover ham with
water;
cook
until
tender.
Add water whenever necessary. Add ground kale, onions, carrots and rice. Cook over low heat 1/2
to
hour, until kale is well cooked and blended.
If kale
is
at
all
tough,
do not add carrots until last half hour.
This soup must be salty to be good.

title: louisiana shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients except shrimp and simmer until butter is melted.
In a single layer, place shrimp in a casserole and cover with butter mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with lots of hot French bread to dip in butter sauce.
Peel shrimp as you eat them.

title: bread pudding
directions: In a pot, heat milk. Blend in bread cubes and butter. In a bowl, combine sugar, salt, raisins and eggs.
Blend milk mixture into egg mixture. Pour into greased baking dish.
Place in a pan of hot water. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix and drop by spoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: In a bowl, mix nuts, dates and cherries.
In another bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Mix and add to fruit mixture.
Beat eggs until frothy; stir in vanilla.
Fold in fruit mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and waxed loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan before removing to wire rack.

title: monkey bread
directions: In a bowl, stir together the sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits into quarters and roll in spiced sugar.
Throw into a greased Bundt pan.
Add remaining sugar and cinnamon on top.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Place shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla in mixing bowl. Beat thoroughly. Sift together flour, salt, soda and add to shortening mixture. Mix well. Blend in oats. Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: fried cheese meltaways
directions: Heat 2-inches of oil in fryer at 375°.
Beat biscuit mix, egg and milk until smooth.
Cut cheese into 3/4-inch cubes.
Coat cubes lightly with dry biscuit mix.
Insert fork or toothpick into each cube and dip in batter, coating completely.
Fry a few at a time, turning carefully, until golden brown (1 to 2 minutes). Drain on paper towels.
Makes 40 to 45.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Alternate the ground chuck, onion and vegetables in a casserole.
Add cream soup.
Top this with cheese; layer the top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° until it gets bubbly or brown.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish, place slightly thawed hash browns.
Pour melted butter over potatoes.
Mix soup, milk, sour cream, salt, pepper and onion. Then pour over potatoes.
Top with grated cheese and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: plum torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour, baking powder and eggs and beat well.
Spoon batter into a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Arrange plum halves face down in batter. Sprinkle lightly with sugar and lemon juice, depending on sweetness of the fruit.
Sprinkle on cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for `1 hour.
Batter will rise and cover plums.
Remove and cool; refrigerate or freeze, if desired.
Or, cool to lukewarm and serve with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.
To serve frozen tortes, defrost and reheat briefly at 300°.
Yield:
8 servings. Approximately cook time:
1 hour.

title: fire-and-ice pickles
directions: Combine pickles, sugar, hot sauce and pepper flakes in a large bowl; stir well.
Cover and let stand 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Spoon pickles into pint canning jars.
Add a clove of garlic to each jar.
Cover with metal lids and screw on bands. Store in refrigerator.
Yield:
3 pints.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Cook in acidulated water 5 minutes; drain and cool.
Finely chop shrimp, cream butter and beat in shrimp.
Add mace, salt and pepper to taste.
Put in mold and chill well.
Turn out, garnish plate and serve with crackers. Yield:
1 1/2 cups shrimp butter.

title: green bean and fresh basil salad
directions: Trim the beans and bring the water to a boil.
Add 2 tablespoons salt and the trimmed beans.
Cook at a rapid boil until beans are tender, but still crisp, from 3 to 10 minutes, depending on size.
Drain in colander and run under cold water to stop cooking.
Drain again and let cool.
Place in bowl.

title: potato souffle
directions: Combine the milk, salt, margarine, mustard, cheese and pepper. Mix well.
Add hot mashed potatoes.
Separate the eggs and beat both separately.
Add beaten yolks to potato mixture and mix lightly.
Fold in beaten whites.
Pour mixture into greased souffle dish or casserole and bake at 350°
for 50 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown hamburger meat, then add spaghetti sauce and cook on low until thoroughly heated.

title: easy chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; add eggs and beat well after each egg.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Put in a well-greased tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool before turning out.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat on high until mixture is light and fluffy.

title: herb omelet
directions: Scramble and cook eggs until bottom is set.
Add remaining ingredients as filling and fold egg over.
Cook until middle is set.

title: lemon cuke molded salad
directions: Soften Jell-O in 1/2 cup hot water; add sugar substitute.
Add remaining ingredients except mayonnaise and cukes.
Add mayonnaise and cukes after Jell-O begins to set.
Place in mold and let set. Makes 4 servings.
One serving has 55 calories.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add milk.
Fold in beaten whites. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake until firm.
Nutmeg and a little white sugar may be sprinkled on top before baking if desired.

title: buttermilk borsch
directions: Put 1/2 cup beets and remaining ingredients in blender with 1/2 cup ice cubes and whirl 30 seconds.
Serve in mugs topped with a few shoestring beets, if desired.
Makes 2 1/2 cups or 2 servings, about 90 calories each (without topping).

title: play dough
directions: Take 2 heaping cups of patience, 1 heart full of love, 2 hands full of generosity, a dash of laughter and 1 head full of understanding.
Sprinkle generously with kindness and plenty of faith; mix well.
Spread over a period of a lifetime and serve everybody you meet.

title: gwen's chili
directions: In big skillet, fry hamburger, green pepper, onion, salt and pepper until hamburger is brown.
Drain excess oil.
Add Hormel hot chili with beans.
Add tomato sauce.
Let simmer 10 minutes on low heat.
If too much for skillet, let simmer in a pot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir onion and mushrooms in oleo until onion is tender.
Add enough water to mushroom liquid to measure 1 1/2 cups.
Stir into onion/mushroom mixture with celery, bean sprouts, soy sauce and sugar.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 15 minutes.
Blend the 3 tablespoons water and cornstarch; stir into vegetable mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in chicken; heat through.
Serve over chow mein noodles.

title: french onion sloppy joes
directions: Cook ground sirloin in pan on top of stove; drain liquid. Sprinkle 3 tablespoons flour over ground sirloin and stir until dissolved.
Pour the French onion soup over the ground sirloin and simmer until thickened.
Just takes a few minutes.
Serve on your favorite sandwich rolls.
A good alternative to the "tomato" Sloppy Joes!

title: emerald salad
directions: Heat liquid and dissolve gelatin in it. Allow it to set.
Whip with mixer and fold in the remaining ingredients.
Set in a large mold or several individual ones and allow to set.

title: hornet's nest cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed.
Mix cooked pudding and cake mix together (no eggs or milk).
Spread butterscotch morsels and pecan halves on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Cook broccoli.
I slit top of box and put in microwave on high for 5 minutes.
Take 4 crescent rolls.
Press them flat into a round pie plate, making a bottom crust coming up on sides.
Mix all of the other ingredients, pressing them down into crust.
Take remaining crescent rolls, unroll, and make a top crust.
Bake at 375 degrees or until brown.
(4 servings.)

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Add the rest of the ingredients in the order given.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetarian meatballs
directions: Grind crackers, nuts, cheese and onions.
Beat eggs well; mix all together.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil and fry until brown on each side.
(Watch carefully as they brown fast.)
Place in large pan and cover with tomato juice.
Simmer 45 minutes or bake in casserole 35 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Prepare vegetables and toss together.
Set aside.
Mix vinegar, sugar, pimiento, oil, mustard, seed and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Let cool a while.
Pour over cabbage.
Toss.
Set in refrigerator.

title: grammy's chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken.
Cut into bite-sized pieces.
Mix and heat soups, onion, chilies, cheese and broth.
Add cooked spaghetti and chicken.
Heat in a 350° oven in a 9 x 13-inch pan until bubbly.

title: company chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in a greased baking dish and cover with Swiss cheese slices.
Mix soup, sour cream and wine well and pour over cheese and chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing over top and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: tropical pineapple smoothies
directions: Place the first 6 ingredients in a blender; cover and process until smooth. Add ice cubes. Cover and process until smooth. Yield: 3 servings.

title: potluck jello pineapple salad
directions: Step #1:
Take 1 package of strawberries and 1 can pineapple. Strain juices from fruit and set aside.
In mixing bowl, dissolve 1 package jello in 1 3/4 cups hot water.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch plastic container. Add fruit. Stir to mix. Add cold water to reserved juices to make a total of 1 3/4 cups.
Add to jello-fruit mixture.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in a 2-quart dish.
Mix Veg-All, soup and chicken broth and pour over chicken.
Mix margarine, flour and milk and pour on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into oiled 10-inch iron skillet and bake at 450° until brown (20 to 25 minutes).

title: *rahmschnitzel(veal cutlets in sour cream sauce)
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons margarine, then remove from pan.
Add remaining 2 tablespoons margarine to the pan.
Season veal cutlets with salt and pepper; dredge in flour. Saute until golden brown.
Add onion and mushrooms, soup stock, lemon juice and sherry; heat.
Add sour cream and stir.
Simmer slowly until cream is well heated (do not boil).
Serve with rice.

title: tomato provencale
directions: Cut tomato into halves crosswise.
Place cut side up in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste. Top with butter and
cornflake
crumbs.
Bake
at
until tender. Yields 2 servings.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Boil for 1 minute the first 5 ingredients (if boiled too long, tends to get dry; I undercook a bit as I like chewy).
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Mix well and drop by spoonful on wax paper.
Cool on a cookie sheet. Store in refrigerator.

title: spicy beef dip
directions: Lightly brown ground beef and pour off excess fat.
Add onion and garlic; cook until onion is tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, catsup, oregano and sugar.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Remove from heat and add cheeses.
Stir until cream cheese is melted and well combined.
Serve warm.
Makes 3 cups of dip.

title: carrot cake muffins
directions: Combine flour, soda and cinnamon. Set aside.
Mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla, stirring until well blended.
Add flour mixture; stir lightly. Add carrots, coconut and pineapple.
Mix until just combined.
Fill muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm. Can also be made into small loaves.
Makes 16 to 18.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix with all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Let sauce cook until pepper and onion are tender.
Simmer until spaghetti noodles are done.
Drain and serve.

title: craft recipe
directions: Mix to form dough.
Roll out in additional cinnamon.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Let dry two days.
Paint if you wish.
Put wires through for ornaments or magnets for refrigerator.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix the sugar and salad oil together.
Beat the 4 eggs and pumpkin together with sugar mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add 1/2 dry ingredients and 1/3 cup water to sugar/egg mixture.
Mix well.
Add rest of dry ingredients and 1/3 cup water to mixture and mix well.
Beat on medium-high for 2 minutes.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until lightly browned.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool.
Freezes well.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt Cheez Whiz in large mixing bowl. Add milk.
Add Bisquick, a cup at a time, and mix with spoon.
Add sausage.
Mix with hands.
Make into balls about the size of a walnut.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 15 minutes. Makes approximately 50 balls.

title: parm-a-chicken
directions: Combine cheese, flour and seasonings.
Dip chicken in combined egg and milk; coat with cheese mixture.
Place in baking dish. Pour melted butter over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini-pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs. Add oil, sugar and vanilla. Beat until light and foamy.
Stir
in
zucchini	and pineapple.	Combine flour, soda, salt, baking
powder,
cinnamon,
nuts and raisins. Stir gently into zucchini mixture.
Bake
in
greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans at 350° for
hour
or until tested done.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes with water, just enough to cover.
Add diced onion.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add cream of celery soup. Blend well.
Add all of the half and half.
Blend well.
Cook until very hot, but not boiling.
Dip into bowls and top with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Place rhubarb in bowl. Combine beaten eggs with milk, sugar, flour, salt, nutmeg and mix with rhubarb.
Pour into unbaked pastry lined pie plate.
Dot butter or margarine over top.
May be covered with lattice top or leave uncovered or top with crumb topping.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery.
Drain grease off.
Add soups, vegetables and mushrooms.
Mix in the chow mein noodles.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pie
directions: Melt butter for filling in a saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Add broth, milk and seasoning.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add chicken and vegetables, heat thoroughly.
Pour filling into casserole dish.
Top with your own pastry crust or Bisquick or ready made pie crust.
Bake at 400° (hot oven) 30 minutes or until browned.

title: fried bread
directions: Combine
flour, baking powder and salt; cut in shortening until
coarse crumbs form.
Add water gradually; mix just enough to
hold
together.
Turn
out
onto a lightly floured board. Knead
gently
until smooth.
Cover and let rest for 5 minutes. Roll into a 12 x 15-inch rectangle.
Dough should be very thin. Cut
into 3-inch squares.
Drop a few squares at a time into deep hot oil.
Turn squares 3 or 4 times at first to make them
puff evenly.
Fry
or 3 minutes on each side or until golden
brown. The
squares
will puff up as they cook. Serve hot with honey and butter.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: coconut cream dessert
directions: Take crackers and crush them up. Melt stick butter over crackers. Mix together pudding, milk and ice cream.
Pour over crackers.
Put Cool Whip on top.
Pour coconut flakes over top. Refrigerate several hours.

title: mashed potatoes with cheese
directions: Cook 3 medium potatoes in saucepan until done.
Drain.
Put potatoes, milk, butter, salt and cheese in bowl.
Mix with an electric beater until creamy.

title: lasagna
directions: Fry hamburger meat.
Put noodles in pot and boil while cooking meat.
Simmer meat about 30 minutes, then layer your noodles and sour cream and cheeses.
Put in oven until cheese is melted.
Bake at 350°.

title: brown sugar oatmeal pancakes
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine egg, oil and buttermilk.
Combine flours, baking soda, salt and sugar; add to egg mixture, stir in oats.
Pour in 1/3 cupfuls onto lightly greased hot griddle.
Turn when bubbles form on top of pancakes.

title: cheese tassies(dessert)
directions: Cream together (with mixer) cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Put a vanilla wafer in each cake paper and fill each with mixture almost to the top.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool and top with pie filling (use midget cake papers.)
Yields approximately 3 dozen.

title: aunt mae's freezer beans
directions: Drop beans in boiling water.
Take out; put them in ice water. Put on towel and dry.
Put in freezer containers and freeze.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, flour and salt.
Stir until it makes a paste.
Add onion, sour cream and Swiss cheese and mix until creamy.
Mix with green beans and put into a greased casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: spring potato tart
directions: Peel potatoes and slice 1/8-inch thick.
Place half the potato slices in greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and basil.
Top with layers of sliced onion, asparagus and tomato slices, sprinkling each layer with salt and basil.
Top with remaining potato slices; sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Remove cover and continue to bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Split potatoes partially lengthwise.
Then cut across about 3 times, depending on size of potato.
Sprinkle garlic salt, salt and pepper between slices.
Generously spread with butter between slices and on top.
Bake in foil at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add bananas and eggs and beat well.
Mix and sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk and vanilla to sugar mixture.
Add nuts last.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) layer pans which have been greased.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with favorite icing.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Add all ingredients together. Mix well and cook for 1 hour at 300°. Serves 4.

title: fruit and nut crisp
directions: Spread cherry pie filling and pineapple into bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour dry cake mix over this.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix (margarine will not saturate all cake mix).
Layer coconut and nuts on top.
Bake in a 325° oven for 55 to 60 minutes. Should be golden brown.
May bake longer if you like a crisper crust. Serve warm or cold and if desired, top with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: robert's cream of potato soup
directions: Boil ham, celery, onion, salt and pepper until ham is tender. Remove ham; dice in small cubes.
Add enough water to ham broth to equal 3 quarts.
Return to burner.
Add potatoes, garlic and parsley flakes.
Boil until potatoes are tender.
Mash potatoes with wire whisk until they are coarsely mashed.
Mix cornstarch and cream; add to potato mixture.
Bring to a boil and serve hot.

title: iowa baked pork chops with sauerkraut
directions: Brown pork chops.
Sprinkle with salt.
Pour sauerkraut into large (at least 3 inches deep) casserole dish or pan which has been lined with aluminum foil.
Spread evenly and place browned chops over this layer of kraut.
Cover pork chops with additional kraut and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.

title: raisin cheesecake cookies
directions: Mix cream cheese with sugar until light.
Beat until smooth. Spread mixture over baked crust and sprinkle reserved crumbs over top.
Return to oven and bake 30 minutes or until set in center. Cool to room temperature.
Cut into bite size squares.
Store covered in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Can be frozen.

title: creamy sweet corn
directions: In a saucepan, combine corn and half and half. Stir in the butter, salt and sugar. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Reduce heat and let simmer, uncovered, 8 to 10 minutes or until heated thoroughly. Sprinkle on black pepper and serve.

title: cheesy beef or turkey stuffed peppers(serves 6)
directions: Place peppers in a 2-quart (12 x 7-inch) glass baking dish; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients, except shredded cheese, in medium mixing bowl; mix well.
Spoon meat mixture into green pepper halves.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave for 25 to 30 minutes on Medium-high (roast) or until meat is well done (about 140°).
Top with shredded cheese and continue cooking on Medium-high (roast) until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate cherry cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, eggs and oil.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop teaspoonfuls of dough onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
These cookies are simple to make and taste like chocolate-covered cherry candy.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a very large bowl, layer ingredients in the order listed (from the bottom of the bowl up).
Cover and refrigerate.
This can stay for days in the fridge.
In fact, if it sits for 24 hours before serving, it tastes better.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients with an electric mixer until smooth.
Pour into 2 large or 5 small greased loaf pans.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: date-nut brownies
directions: In top of double boiler, melt chocolate and butter over simmering water.
Set aside.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: For Chocolate Sour Cream Fudge, follow recipe and add 2 squares (each 1 ounce) unsweetened chocolate with the vanilla.
Do not stir.
Cool and continue as recipe directs.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In ungreased square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches, stir together flour, granulated sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa. Mix in milk, oil and vanilla with fork until smooth. Stir in nuts. Spread evenly in pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa. Pour hot water gently over batter. Bake 40 minutes. Let stand 15 minutes. Spoon into dessert dishes and top with ice cream. Makes its own chocolate sauce.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: In iron skillet, put the margarine, onion and celery. Cook until onion is golden brown. Add frozen broccoli and heat until broccoli is separated and thawed.
Add the Cheez Whiz and stir until it is completely melted.
Add the milk and soup. Add the rice and mix well.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: a quick, delicious chicken or turkey breast recipe
directions: Mix oil and lemon juice in one bowl.
Mix Bisquick, grated cheese and pepper in another bowl. Dip chicken in the first bowl, then into the second bowl.
Saute in some butter or margarine. Squeeze fresh lemon on top
when serving.

title: orange pineapple ice cream
directions: Combine Orange Crush, pineapple and Eagle Brand.
Pour into ice cream freezer canister.
Follow directions for your freezer. Mix well until firm.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour in enough marinade to immerse meat halfway; then cover dish.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight, but no longer than 24 hours.
Turn occasionally.
Cubed meats should be marinated only 2 to 3 hours.
Grill or broil to desired doneness.
Excellent on beef, chicken or pork.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Melt margarine
and blend in cocoa. Add sugar and eggs; stir well.
Add
flour
and
vanilla.
Bake
in a 350° oven in greased and floured
9 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overcook!
As
soon as brownies are removed from oven, top with marshmallows
and
sprinkle
with nuts.
Frost with Fudge Frosting.

title: coconut dream cake
directions: Mix cake mix by directions.
Bake cake mix.
While hot, stick full of holes.
Pour milk and cream of coconut on top of cake.
Let cool.
Put Cool whip on top of cake.
Sprinkle coconut on top. Sprinkle with nuts.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: butterscotch spiders
directions: Melt
butterscotch,
then mix peanuts and noodles; drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.
Good luck!

title: upside-down delight
directions: Cook bacon; drain and crumble.
Reserve 3 tablespoons drippings.
Arrange green pepper rings in heavy 10-inch iron skillet.
Place olives and corn around peppers.
Spoon corn over peppers.
Saute onion, garlic and meat in bacon drippings until meat is lightly browned.
Add to meat the salt, tomato juice, chili powder, lemon rind, parsley, chives, Worcestershire, steak sauce and Accent.
Spoon over corn.
Prepare corn bread mix according to package directions.
Spoon over meat mixture.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; cover for 5 minutes. Turn upside-down on dry platter.
Serve in wedges.
Yield: 8 to 10 generous servings.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Trim fat off brisket.
Marinate brisket overnight with garlic, celery salt and liquid smoke.
Next morning, bake in a slow oven in marinade for 6 to 8 hours at 300° to 325°, according to size of brisket.
When done, take out of oven and set for 30 minutes. Slice and put in serving dish.
Put barbecue sauce on meat and bake 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; add beaten eggs just until mixture is moist.
Fold in zucchini; fry in butter.

title: oven baked eggnog french toast
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, cut French bread crosswise into 16 slices, arranging on a jelly roll pan or cookie sheet; overlap if necessary.
Mix next 4 ingredients with eggs.
Pour over bread, turning slices occasionally to absorb all liquid. Arrange slices on greased cookie sheets and bake at 500° for 8 to 10 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Serves 8.
Good.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Cut steak in 2 x 2-inch strips.
Combine all ingredients in a 5-quart Dutch oven.
Add meat and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Grill on barbecue grill after draining.

title: rice and red kidney beans
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add onion, pepper and garlic.
Cook and stir until tender, but not browned. Stir in broth, beans, tomatoes and oregano; bring to boil.
Stir in rice.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir.
Cover; let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 low-fat servings.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash the spinach and pat dry.
Tear into bowl. Top with sliced eggs and bacon.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine sugar and flour.
Stir in the pineapple juice, then add the cheese to that.
Mix all ingredients well.
Spoon into greased casserole dish.
Combine melted butter and cracker crumbs.
Stir well and sprinkle over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: john's ribs #2
directions: Trim excess fat from ribs.
Cut into single bone.
Cut into squares, 2 x 2-inch size.
Put ribs in deep frying pan.
Add the rest of the ingredients except the bay leaves.
Mix well by hand so that all the meat is well seasoned.
Put 2 bay leaves on top of meat.
Cover and cook on low heat until meat is simmering.
Mix again and separate each piece from each other.
Turn heat to medium and cook for 1 hour or until the meat is tender.
Take cover off and continue cooking until only oil is left.
Drain fat.
Serve hot.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
To the juice, add lemon juice and cornstarch.
Cook until clear and then add NutraSweet.
Cut grapes in half.
Cut apples and kiwi into bite size pieces; add to drained pineapple.

title: strawberry delite
directions: Mix flour and butter together.
Press on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown.
Cool.

title: artichoke appetizers
directions: Drain marinade from 1 jar of artichokes into sauteing pan. Discard other marinade.
Chop artichokes; set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in marinade until onion is limp, about 5 minutes.
Beat eggs until fluffy, then add bread crumbs, salt, pepper, oregano and Tabasco.
Stir in cheese, parsley, artichokes and onion mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 11 x 7-inch baking pan. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes before cutting. Makes 4 dozen appetizers.
